text: Saya dan tunangan saya baru saja menginap di Prahda Village selama 2 minggu. Sungguh luar biasa. Staf di Prahda Village sangat menakjubkan. Mereka sangat membantu dan saya tak pernah bertemu orang-orang sebaik mereka. Lokasi Prahda Village (menurut saya) ada di bagian terbaik di Seminyak. Letaknya jauh dari kebisingan jalan utama tapi hanya butuh 5 menit untuk pergi ke sana. Kami Prahda karena lokasinya karena kami bisa berjalan kaki ke pantai La Lucciolla, Potato Head, Ku De Ta. Bodyworks dan Sea Circus (bagus untuk sarapan) letaknya 100 m dari sini. Kita bisa berjalan ke kebanyak tempat. Vilanya sempurna. Kolam renang pribadi yang hebat, ranjang yang besar dengan kamar mandi di dalam dan ruang tengah yang luas. Bonus pijatnya menakjubkan dan sarapannya sangat lezat. Sangat sulit untuk menemukan kekurangannya. Kami pasti akan menginap di sini lagi.
title: Prahda - Menakjubkan

text: Tinggal di Pradha Vilas selama seminggu di bulan November dan terkesan dengan kualitas akomodasinya, juga dengan lokasi yang sangat baik, dekat dengan pantai dan Petitengenet beberapa bar terbaik & restoran terbaik di Seminyak (Kudeta, Lucciola, Potato Head ... ). Namun tempat itu damai, jauh dari jalan utama. Para stafnya sopan dan ramah. Mereka benar-benar bekerja ekstra untuk menyenangkan pelanggan: kami memiliki masalah dengan AC di kamar tidur dan manajer memberi respons cepat dan bahkan menawarkan peningkatan villa jika kami masih tidak senang dengan suhu di dalam kamar. Jika sedang tidak berselera untuk keluar makan siang atau makan malam, layanan di villa menawarkan makanan yang lezat dan tidak mahal.
title: Layanan luar biasa dan tempat peristirahatan yang tenang di Seminyak

text: Yes the place might be a little tired but it was so good. The Villa was perfect and spacious with your own pvt tranquil pool. Staff was always helpful and made sure you were happy with your room and experience. Would recommend this place to anyone.
title: Perfect accommodation

text:
Amazing location down a tree lined alley in the heart of Seminyak, don’t worry about breakfast as healthy options Clean Canteen, Sisterfields around the corner... if you are a sun lover you MUST insist on a pool villa with sun! We are waiting to move to one ... will update to see if we do but hard when booked out. Nice villa, needs a bit of tlc... but always good to be with these beautiful people. Cheers hope this helps 
Not Villa 12 or this side
title: Perfect location...info for sun lovers

text:
Travelled as a couple in July, chose to finish our 2 week trip with 4 nights in a one person pool villa. 

The villa itself was beautiful and luxurious - the open style bathroom with double basin and waterfall shower was amazing. The four poster bed was comfy and every night they came into our villa and lit mosquito coils and provided a turn down service which was a really nice touch. There was a huge selection for breakfast and always too much delicious food!! 
We loved relaxing in our villa and they fit in the housekeeping service around our schedule. 

The pool was a little bit cold due to being in the shade most of the day but it was at least refreshing! 

Location was 10/10. Walking distance to the cool bars and restaurants (motel mexicola 1 minute away,  boss man burgers 3 mins walk away). Approx 4 mins to get onto the beach. Also close by to potato head, the W and some luxe restaurants including Merah Putih for delicious indo food. 

A little bit of traffic noise (to be expected anywhere in Seminyak) but otherwise tranquil and quiet. The staff were lovely and arranged everything we needed. 

Loved our stay and will be back!!
title: Hidden oasis in the middle of Seminyak

text:
For our first trip to Bali, this was a perfect place to stay! The location was great with many destinations within walking distance. Seminyak Square and Seminyak Village were 2 minutes from the villa and Ku De Ta an extra 5 minutes from there on the beach front. From there you can walk along the beach for roughly 10 mins and arrive at Potato Head. Hotel Mexicola is also a minutes walk from the villa! The one bedroom villa was very big and spacious with a large family room, bedroom with air conditioning, a large bathroom, nice and modern facilities (best bed I have ever slept in). The one bedroom villa had a big clean pool and hot tub which was perfect for couples! The staff at Pradha villas were very professional, friendly and helpful. It had 24hr security which was great. The breakfast included was very good, with a large variety to choose from such as eggs and sandwiches, as well as side dishes such as pancakes and banana bread. It was such a big brekkie it would often keep us full through lunchtime! Room service came at a cheap price. The villa was very well kept with daily thorough housekeeping. Staff came into villa twice in the afternoon/night to spray mosquito spray- therefore we had no issues with bugs. We booked a massage through Pradha which was very cheap, and the staff set up in our villa which was nice. 
I would definitely recommend this place, I plan to go back hopefully in the near future!
title: Beautiful villa, great location, amazing experience.

text:
You get much more that you expect. THE 2 BEDROOM POOL VILLA was posh,spic and span,very well maintained spacious and super awesome.When we checked in I thought the location was a bit odd and a kind of awkward approach as it's in a back lane.But soon realized that this location made the stay quite and peacefull. It's just 300mtrs from seminyak square within walking distance to  everything. Beach was 3 mins walk..night clubs like ku de ta and potato head 5mins walk.
Breakfast was excellent and floating breakfast was like a welcome surprise..The private pool was pretty BIG  and a jacuzzi next to it was like Icing on the cake. Bathrooms were big size and had open air showers..Room were big with comfy beds.Staff was super polite and ready to help. Even the smallest needs were attended to with prompt attention..Room service menu was good and reasonable. Complimentary afternoon mocktails were nice too! We loved every bit of our 3night stay and highly recommend this property.
title: Incredible experience..awesome property

text: Amazing. We stayed in 2br villa with pool. Its walking distance to the beach, nice bars,  mexicola and seminyak square yet very quiet. Very friendly staff and breakfast is amazing. Very clean and secure. One of the best villas I've stayed in.
title: Amazing villa to stay in seminyak

text: This is our first Bali holiday in a villa and this place was fantastic. It is a short walk to Eat Street, so well located. Very quiet and you wouldn't know we were near civilisation. The staff couldn't be more helpful. The villa was well maintained, the pool was larger than expected, the gardens were well looked after. The breakfast selection was larger as were the serves, more than we could eat. The room service menu was a bit limited but everything we tried was great. Would like to see more Indonesian snacks on the menu for when we were to lazy to go out for lunch. Only complaints was the lounge wasn't as comfortable as I would have liked and a microwave would have been a good addition. The drink prices in the mini bar were so good I didn't bother buying any at the Mini mart, in some cases it was cheaper.
title: Highly recommend - fantasitic stay

text: The villa has a private pool and outdoor bathroom which we have enjoyed. Great location- quite close to the beach, cafes, restaurants such as sea circus, motel mexicola, seminyak square, and neon palms. Rooms are always made and Towels are replaced everyday. Floating breakfast was amazing. Definitely request this when you choose your breakfast preference while checking in. Luggage storage also available if you end up arriving early or leaving late. Wifi is good. A little bit on the expensive side but worth it especially if you want a relaxing and peaceful holiday. There are mosquitoes at night but staff always put mosquito coils outdoors and spray repellants in the afternoon. Will be back next time we’re in Seminyak.
title: Excellent

text:
I was so happy to have choose Pradha Villa for our honeymoon, we were there Dec 3rd 2018. The villa was very spacious and the pool was clean(compared to many other villas in Bali). 

The villa was clean and had a nicely done interior complete with DVD players both in the living room and in the room. It also has a Harman Kardon Bluetooth speakers ready. 

For Breakfast you’ll have to order from a list and they’ll send it right to the villa and u can even have breakfast in the pool. 

The front desk was nice enough to assist me with scooter rental and the bike was pretty new and had no issue. 

Overall, we were very happy with our stay and thank you to your amazing team of people who made our stay a very memorable one.
title: A five star accommodation

text:
I love the location. Turn right and 10 minutes walk to the beach. Turn left and you have many restaurants and shops. And when you need to go further for more restaurants, its no more than a 10 minute IDR30,000 taxi ride. 
The 2 room villa is spacious. One cannot cook and food should be ordered from the villa itself and the quality is average. Its better to step out of the villa as there so many good food options nearby.
Wifi speed was slow. Although I complained, nothing was done. They need to speed it up
The master bedroom’s bathroom is partially “outdoors”. I don’t think it’s necessary. The wooden planks at the shower were loose and pinch the feet. Towels were grey and “hard” when they should be white and fluffy. 
The pool is not properly cleaned and we had insect bites
Staff are friendly and helpful. Security is good.
If they can address some of the issues like wifi and maintenance and towels, it would be a highly recommended option
title: Great location. If some issues can be sorted out, this is highly recommended

text:
My family just returned from 6 nights in a 2 bedroom villa. I use trip advisor as my bible therefore I wanted to share our experience at Pradha as we had mixed reviews of our stay. 

Firstly as mentioned by other guests,  the location is 10/10. Close to the square, shops, great restaurants/cafes, W Hotel, Ku De Ta beach club etc. 

The villas are large, exceptionally clean, beautiful plunge pool and spa, beds were very comfortable and fitted with good quality linen however the villas are looking on the older side and could definitely do with a face lift. There is a kitchen but only equipped with a few things. This is hard when travelling with children. We would have loved a toaster, microwave & dishwashing rack. There is a stove but only one pan. There was a large filtered water tank in the kitchen which provides you with both hot and cold water which was so handy. 

If you have a young family (ie toddler, crawling baby) I would NOT recommend these villas to you as there is a large pond/fountain at the entry which cannot be blocked off and you will be on edge the entire stay. Also the lay out means that you are very far from the second bedroom and unless you bring a baby monitor, you will not be able to hear the children in the night. If they wanted to get up and come into your room they have to go outside across the grass (which is uncovered) to get in. Not ideal especially as it rained heavily every night we were there. 

As you expect in Bali, mosquitoes are in abundance. Because the shower (in the main bathroom) is open air, we constantly had mosquitoes in our bathroom which then came into our bedroom. The staff were wonderful trying to control by spraying the rooms with bug spray and light coils each night but they were still present. Bring lots of bug spray! 

We did not enjoy the breakfast at all. Each day it was served to us cold, the toast was barely cooked, cereal and milk laced with sugar, eggs sunny side up and omelettes were still raw, pastries and banana bread were stale, French toast was soggy and coffee was not drinkable. We gave up by the last day and went to Sisterfields cafe for a nice breakfast. 

The internet..my oh my! If you want good wifi you will not find it here. It cut out every 5-10 minutes, the connection was very weak and very slow. we would continually have to reconnect, we couldn’t face time family or watch videos, you tube etc. This made it extremely hard for my husband to get some work things finalised whilst we were there. We would have to go up to one of the cafes in town to connect. Considering that many places we went to in Bali had great Wifi I think this is something Pradha should fix ASAP & consider a new provider.

 If you want to use a cot for your baby you will be charged. We travel regularly and never have I had to pay for a cot. I was really unimpressed by this and felt at times that where ever they could make money from you they would. A cot should not be one of those. 

Another ‘charge’ we received was for requesting almond milk for breakfast. Due to a dairy allergy I asked for almond milk for my breakfast cereal. I was advised that I could have it but would be charged. Seriously? 

During our stay we asked the villas to install a  pool fence for our toddler. There is a daily charge of AUD $25 for this plus they charged an additional $30 AUD to install. The pool fence was sturdy and provided us with peace of mind. 

The shuttle service into town was handy and the staff who drove us were so friendly.
title: Liked our stay but didn’t love

text: Staying at Pradha villas was the best decision I’ve took in my life .. we stayed there at our honeymoon vacation and they made it an unforgettable one.. everything was beyond perfect and we got exactly everything was mentioned in the package , they made it so perfect that we had no problem to stay at the villa for all day long 😍 will do it again and again and again ❤️❤️
title: Best thing that happened to us in Bali

text: We spent a week at Pradha Villas and loved it. The staff were incredibly polite and helpful, the villa was modern and clean, and the location is fantastic. Nearby spots include Motel Mexicola and Potato Head Beach Club. The actual beach itself is only a couple of minutes away on foot. My only criticism is the villa we were put in was located next to a busy road, the noise was annoying which was mainly from a nearby bar, there are many villas not located directly next to the road so I suggest you request one of those. All in all great value for money and wonderful place to stay.
title: Week long stay in Pradha Villas, Seminyak. Bali.

text: Very good service and tidy，romatic memory. especially the Staff and very caring Manager makes a wonderful start of my day. She arranged our request and always please us from the check in till we leave. The villa its self was clean, location is very good, easy access to best spot in Seminyak. We are very happy and we will definetly stay with Pradha again.
title: Special Staying

text:
This is our 2nd trip this year.  Villa has just been renovated this year.  Fresh colors, new plants and deco.  Wide selection for breakfast menu however the quality is not as good a our last trip in March.
We have tried a few villas in Seminyak and always return to Pradha for its location and service.  Totally recommend for couples and Family.
title: rejuvenated villas!

text: If you are going to Seminyak, stay at the Pradha villas, you will not be disappointed! This was the best accommodation we stayed in in Bali. The villa was extremely clean and HUGE, the private pool and jacuzzi were fabulous. We had plans to see lots in Seminyak but spent most of the time making the most of this wonderful villa. We found the staff to be extremely friendly and helpful. The staff bring your breakfast to the villa and set it up at your table. They also came in daily to treat the room for mosquitoes.  The villas are very well located, 2 mins walk from a vast array of restaurants & shops. The Pradha Villas were definitely a highlight of our trip and we wish we had stayed longer than 2 nights.
title: Best Villa of our trip to Bali - would highly recommend!

text:
We booked a 2 bed pool villa here for our young family. The villa was fantastic, with the open living concept that most pool villas in Bali have. We were admittedly worried about the open living with a 1 year old (we didnt want her wandering off to the pool) but it ended up being a non-issue for us. However - the welcome foyer of each villa did have a water feature and steps over the water leading into the villa - where our little one did often go to! So keep in mind if you have younger ones.

Back to the villa, the rooms were spacious, the decor was modern, and the pool was superb. The villa was spotlessly cleaned everyday, and all towels (pool and room) replaced. The service was impeccable! The breakfast was plentiful and served to the villa within a 15 minute specified time slot - and they laid out the table etc so it was like restaurant dining!

In terms of location, this is very close to seminyak square, although we realized there wasn't much to seminyak square! This is walking distance to most places including the beach (pettitenget) but we found we enjoyed the villa so much we only went out once a day!

Highly recommended!
title: Beautiful villas, lovely service!

text:
Excellent location, friendly and helpful staff, nice touches like the
welcome drink, afternoon juice and a generous breakfast. The condition of
place was a bit weathered but this did not impact the quality of our stay.
Pool had sun during the day and was a nice temperature.  The villa was fairly quiet but having said that we were in a good location within the complex. I felt like we were miles away from the hustle and bustle of that crazy street.  Walking distance to eat street with Sisterfields just around the corner and Mexicola just down the road.
title: Location, location

text: I have now stayed in Bali 4 times & Pradha Villas is by far the best accomodation I have experienced yet ! The villa is so spacious, clean, modern & peaceful. It is so close to the beach & Seminyak square but nestled into a quiet street with a secret access that gets you on the Main Street quickly. The staff are so beautiful & kind. They deliver breakfast to your room daily, clean during the day & set you up at night (turn lights on & put mosquito coils around). Could not recommend this place more. Will certainly book again this year, I honestly don't want to leave
title: BEST VILLA EVER !!

text: What a great place this is. Tucked away in a gorgeous green laneway you'll find lovely villas. We had a 2 bedroom pool villa which was heavenly. Breakfast is full of great choices and can delivered at a time to suit you. The staff are very kind, highly professional and nothing is too much trouble. They go to great lengths to keep mosquitos away by burning coils and spraying rooms at dusk. We stayed at the villas in July 2017 and did not see any mosquitos at all. Rooms are air-conditioned nicely appointed (really comfortable beds too). This is a brilliant location with shops, cafes, restaurants and the beach just minutes on foot.
title: Pradha Paradise

text: We stayed in a 2 Bed Villa. The arrangement of the villa is in nice contemporary style with a pool you can swimming. The Staff is very friedly and helpful. The breakfast for a villa is just great with a wide selection. We also have a dinner in the villa. The food is top an nicely presented. The building itself could use a little paint here and there and then earns 5 point again
title: Retreat in Seminyak

text:
Stayed at pradha villas for 2 nights cos of consistent good reviews and good location. We had a newly renovated villa and weren't disappointed. 
Our villa had lovely morning sun at the pool area. Spacious living area with big bedrooms and bathrooms. Air conditioning in the rooms were so comfortable after a hot day outdoors.

Living area had a high ceiling fan which was ok. Prob adding another ceiling fan above the dining table would be better. It was quite hot to eat breakfast there in the morning.

Normal problem with lizards and insects as this is open concept. Some insects in the pool too.

Staff service was good and efficient. 
We ordered breakfast one morning and it was delicious.

Our villa was near the shortcut leading to seminyak square. That shortcut closes at a certain timing so take note. Roads there can be quite dark but ok if you're in a group or just use a torch.

Overall a relaxing stay:)
title: good location and perfect for groups

text:
Loved the location, so close to the heart of Seminyak, yet tucked away on a quiet side street. It's also a quick walk down to the beach. The Villa was perfect, super clean pool, amazing room, beautiful open air bathroom, and huge to top it all off.

The kitchen was dated (take note management), but that didn't change my opinion of the place. All staff was super sweet and helpful.
title: Tops!

text: I m still staying here , it is situated in the heart of seminyak and yet so silient. They serve breakfast in the villa which is awesome and service is awesome. We also got complimentary drinks here . The staff ika was really helpful and always smiling . They also have in villa massages which are great . Overall a great experience . They do have a mosquito problem for which they come every evening and spray mosquito repellent and coils. Thank u pradha villas looking forward to coming again
title: Huge villas with great ambience

text:
We stayed for 3 nights and felt so welcomed and looked after, with the lovely team even making a larger villa available for us to get some additional time in the sun!
Perfect location for the amazing restaurants and close proximity to the beach, we highly recommend Pradha Villas!
title: Amazing Villa and Experience!

text:
Our first time at pradha villas we were looking for a more modern villa to celebrate my birthday. Which is today :-))) 
Pradha does not disappoint one tip ask for villa on left hand side as while our pool is gorgeous very little sun and that is one reason for pool villa to laze in the sun so little disappointed.
Bathroom is outdoors but undercover so can get a little hot and humid. The bedroom is cool and inviting. Outdoor area is spacious . Small bar fridge nut no freezer door and hot cold water dispenser though the cold water is warm lol
For Bali the villa is nice and we would recommend as sometimes in Bali maintenance is not undertaken but at Pradha it is immaculate. Very near mexicola restaurant and sisterfield if you are trying to get your bearings. Staff are unobtrusive and ver pleasant. 
We will definitely be back but will ask for sunny pool.
title: Great villa seminyak

text: From arrival to departure the staff made our experience a truly unique and pleasant one. We were initially unsure as some photos and comments on TA were concerning however this was not our encounter wonderful staff assisted with bookings and outings in room dining and outside services without hesitation, teaching us some balianese along the way! The villa in which we stayed was a two bedroom and had a spa and pool with plenty of sun during the day 9am till 4pm. Staff assisted with a mosquito net however these were not an issue inside the room and outside areas were treated daily with could and spray, in fact not one bite while we were here for our 2 week stay!! The breakfast was good and choice was plentiful. The photos attached we have taken show the breakfast servings for two people. I rate this a five based on Service, Ammenaties and value. Great location for beach walks, nightlife, restaurants and shopping. The staff are an asset can't commend them enough.We can't wait to go back!
title: Tranquil retreat

text: Yes, I will admit, I shed a quiet tear in the taxi to the airport after saying goodbye to the wonderful Pradha Villa staff and the week in paradise we experienced at Pradha Villas! A wonderful and refreshing escape for myself, husband and two children. Beautiful and tastefully designed and decorated villas, a spotlessly clean pool surrounded by Frangipani trees, friendly and attentive staff, central location. The open plan design was a highlight and a wondeful novelty for our two children.Thank you Pradha Villas - we will be back!
title: A very special place to stay

text:
Both my wife and I enjoyed our stay over at Pradha. The location is excellent, walking distance to Seminyak Square and yet away from the noise at night. 
We booked the 1 bedroom luxury villa and it comes with heated jacuzzi. Excellent for those night soaking inside the warm water to relax your tired bodies. 
The staff were attentive to our needs.
Take note they do come to your villa during the evening time to turn on the lights, spraying of insect repellent and burning of mosquito coils. 

Thank you Pradha and we will be visiting you again.
title: Wonderful stay over at Pradha

text:
We spent a week at Pradha villas, ending up renting two villas next to each other. We were in touch with the manager and she helped us arrange for airport transportation, massages and fill our fridge with beverages of our choice. She provided wonderful service.
The villas are not the most luxurious out there, but they are super nice, especially considering the price and the location. Around the corner of Pradha villas there is so much to each and drink, just a short stroll away.

The villas were clean and spacious. Service was great.
The only thing they could improve on would be the quality of the breakfast. We love the Nasi Goreng, but the one we got for lunch was significantly better than the one they serve for breakfast. A few days we went to Sisterfields nearby, which serves delicious food.

Overall, I can highly recommend Pradha villas. They truly made our stay memorable and enjoyable.
title: Wonderful week-long stay

text:
My partner and I stayed with Pradha villas for a week and a half, and at first we didn't think we'd be able to stay here as the bathroom and living area were open allowing mosquitos in. However by the time we checked out, we never wanted to leave! On the first day we asked the staff if there was anything they could do about the mosquitos, they then set up mosquito coils throughout the villa and lit them for us every night, as well as sprayed our rooms daily (I'd still recommend bringing insect repellent however). Later in the week, we asked if we could have a portable fan in our bedroom (The air conditioning worked fine but didn't blow directly on the bed and we kept waking up hot no matter how low we set the AC), and when we returned from shopping we found a fan set up in our room. One night, we dropped a plate and the staff came promptly to help us clean up all the little shards off the floor. Throughout our entire stay, the staff went out their way to make sure we felt comfortable and were always so friendly. 

The rooms were beautiful and spacious. The pool was amazing to swim in, always the perfect temperature. The location was perfect and close to both shopping and food, as well as the beach. The daily breakfast was delicious and offered many alternatives so we never got sick of eating anything (definitely try the mi goreng!). They even provide extra pastries and breads on top of what you order so you definitely won't feel hungry afterwards. 

The only issue I had regards the laundry service. My partner had his clothes returned in excellent condition but i noticed there were two new holes in my dress after it was cleaned (good thing it was a cheap dress). 

Overall, We really loved staying here and would definitely stay here again.
title: Really Enjoyable

text: We stayed at Pradha Villas as a free night I had received from Hotels.com and it was the closest to where we recently stayed and we loved the area. We were pleasantly surprised. Nice huge villa for the two of us, good location but tucked away from all the noise on the streets, the pool is big which is always what we look for in booking a villa and the rooms are spacious and clean. Would have loved to stay another night but they were booked out. Cant review the breakfast as it never came with our package but the staff were friendly.
title: Good location, very private

text:
I rarely review hotels and I travel for a living and have been living in hotels for the last seven months solid. In other words, I log a lot of hours on the road. This place deserves a review. It was INCREDIBLE. The villa was gorgeous. The staff was incredibly friendly and helpful. The breakfasts were amazing. In fact, after going out to dinner in the busy town the first night, we found ourselves thinking that we never wanted to leave our villa again. Then we looked at room service and realized we didn't have to. Their meals were significantly less expensive than the restaurants and could be eaten by our pool! (Yes, I know it's lame that we came all the way to Bali and refused to leave our villa, but why mess with a good thing?) Of course, it is an indoor/outdoor living space, so there's no air conditioning in the living area (although there is in the bedroom) and you're sharing your space with the geckos. But that's a part of the experience and the beauty of the villa. In all, this was my favorite place I've ever stayed. Highly recommended.

(Also good wifi and a quick walk to many restaurants and the beach. And they provided a complimentary airport pickup and return. And the kitchen had one of those coolors of filtered water, which was such a score in the heat.)
title: Spent our entire week trying to figure out how we could live here forever.

text:
The staff at Pradha Villas are just exceptional, from Reception to the lovely Security men and the gardeners.  My room was a little tired, but it was clean and very spacious.  The bed was wonderful.  The breakfast was delivered to the room at your nominated time that suited and this was plentiful.  Our cold/hot water bottle was not working and it was replaced within the hour.  The pool was great and the spa at the end of the pool I finally realised had functions for the water to be heated, once I found this I was regularly in relaxing (the weather was cold and raining).  

Upon arriving to the Villa I was a bit grumpy as I thought the Villa was very close to Seminyak Square and the way the taxi delivered us I thought this could not be true.  Upon asking the Reception, she advised that there was a 'short cut'.  This was a god send as once down this little short cut to a street you turn left and at the end you can turn left and very quickly you will be a Seminyak Square, if you turn right and walk a way you are down to Mexicola etc. etc. You can do a huge circle of all the best restaurants.

The mosquitoes are a problem but the staff spray nightly, although the bedroom was a closed-off safe haven with great air-conditioning.

I would recommend this Villa for the situation, staff and spacious room.
title: Enjoyable Stay...

text: We have travelled to Bali several times. This Villa was clean, the staff were so friendly and helpful, and the pool was awesome. It was very close to the heart of Seminyak. We hired a scooter there was safe parking for it and easy access to everywhere we had to go. I would defiantly stay here again.
title: Great Bali Villa

text: What a wonderful place to stay at. This was our second time in Seminyak and we made the better choice at staying at this villa. Fantastic location, close to all the fancy restaurants and awesome service. Very clean hotel, plenty of storage, 24 he security and really friendly staff.
title: Fantastic time

text:
Lovely villa, very comfortable. Two sleeping rooms, both with ensuites. One large open room, with great breeze on hot summer afternoons. Superb private pool and garden. Paint was a little tired, but did not detract from the experience. Room service great, including breakfast served in your room each morning. 
Very helpful desk staff, but could improve knowledge of tours on offer. Location is well situated to venues in Seminyak.
Thanks to the staff for a great stay. Would highly recommend.
title: Seven night stay - well looked after by the staff

text:
We originally booked a private pool villa via Airbnb but when we arrived at the original accommodation, there were multiple issues not solvable overnight. We had no choice but to seek alternative lodging as we had young children (4 year old & 1 year old) and also hosting 2 overseas guests.

Fortunately, we were able to book this place and move in on the same night we arrived. What a godsend Pradha is that turned around our week in Bali from extreme disappoint to absolute fabulous! 

The issues we had with our original Airbnb accomodation were absolutely not present at Pradha:
1. Crystal clear water in the Pradha swimming pool vs Cloudy pool water in our original accommodation (what's the point of private pool villa if you can't enjoy clean, clear water)

2. Very small to no gaps of the Pradha bedroom doors vs big gap in our original accommodation (where we had mosquitoes and insects flying into the room)
- Pradha villas has outdoor shower but we didn't have mosquito issues in the bedrooms (and there were no mosquito netting in our villa)

3. Clean towels and linen

4. Clean bathroom tiles

I believe all the above are hygiene/basic factors of any accommodation.

Other plus points of Pradha Villas:
1. Staff provided extremely friendly services
- at times i think they over-serviced us
- there was also afternoon drinks/refreshment service and evening turn down service

2. Very accessible to Petitenget beach and restaurants in Seminyak area
- would have walked more if we didn't have kids with us

3. clean and good size pool
- staff puts in cleaning tablets every other day
- we are particular about cleanliness of pool water as we have had trips whereby pool water caused fungal infection on our children but no issues here *knock wood*

Downsides
1. Breakfast is still rather oily (even though we put in request to reduce oil)
- the boiled stuff is fine

2. Late checkout
- understand that late checkout is subject to availability. However, in our numerous requests, the reasons given for not being able to provide this kept changing. 

Would certainly consider to go back here for next Bali trip.
title: Extremely wonderful time for adults and kids

text:
If I can find any fault with Pradha Villa, it would be me not discovering this Villa any sooner! The Villa is huge, beautiful, nice clean pool with a Hydro-pool that drains out and refill back everyday! Staff attendance, service level and friendliness are top notch, this makes a difference from the other villa because of the good hospitality skills the staff are so well-trained! Kudos to the team in Pradha Villa!  Breakfast spread is fantastic and we had our fill every morning with joy!

The location is very convenient within walking distance to the new Seminyak Square, lots of eateries and restaurants around, and also close by are the likes of famous spots Breeze The Samaya, Ku De Ta, and various pharmacies and minimarts around. 

I will definitely recommend this Villa to my friends! 

PS - One suggestion, should install a fan or perhaps a portable fan near the dining area.
title: Excellent stay at Pradha Villa!

text:
We really enjoyed our stay at Pradha. It is in a great location and the manager and staff are really pleasant and obliging.

There were a few aspects of our Pradha stay that were better than other villas we have stayed at. Firstly Pradha’s, complimentary pick up & drop offs, including from & to other hotels. On the way in they picked us up from the Courtyard Marriot in Seminyak and on the way out, they drove 6 of us, 2 vans, across town to the Conrad in Tanjung Benoa. The Conrad would have charge $35- per van for the same trip.

Also the kitchen had a large water heater/cooler tank unit as well as the usual bottled water so we had no clean water concerns.

In general, we have stayed at a lot of villas, the Elysian, Le Jardin, Maya, Komaneka’s, Puri’s, Maca, Equilibria, so pretty easy to make comparisons. The 2 bedroom villa which we shared with our adult daughter was well designed, virtually 2 villas in one. Loved the solid timber door separating bathroom & toilet, from the bedroom. So many villas and hotels these days have pathetic wobbly sliding bathroom doors with the toilet virtually in the bedroom. I hate having the toilet right near the bedroom. 

Breakfasts served in the villa were good, plenty to choose from and good quality/quantity.

Internet was good, good enough for streaming most of the time.

A security guard was present after hours & entrance door/gate manned and locked over night.

We also loved the big villa pool.

There were a few things we didn’t like. The lounge/ kitchen area was large which was good but it was completely open, so hot during the day and mosies at night. The open lounge also meant that when you walked in and out of the air conditioned bedrooms the temperature variation was dramatic. They should also get new TVs. 

Afternoon tea could use improving, not a patch on Elysian, Maca’s, Maya.

The shuttle stopped at 5pm while most other villas have shuttles up to 9 or 10 pm.

Overall we had a great time and thank the management and staff of Pradha.
title: Great Location Great Staff

text: At last minute my husband had to work so i found it was a little daunting staying in a villa with my 2 children alone... it turns out the staff were extremely helpful they offered my 8yr old boy a little cruise on their scooter as i was a little scared to do so myself, the team were very helpful with both my kids! English was terrific and reception lady named Wulan organised and helped us every step of the way. I would definitely recommend this place it is an alley way away from the busiest part of Seminyak but without noise when we returned to the Villa. Breakfast was beautiful and on time, Bill was correct once we left and overall you will not be disappointed. Thanks Prahda Villas!
title: Just beautiful!

text:
Lovely villa, spacious, perfect location, very helpful & friendly staff
The villa is very clean , the beds & pillows are so comfortable, the pool is beautiful & has a spa at the end
It's my second stay at Pradha villas & would highly recommend 
Close to shopping and nice restaurants
title: Lovely spacious villa

text: We just returned from 7 nights at Pradha Villas.  Our biggest prerequisite was sun around the pool &, happy to say, we got plenty of that!  The split-lock villa was nice & spacious & must have been recently refurbished as it looked nicer than the photos on their web site.  The breakfasts also exceeded expectations so we ended up having more of them in the villa than planned.  All the staff seemed to go out of their way to be friendly & helpful whilst also being respectful of privacy.  Needless to say, the location is premo, which is why we sought out these villas after looking at a few in the area whilst in Bali last year.  We have been to Bali numerous times & would definitely stay here again.
title: Awesome Stay

text:
We stayed in Villa 5. It was original and could do with a bit of an update in some areas (bathrooms), but was clean and serviced well on a daily basis. The private pool was fabulous. The staff were great and very responsive. In particular our morning breakfast was delivered by the delightful Tenee (sorry not sure of spelling but Tee-nee). She was fantastic. Plenty of variety with the breakfast, although it was delivered cold one day (not by Teenee)
One area which could be improved was the kitchen. It had a good fridge and cooktops, but was only equipped with cutlery,a small frying pan, a few plates and glassware. No pots, sharp knives toaster  or general kitchenware. Look I know breakfast was provided, and dinning in or out is not expensive, but every now and then it's nice to prepare a bit of your own food, so a better fit-out would have been appreciated. 
The only other small grumble, which is probably beyond the control of Pradha, was the adjacent Warung (restaurant) having loud music on a few nights, but that was always finished soon after 10pm. It probably wasn't that loud but the nights are still and balmy and the noise probably just travels a bit.
Overall all, in conjunction with the beaut Bali weather (9 days of clear skies, no rain), just fantastic reasonably priced food, this was just our best holiday in years. Will be back.
title: LOVELY VILLA

text:
This villa was perfect, a real getaway! It was located on a side road and a couple off blocks just off the main road. Excellent location for Seminyak a small walk down the road to my favourite place ..... Bodyworks where you can be pampered in the spa with amazing treatments. The villa was serviced daily and also breakfast could be made for you in your villa at a chosen time. Would recommend this place.....

title: Fantastic villa with private pool in a little side road

text: We really loved the location of the Pradha Villas, with just a 5 min walk to the center of Seminyak and a <10 min walk to the beach.  Lots of restaurants, cafes, boutiques, massage places, etc. within a few minutes (or less) walk.  Quiet area, with no real problems with our 2 bedroom villa, but it lacked "character".  Nothing a little interior design work could not improve quickly. Very friendly and helpful staff. Worth a stay for couples wanting convenience & a fair level of comfort in Seminyak.
title: Great location &adequate facilities

text:
Couldn't have picked a better place to stay. 

We were in villa 10 (2 couples) for 6 nights. The staff were amazing from the get go - they picked up us from the airport with cold Bintangs, hired us motorbikes and drivers for a couple of days. The breakfast was good (mi goreng and nasi goreng are the way to go), the fridge was stocked with soft drink and beers, for the same price as you'd buy at supermarkets - they also had room service and in room spa treatments available - all of it was really well priced. The villa itself was great - much bigger than we'd thought! Super clean, beautiful pool and in the best location. It's just around the corner from Motel Mexicola, Sea Circus and Bodyworks - Sisterfields was a quick walk too.

Will definitely stay here when I'm back!
title: AMAZING

text:
Stayed in Villa number 6 for five nights. First time to stay in a Villa in Bali and will never look back. Villas are the way to go.
Well located to all the upmarket bars including Kudeta, Potato Head and W Bar including top restaurants at your doorstep to include Mecicola, LaLucciola, Bossman and Sisterfields.
Villas are a little dated but acceptable for Bali. We did check out  Villa numbers 10 and the luxury Villa but there was little sun to sun bake and the pools were smaller.
Will definitely stay back in Villa number 6 when I return.
title: Home Away from Home

text:
We booked Pradha Villas looking for mid-range priced family accommodation in a central location in Seminyak which allowed for independent living. It did not disappoint. Pradha Villas is located in a side-street running parallel to Jl. Kayu Jati, meaning that it is in a quiet cul-de-sac but perfectly located for Petitenget Beach, Seminyak Square and all of the shops and restaurants on Jl, Kayu Aya. We were in Villa 8; nearest the short-cut linking the villas with Jl. Kayu Jati. Our taxi from the airport needed some help to find the side-street initially; though Pradha Villas is behind Warung Mina on Jl. Kayu Jati so this is a useful landmark.  

Our first impression of the villa was that it was lavish and tasteful. Our villa comprised two separate sleeping areas, each with en-suite toilet, bath and shower.  These were connected by a communal lounge, dining area and kitchen, without permanent walls on two sides. This creates an inviting, airy space; ideal for relaxing, eating and reading in daylight; but tricky to mosquito-proof at night. The pool was generously sized for the villa, with decking and a jacuzzi placed around it. There was  well thought-out planting, with mature trees, shrubs and lawn interspersed by flowing watercourses. The villa was encased by a high wall on all sides, though conversation and music could clearly be heard from the villa next door. 

Each sleeping area has air-conditioning, access to the pool and adequate storage space. In one of the bathrooms, the shower is opposite the toilet, making the layout somewhat impractical. In the other, as a design feature, the shower has no covering roof. We found this liberating and sensible, considering the climate and direction of rainfall. The temperature in Bali meant that we kept the air-conditioning on all of the time, so quickly realised that the unit in one bedroom was faulty. We told the villa management team, who had it fixed that day whilst we were out. They also arranged a free one hour massage at the villa at our convenience as recompense. 

Breakfast was ordered the day before and delivered to the villa at an arranged time. We thought the choice was reasonable, with cooked continental and indonesian options, muesli and lots of fresh fruit. We didn't chose to have breakfast elsewhere, considering the choices available at restaurants like Grocer and Grind and Sisterfields as no different to those at home; with the inconvenience of having to go out. This meant that, after breakfast, we got to see the birds darting down to the table in the dining area to enjoy our crumbs and leftovers. We didn't cook in the kitchen, though ate lots of fruit bought on our travels. We did not order room service. The fridge was pre-filled with drinks, which were diligently inventoried and billed for. We removed these, replacing them with cheaper drinks from Bottle Avenue just around the corner. Housekeeping was regular and unobtrusive, arranged around our schedule. The staff were friendly and chatty. It included daily linen changing and clean bath and swimming towels The evening turn-down included spraying and the lighting of mosquito coils. The villa management team was a mine of useful information.

During our stay, we gradually noticed some of the downsides that other reviewers have mentioned. There were cockroaches in both bathrooms on a few nights - possibly coming from under the wooden shower trays; with a dead roach under the coffee table in the lounge and a live one on the sofa on one occasion. The latter prompted us to look behind the sofa; which revealed a rather large, very sprightly, arachnid. During the furniture reshuffle, we observed that behind the sofa and under the coffee table had not been swept or dusted recently. The decking area around the pool harboured millipedes, which casually ventured out to explore in the cooler evenings. None of these co-tenants particularly bothered us; as we expected this is the tropics. Some of the bathroom counter-tops are becoming water-stained, the walls behind the toilets need sponging and wiping and the air-conditioning vents need dusting, but these minor issues did not detract from the overall cleanliness and comfortableness of the villa. There were some stains on the duvet covers. The toilets seem to be low-flush; though this may not be deliberate, meaning that several flushes may be necessary. The drains were slightly smelly after prolonged periods without rain, though this may be related to inadequate drainage in Seminyak. The smell was not pungent, but was noticeable on several days. 

The villa seemed secure and private. All living areas were lockable, with safes in both bathrooms. The separation from the main shopping and eating areas in Seminyak meant that the villa grounds were quiet; and we rarely saw other visitors. The paths and communal areas are well-pruned and clean. All staff were polite and reserved, eager to help but respectful of our privacy. Each morning offerings and prayers were said outside of each villa. 

We would have no hesitation in returning to Pradha Villas or recommending it to others.
title: Enjoyed an inviting and comfortable stay here in July 2016

text:
Pradha Villas are in a perfect location only 5 minutes walk to Motel Mexicola and Seminyak Square. 

The villas are comfortable and for the price, great value. They are by no means luxurious, perhaps even a little tried, but as I say for the price I wouldn't complain!

The breakfast which was included was not fantastic, so we decided to decline that each day and walk into Seminyak where we were spoilt for choice. The amenities were ok, clean and working. The pool large and maintained well.

The staff were lovely and very caring when I became extremely ill on the last day, offering to get me a doctor and providing me everything I needed to make me comfortable before my flight home. 

For location and price, you cant beat it! You just shouldn't expect any more than say 3.5*. All in all I would stay again purely for the location and the staff who were lovely!
title: Great Location

text:
Back in 2009 we stayed at this gorgeous villa.
In July 2016 we came back. 

If I could I would come back tomorrow. 

This place is beautiful inside and out. 
From the bedding and room comfort to bathroom knick knack essentials were well thought of. 

Food: breakfast  is provided and the selections were diversed, fresh,  delicious and eye pleasing. 

Location: seminyak shops were just walking distance !! On that note: Bali Bakery is a must try!
Just order whatever you feel like eating. You won't be disappointed

Staff: they are well knowledged, friendly, and helpful! 

Did I say that I would come back tomorrow if I could?

I would. Seriously. Just book the room. 

Amelia.
title: Happiness in a nutshell in Pradha Villas.

text:
3 years ago, our family stays in this incredible pradha villa, and now 3 years later we were staying here again for 8 days..

U can take my word, that this is really a piece of heaven among the crowds at Seminyak.. when u got there.. all are peace and calm and really fells like home..

Kids are loving the pool, and wont come out from it..  and the beach are very near, only 2 minutes walking distance..

Staff are very helpful, kind and their smile always be there for you.

We will come back again :) 
Thx u pradha
title: 3 years after, we come back, and it's still really a piece of heaven in Bali

photos.caption: this shot taken from the jacuzzi

text:
I was skeptical at first considering the location was on a really small and crowded street but man, it was a perfect romantic getaway.

Single Lux Villa, great space, clean and everything was working fine(meaning AC, TV, Internet)

The villa is old wooden motif and well worn, the space was very relaxing and the service was just...perfect.

Price was fair for the villa so if you are in a upper-lower budget, I would recommend and I would say book directly rather than go yhrough sites, booking direct gets the airport pick up and drop and that in itself is worth it.

If you're looking for a quick escape...this is one of the better places to be!
title: A perfect hidden gem

text:
Would have given 4 1/2 stars but this not possible

We spent 7 nights at Pradha recently ... we had a one bedroom Villa (which was a two bedroom Villa with one separate building bedroom locked off... which was a really generous size) great location just one street back from Seminyak Square, a 5 minute walk to the beach and 5 minutes from Eat Street !

The housekeeping was excellent with the room cleaned daily. They sprayed for mozzies each night at the turn-down service and lit mozzie coils outside and in the partially open air bathroom.

As with nearly all buildings in Bali the attention to detail of the building and the maintenance repairs are not good by Australian standards ... but do not let that stop you from staying!

Highly recommended.
title: Great Location Good Value

text:
Go to Bali every year for the past 6 years and this is the third time we stay here. The villa is very near to the eatstreet, is walkable distance. Stayed at 1 bedroom luxury villa, very happy with their service too. Food also nice with reasonable price. 
Only 1 bedroom luxury villa got hot tub (hot water Jacuzzi), that is one of the reason why we choose this villa, as lot of other villa don't have hot tub. Near to the beach too. Their massage ok only, better go find other spa. But this time the villa show a little bit of tired, believe need a touch up to maintain their quality.
title: Great Villa

text: If you want an oasis in Semanyak, this place is for you.  Our villa, had a small pool, air conditioning, kitchen and big sitting area.  The staff rule!  So nice and helpful. Close to the beach, shopping, dining.  Semanyak is a busy place now, which has advantages, but we felt miles away from it all here.  It was at the upper end of our budget, and I'm glad we chose this place. VERY private.
title: Worth the price

text: I loved my stay in Pradha villas. Awesome breakfast and awesome staff and service. Will definately stay here again if I ever visit to Bali and suggest all my known ones to stay here. The best villa property and it's close by the market beach and clubs restaurants. Keep it up. Thank you for the amazing service. Pradha villa made my family stay a memorable one.
title: Best stay

text:
There is not much else to say other than this was a perfect getaway for a long romantic weekend, all the staff was very welcoming and giving their best effort to complete our holiday. 
Location is perfect for Seminyak very close to every spot place in Seminyak
Villa was well kept and very clean, they had a villa which has been refurbished, but it was vacant while we were there so could not see this wish the next of our visit hope all of the villa has finish being renovated. Although our villa was beautiful. We really enjoy our stay.

Will come back
title: Great Service, Great Villa, Awesome Location

text: Lovely small complex of villas with the personal touch. Our villa was perfect for a couple, open plan living with luxury master bedroom and ensuite. Very happy with the quality of our villa and the level of service from friendly helpful staff. Nothing was a problem. The location is excellent, in amongst the best of Seminyak. Such a short stroll to everything.
title: Haven in Seminyak

text: These villas were great, great location and very friendly staff. The villas are incredibly quiet and peaceful given the location next to a busy street. Staff were fantastic, very accommodating and helpful with bookings and reservations for restaurants and activities.
title: Great Location

text:
Found Pradha villas on Cantik villas website. To be honest it was a bit of rock, paper, scissors between my wife and I as to which of the many villa options we should take. Turns out that my winning streak also turned up a winner of a place to stay. 

Villas are in the perfect location for patrolling Seminyak on foot. 100 meters from Seminyak square and 200m walk to the beach meant we had so many options each day.

Villas themselves are starting to show their age however the are incredibly quiet and peaceful given the location next to a busy street. Pool setting is perfect for relaxing all day and the villas are designed to provide maximum shade whilst enjoying the poolside ambience. 

Staff are always friendly in the true Balinese style and they adore children.

Breakfast is basic but filling and wholesome and, given the location, you are spoils for eating options. If you like the Indonesian food then Warung Mina is right next door and you can get a damn fine nasi goreng for $4aud.

Can certainly recommend the villas for price, friendly service, location and ambience especially if coming with a family.
title: Rest and relax

text: A gorgeous little find in the very busy Seminyak area. Close proximity to Eat Street, Beaches, and many restaurants and beach clubs. Majority within walking distance if not too hot! Villa was well appointed and the rooms very comfortable. As with most places in hot humid areas the villa was showing a need for a refresh. Staff were fantastic, very accommodating and helpful with bookings and reservations for restaurants and activities .
title: A Quiet Oasis

text:
Very good location - easy access to centre of Seminyak yet privately tucked away from the noise and crowd.  The 2-bedroom villa 10 is very well maintained despite its age.  The master-bedroom and second bedroom are of good size.  And, so are the respective attached en-suites.  Common area and pool were well kept.  However, the kitchen, white goods and cabinetry needed to be renewed. 
Staff friendly, helpful and willing to consider our various requests.
The villa was sufficiently comfortable that our 2 night stay seemed too short.
Certainly a villa to consider at our next visit.
title: Decent Place ... Good Location, decent value.

text:
Stay 2 nights at 1bedroom luxury villa.
Pros:
Location was great, turn left and its a 3 minute walk to the shopping area (Seminyak Square, Seminyak village), restaurants, cafe (Grocer & Grind, Sister Fields , Bossman , Chandi....) turn right and its about 7mins walk to the beach , 10mins walk to restaurants and cafes along jln Petitenget. (Sarong , Sardine, Metis , Merah Putih ,Biku , the Fat Turtle)
Pool was nicely maintained and good size , love the jacuzzi which was working well. 
The staffs at the villas were pleasant and helpful.
Cons:
Both living room and bathroom are open air and lots of mosquitoes and creepy crawlies (spiders, millipedes , earthworms)however Mozzie coils were lit for us throughout the day.
Villa look old and in need of an overhaul. Its generally was starting to look chipped and worn in many places. It was rather dark and rather dated, and the lighting arrangements were mostly pretty poor so that at night there did not seem to be enough good light. Bathrooms was MOULDY and tended to smell bad due to poor drainage of the semi-outdoor shower.
title: Great location

text: Unbeatable location, 10 minutes or less walking distance to quiet part of Seminyak beach where La Luciola and Samaya located. We can watch nice sunset minus the crowd here. Just around the corner are Seminyak square and Seminyak Village with amazing cafes and restaurant nearby. Motel Mexicola is 2 mins away from main street.  Rooms are spacious, pool was perfect and the staff were attentive! Would highly recommend....we didn't have to catch a taxi anywhere. Would definitely go back!
title: Perfect villa in every way

text:
Location was great, tucked away from the busy streets.We stayed in a 2 bedroom villa with Pool. The pool was a great size and big enough for our children to play in it all day. The staff were extremely helpful. To my surprise they  called our room one day to tell us that my Husband and I both had a courtesy massage that we needed to book.
I would definitely  recommend Pradha Villas.
The only thing we were not that happy with was the Breakfasts. We ordered Breakfast for our 1st morning and when it arrived we had to ask the staff to take it away.The eggs were not cooked properly. It wasn't a problem as there are so many lovely places to eat Breakfast close by.
title: Great location tucked away from the busy streets of seminyak

text: One of the best locations in Bali positioned right in the middle between Seminyak Square and the beach. Amenities, furnishings and service are a little on the cheap side compared to some other villas. They do have premium villas which I am keen try if not sold out next time. Great if you want to walk to La Lucciola, Sister Fields etc and the beach for breakfast regularly (which we do).
title: Unbeatable location, service could improve

text: Best location.... Close walking distance to Seminyak square and amazing restaurants / cafe's. Motel Mexicola just a 2 min stroll and this is BY FAR the best place. So nice and peaceful. Amazing staff who go out of their way to make sure you're always happy. Cannot really fault anything... if I had to be picky... rooms could do with a bit of a revamp (some things were noticeably worn or old) and it's different adjusting to an open shower to outside with Lizards greeting you in the shower :-) Highly recommended and will be going back next time im in Bali.
title: A  small slice of heaven...

text:
Location was good being close to a range of restaurants.

Villa had a very big pool, spa within the private pool and nice bathtub to indulge. 

Breakfast was pretty good being cooked and delivered to your own villa. 

The pathway to the villa is also beautiful with lovely greenery and flowers.
title: Good location and great villa

text:
We stayed here for 7 nights.. It's a beautiful open living Villa.. Great pool, kitchen and Ensuite..
It's in a awesome location.. Between Motel Mexicola and Sisterfields..
Negatives I have is the breakfast.. Very basic.. Not cooked well.. All I could taste in the poached eggs was vinegar and the pancakes were like rubber.. No taste..  Only had breakfast for the first 2 mornings then had the rest at Sisterfields which was amazing.. 
Also they only stocked the mini bar twice in 7 nights so we didn't have much available to drink.. Overall, the staff were friendly.
Would I go back? Probably not. For $280 a night you want at least an above ave breakfast and better service..
title: Excellent Location

text: Perfectly situated in the Seminyak part of town, well within walking to alllocal restaurants, shops, and other fun. The villas are beautiful complete with private yard, tv/cable, wifi,and pool. Staff A+ service, prompt and friendly. Overall highly recommended!
title: Beautiful villas and location.

text:
Pradha is located very near to the beach...and also very near to the main stretch along seminyak square. U can easily walk to the staples Potato head, kudeta etc.
Villa was very clean n spacious. Pool was nicely maintained, jacuzzi was working well. If you dislike creepy crawlies, this place is excellent...we saw minimal. Mozzie coils were lit for us throughout the day.
Staff were friendly and polite. 
We called for inroom massage, very nice and good value.
Definately need to mention that the mini bar was very well priced. We didnt need to go to the mart to stock up on our bintangs :D
Overall i think Pradha is definately a good stay. The only thing preventing me from giving it 5 stars is that we've seen more beautiful villas around, Pradhas design is a little more basic...not saying its not nice...jus that perhaps aesthetics wise, there could be more done.
This is a good and safe choice, we would definitely recommend Pradha to friends.
title: Best Location!!!

text:
Pradha Villas was an incredible place to stay. 

Location: The location is really convenient (close to beach, Potato Head, really nice restaurants/shops etc.). Also right next to Mexicola (a nice and cheap Mexican restaurant)

Villa: We stayed in the one bedroom luxury and I couldn't believe how great it was. The actual villa was the most amazing place I have ever seen. The photos can barely do it justice it was spectacular.  Also for being in such a busy location - we really felt very secluded.

Service: We were also extremely impressed with the service of all of the staff. They went above an beyond every time (including helping us deal with Airport staff on the phone when my bag went missing). 

They cleaned/mosquito sprayed every day. 

Overall - An amazing stay - worth all of the money!!!!!!!!!!!!
title: Amazing location, Great Service - A must stay!

text: We had a two bedroom villa, when we walked in we went wow... It was a lovely place to stay if you want peace and quiet, During the day we had a few days just relaxing & sunbathing, it was so nice just to climb into our own pool and we only saw the staff  when they came to clean the villa and about 6pm, when they came every night to light mosquito coils. It was within walking distance of Seminyak Square, the beach and many shops and restaurants. We got a taxi to Kuta and Legian (very close by) where they were lots of market stalls. Overall Seminyak is nice with lots of boutique shops, but if you want a bit more nightlife the choose one of the other resorts.
title: Lovely Villa

text:
My partner and I stayed here for 10 nights, based on a recommendation of a friend who comes here every year. She wasn't wrong - we loved it. 

The location is perfect. Close to the best part of Seminyak but tucked away from noisy streets in a secure and peaceful surround.

The villas and gardens are well maintained and beautiful. We loved the completely private pool, the semi outdoor shower and the most perfectly comfortable bed. 

We rented a two bed villa but with one of the bedrooms locked off - this was perfect in giving us more living space. 

The staff were very friendly and accommodating.  Breakfast in the villa each day is great and, although good, I would rate the food as the only aspect closer to average. Also hard to compete when there are some great little cafes nearby. 

We will definitely return. We loved our stay and thought it was great value for money.
title: Fantastic value and great location

text:
A fantastic place to stay! Location is perfect, turn left and its a 5 minute walk to the busy road with restaurants, bars and spas, turn right and its about 10mins to the beach. Its also within walking distance to W Hotel and Potato Head, good places to hang out day or night. The shortcut path(opposite villa 6) is useful when heading to the retsuarant area.

The staff at the villa are very helpful and caring. They do a super job of maintaining the rooms and ensuring that everything is as it should be.  The villas themselves are gorgeous with a private pool, spacious lounge area and a comfortable bedroom. 

The choice on the breakfast menu and range of fresh juices was good. Room service is also available at reasonable prices. 
A free drop off service is available to certain local areas, which we found very handy.

Overall it was a fab stay and we would definitely return here!
title: Great place!

text:
I came across Pradha Villas from the reviews in Trip Advisor.  What appealed to me was the private pool along with a jacuzzi within the compounds of the villa.  Coupled with the fact that it is only five minutes walk to great food - Petitenget, Sisterfields, Chandi, Grocer & Grind etc. 

The Seminyak Beach was just around the corner and i took my daughter to the beach every morning.  She loved every bit of it.  From just standing by the shore and letting the waves rush in to playing the sand.  Great view too!

I made the reservation in June and followed up with several email with enquiries I had.  The friendly people there answered each and every emails/ questions I had.  

Breakfast were brought to the villa but with such great food around the corner, I only opted for the in-house breakfast on one of the mornings.

Definitely staying there on my next trip.

p.s. Beware of mosquitoes in the evenings.  The staff did a good job during their turn down service.
title: Wonderful hideaway in the heart of Seminyak

text:
Lookin for a nice place to stay in Seminyak we decided upon PradHa Villas located just behind the main square within easy walking distance to the Shops, Restaraunts  and the Beach. We were allocated Villa 10 (they only have 10 Villas so this was the furthest from the reception) which was very secluded and private. You open the padlock to the outer doors walk across the little bridge over the goldfish pond into the open plan kitchen / dining area. Off which is a toilet and 1 of the two bedrooms with its own en-suite bathroom and outside shower. Across a section of decking/grass is a second separate bedroom block also with its own en-suite bathroom and outdoor shower area. In between the two bedrooms is your own private swimming pool and at the far end a Jacuzzi both of which are not overlooked by any adjoining properties. Breakfast is ordered the night before prepared in the Kitchen and brought to your villa at a pre-arranged time. The staff make you coffee/tea and set the table all you have to do is eat as they will come back later to clear away make the beds and generally tidy up!.
You can choose to stay in your villa all day or if you do decide to centre out there is a cut through to the main road approx half way back towards reception (but this gate is locked at 10pm) just turn left for the shops or right for the beach. Very nice place which I would recommend to others.
title: Quite and secluded with easy access

text:
Stayed for 6D5Ns over in Pradha Villas and was pleased with our choice although everything was not perfect.

Villa - The villa was big and spacious with a private pool and a kitchen. Condition of the villa is good and clean, well-maintained. The air-conditioning wasn't cool enough for us though. All amenities were provided but we found one pack of tissues in a box from the toilet with stains on them. During turn-down service, the staff would set mosquito coils in the toilet and living room that might fog the toilet probably due to the lack of ventilation. There are a wide variety of channels on the television. However due to no list of channels provided, it is quite tiring to screen through each channel. The Wifi was good and fast but we always have to login after being disconnected awhile.

Breakfast - The breakfast could be better in terms of selection and quality. We almost tried every single choices in the list and felt the pancakes, western breakfast and mie goring was the acceptable of all. The rest are disappointing especially the French toast, not much of egg coating was on the bread. The juices are not to our liking with only the orange juice being the best out of the lot. The coffee and tea are better without milk. You could get your breakfast prepared either at the villa or the kitchen. The plus point is they are very punctual with your breakfast timing which you requested.

Location - Great location although the main entrance being located inside a small alley. There is a shortcut located between the resort to exit towards Seminyak Square which closed about 10pm daily. The villa is close to plenty of cafes and restaurants (e.g. Ultimo, Rumours, Sisterfield, Motel Mexico, Coffee Library etc.) which are walkable. We are also able to walk to Potato Head Club and Ku De Ta from there as well. You definitely don't have to worry about getting your breakfast, brunch, lunch, dinner or supper here.

Service - We were pleased with the service provided with the staff very friendly and always greeting you day and night with a smile. They even dropped by with a birthday cake in the morning and wanted to sing Happy Birthday to my wife but didn't manage to as she was still asleep, so I just got them to leave the cake in our villa. A really good effort and thought by the staff. The villa provides a free shuttle service (one-way only) beginning 10am to 5pm for nearby areas like Seminyak or Kuta. However, is also subject to availability so book early. In addition, when we requested for a shuttle at 455pm, they told us the shuttle wasn't available which puzzled us. We felt they should at least let us know the cut-off timing. The same thing was experienced when calling for our room service at 1020pm, and they told us the kitchen was closed when on paper it stated that room service ends at 1030pm. Both of these could be better communicated with the guests.

Overall, I would have to say a nice and relaxed stay if you're looking for some privacy but also wanted to be near Seminyak Square. Would recommend couples to stay here.
title: Almost a Great Stay but Statisfied Nonetheless
