text:
Luxurious villa with it's own integrated pool AND room-service!  :)
The villa was large, modern, contemporary, and secluded from the outside world. We spent hours relaxing in/by the pool, and for a couple of days only saw the cleaner and waiter!
And on other days we ventured out into Seminyak which the villa was very well located for.
title: Fantastic value for money!!

text:
The villas are great and you don't hear your neighbors. 

It is pretty clean and the breakfast age cooked directly in the villa if you want. 

The pool is at a correct temperature. 

We just got once a phone call at 7am to ask if I wanted to cancel my driver when I have put on the breakfast sheet that I want to be awake for 10:30.. That was the disappointing part of the stay. 

For the rest it is a really nice place and the Jacuzzi outside at midnight is wonderful :-) 

Enjoy!
title: Great villas!

text:
We stayed at Pradha villas with our two teenage children. The position was perfect - turn right for the beach which is two minutes walk as is la lucciola great for brekky or turn left for many great cafes, Seminyak square, eat street and shopping so close. The villas are situated along a lovely tropical driveway and we were lucky enough to be opposite the walkway to the street so access was really easy to just everything.  The layout of the villa worked for us with the kids bedroom, bathroom, guest bathroom, lounge and kitchen all in one area and very spacious then across some grass was our bedroom and bathroom also very spacious. The staff were all very obliging to any issues or request not that there were many. The breakfasts were not what I was so keen on but the kids thought they were okay then we would go out for brekky number two! The room service was efficient but not so tasty. The pool although a little chilly very refreshing and I spent many hours on the lounge reading my book day and night listening to geckos, birds and of course roosters! All very peaceful though which was amazing being that we were so close to the action. As other reviews had mentioned there is a bit of wear and tear so I was prepared for this so it wasn't too bad and overall didn't effect our stay. There were lots of mozzies though and we found even with the spraying they were everywhere especially we found in the bathroom and robes which were part open air. The mozzies would hide amongst clothes and in the morning I would pull something out of my case or the drawer and a swarm of mozzies would appear but they just seemed to fly away so it wasn't really a big problem.
Overall we enjoyed our stay and felt very safe at all times and comfortable leaving the kids and going out for dinner etc.
title: Great position, comfortable villa

text:
We were really pleased with Pradha. We've stayed in a few places in Seminyak, so we already knew where we wanted to be. And the location didn't let us down. They are a 5 minute walk to the beach, great restaurants, and shopping. 15 minute walk to potato head and other attractions. 

The villas were just lovely too. The grassy yard, large pool and spacious open air bathroom were the highlights. We didn't want to leave! 

If we had to say anything bad - the area is a tad noisy by comparison to previous villas due to it's close proximity to a busy road and unexpected noisy neighbours. But the team at Pradha went above and beyond to make our stay more comfortable - offering to move us and giving us extra massages. We really couldn't fault them at all! 

Thank you so much! We have already recommended you to other people.
title: Awesome location and very attentive staff.

text:
Absolutely loved my stay at Pradha Villas!
The villa is beautiful - clean and spacious. The staff were incredible. They were extremely attentive and always willing to help with any problems immediately, as there is always someone on the reception desk. One of the girls on the desk (not sure of her name) was amazing - she was so lovely and spent her time organising and ringing companies to plan day trips for me and friends. The villa driver is also amazing and chatted to us the full length of the 8 hour car journeys we had with him - he took us to Uluwatu and Bali Elephant Camp (two places I extremely recommend).
The wifi was pretty good, better than most places.
The location is great, its a 2 minute walking distance was all of the shops and restaurants. We didn't really like the villa breakfast that much so went out for breakfast most mornings - Sisterfields was our favourite place to go! You do have to walk up a black alley to reach the villa, so I would recommend putting some street lights there - but I always felt safe walking the alley and there's security 24hr.

Could not recommend this place enough, absolutely loved it!!!!
title: Perfect!

text:
This was our third time to Bali and the first time to Pradha Villas and we will only stay here from now on. 

The villa is big and so clean, the breakfast is amazing and the staff are so friendly and polite. It is in the best location and also quiet. 

I loved the villa and the staff and would be back next year 100%
title: Loved Pradha Villas

text:
I'm just back after 6 nights at Pradha Villas. The pluses are location being close to Seminyak square and the shops and restaurants as well as walking distance to Potato Head etc.
Staff were friendly and helpful. 

The villa itself was large and clean but as with many other comments placed by other guests, very tired and dated. 

Bathrooms and kitchen need an overhaul no microwave,  no ipod dock. No iron or board. No mosquito net for the bedroom we were given. A few basics like batteries in the air conditioning and TV remote control not working. 

We still had an enjoyable stay but you don't feel very special staying  there its more functional than luxury.
title: Good location  but Villas need updating

text:
My best friend and I booked this villa in a hurry because we were just 3 days away from our trip and we have been too busy at work. 

When we reached the villa, the receptionist welcomed us warmly with a glass of orange juice each. It was definitely a good thirst-quencher since we have been walking around so much since we arrived. As we can only check in at 2pm (we arrived at 8am), so we left our luggages in the luggage room. There is a shower with towels provided in the luggage room too, so if necessary, you may use it. Truth be told,the 'luggage room' isn't as the term describes because it is like a hotel room with a sofa!

The villa was great! There is a large pool for ourselves, a well - furnished kitchen with a water cooler as well. So you can constantly get fresh water to drink without the need to lug bottles of water back. Breakfast was delivered to our villa every morning and it was still warm. 

The bathroom is huge and there is a bathtub and shower depending on your choice. 

The location is excellent too. As it is right in seminyak, you can find many clothing shops and cafes there! I highly recommend the cafes Bistrot and Grocer&Grind as they are awesome places to have coffee and just chill out. Do check out potatohead and ku de ta too. They are great places by the beach.
title: Wonderful stay and highly recommended

text: The villa is very spacious and clean. We spend most of our morning activities swimming in the pool daily The unit is only 5 to 8 mins away (walking distance)from seminyak square. Remember to hv a pair of flat footwear due to the uneven n narrow pathways along the walk. The only 2 negative points I hv for the villa is the mosquitoes n the toiletries. Personally I do not like the smell (jasmine) of the shower gel n shampoo provided. In the end I bought the travel size toiletries from a nearby minimart. The staffs are very friendly n helpful.
title: Free & Easy holiday

text: We could not have chosen a better place for our honeymoon. Great accommodation, fantastic team and perfect location. The villa was clean and the turn down service includes mosquito treatment for the night. Great massage, Ubud tour and romantic dinner was complementary as honeymooners. Will be back
title: Perfect honeymoon

text:
The villas are perfectly located about 5-10mins walk from the beach, restaurants & shopping streets. 
One of the highlights was the staff which was very friendly, readily available & polite. 
The villas have spacious open living room, kitchenette, separate bedrooms, huge bathroom & pool. 
All the villas have ample privacy. 
The food was good & reasonably priced. 
The only drawback of the place would be its internet which was very slow. 
Overall, a pleasant & memorable stay.
title: Wonderful stay !!

text: We stayed in a 2 bedroom villa which was great, the villa was clean and had everything we needed. The rooms were cleaned efficiently every day and the staff were really helpful and friendly. The villa was quiet but in a perfect location, in quick walking distance to the beach and good restaurants. I would stay here again next visit.
title: Great location, lovely stay.

text:
Pros:

- Private pool
- Room is large and clean
- In center of Seminyak, lots of restaurants and shop within 10 mins walk.

Cons:
- It is located between the city center and beach, entrance is in a back lane, sign is not clear.
title: Room with private pool in Seminyak center

text:
We had a two bedroom villa (number 9) in mid May at this location.  

Muma San 800m, Potato Head 400m, W Hotel 500m, Nirvana 400m, La Luchiola 400m.

Our villa was clean and the layout offers exceptional privacy for the occupants of each room.  In our case 2 children in one room with us in our own room which is in a separate building on the opposite side of the private pool.  While the villa is nice, it is showing signs of age.  The doors need a coat of stain, the tap ware in the bathroom is showing signs of age and the cupboards in the kitchen are suffering from exposure. All in all these things didn't detract from a great long weekend relax where we sat by the pool and ate ourselves to death at a number of the restaurants near by.

Breakfast, which was included, was simple but nice.  The standard of cleaning was very good and the staff were very friendly.

Would I stay here again?  Yes.  Value for money?  Definitely.
title: Very good mid range private villa in an outstanding location.

text: Accommodation arrangement has been communicated and organized clearly by the sales department way before arrival from overseas. The staffs helped and threw a birthday surprised for my wife. I took the honeymoon package for my wedding anniversary celebration. The in-villa dinner is romantic. The in-villa massage is relaxing, and my wife loves the Balinese costumes photo session. Airport pickup and drop off is timely. The luxury villa is spacious and carefully designed with pools, heated jacuzzi, bathtub, shower cube, kitchen with stoves, utensils and etc. Bedroom is air conditioned where the rest of the villa is open air close to nature. Mosquitoes are common during the evenings but mosquito coils will be lit by the staffs every evening. The villa is 5 minutes walk to the beach, 5 minutes walk to Seminyak Square area, 7 minutes walk to the fabulous Bambu Restaurant. Highly recommended place to stay and even for long stay.
title: Services to the finest detail

text:
We - my 5 year old daughter, wife and I - stayed at Pradha for 3 nights earlier this week. 

The Villa - Nice stylish villa, great comfortable sized pool and jacuzzi. Lovely open living area (sofas, dining area, kitchen) facing the pool and garden. Some of the interiors are starting to fray a bit at the edges so I hope they do a bit of touching up soon. But nothing that got in the way or was uncomfortable. Extremely nice and helpful staff who were always available for anything we wanted. They don't have a restaurant but they do have a kitchen and a small room service menu. Breakfasts were cooked up by the staff in the villa kitchen, but can also be made in the main kitchen and delivered.

The Location - Great location, on a quiet street just behind Seminyak Square and a few minutes walk from all the high-end shops and restaurants on Jl Kayu Aya aka Jl Laksmana/Oberoi. Also just a 3 minute walk to the beach. Great restaurant - Warung Mina - right outside. Had some excellent Nasi Goreng, Cap Cay and more here. They also deliver to the villa, as do lots of restaurants around the area.

Overall verdict - Had an absolutely blissful stay. Perfect if you're travelling with kids who can't get enough of the pool & jacuzzi & bathtub! :-) Also great if you're 2 families with kids. The villa we were in had 2 bedrooms though one was locked. I'd give this place a little more than 4 on 5.
title: Awesome stay at Pradha Villas

text:
My bf and I stayed in Pradha Villa's one bedroom villa, and the villa was gorgeous! The villa was just comfortable for two persons, and it comes with a pool and Jacuzzi! The staff were friendly and helpful with our needs, and was always available. The villa is also safely guarded, so we didn't had to worry about trespassing or strangers walking in to the villa compound.

The villa is strategically located at Seminyak area, it's 10-minutes walk to Potato Head, and 5-minutes walk to Seminyak Square and the surrounding shops. If you're interested to go for babi guling at Pak Malen, that's a 30-minutes walk from the villa, or grab a taxi, it'll take about 10-minutes at a price of IDR30,000. Overall, getting anywhere is convenient for us. 

We had a pleasant stay and will definitely recommend our friends/families to stay at this villa if they're traveling to Bali!
title: Amazing and relaxing villa!

text: First stop on the first time to Bali. This is a great location, it may seem tucked away a bit, but so quiet after the bustle of the streets. Friendly staff, good driver. Booked a one bedroom Vila but given a two bedroom with one locked. Loved the extra space. Interiors starting to show a little wear. Timber decking with loose boards. Saw little Geckos and frogs around the pool garden, no mozzies at all. The staff sprayed at lit mozzie coils at 6.00 pm everyday. So close the Eat Street and all the shops. Great value for money.
title: Great villas, great location

text:
Still staying here, arrived three days ago, leaving in another three.

If you're looking to check out the places in Seminyak everyone keeps recommending, this place is perfectly located. It is about 20 metres from Motel Mexicola (we stopped in on a whim, and I popped back to our villa after sitting down and ordering dinner to change clothes and come back), and pretty much midway between Potato Head and Ku De Ta (tip - if you're going to Potato Head, don't walk via the roads, go straight down to the beach and walk across that way, it's about half the distance). Bodyworks is literally across the road. The main street is only one street over.

Despite that, it is dead quiet here, which is a big factor for me as I am a very light sleeper. It's just far enough off the street and has high enough walls, that the sounds you'll be hearing are just the birds and geckos living around the property.

The villas are very nice indeed (we are in a "luxury" villa). You know how you usually take promotional photos with a big grain of salt? Well, this place actually lives up to them - although our first impressions may have been skewed because we arrived at night time, when the villas and grounds are very impressive indeed (lighting used to great effect). Nevertheless, very nice and you get what you pay for. I would much rather be here than in one of the nearby five star hotels - you just can't go wrong with your own private pool.

As long as you keep the bedroom doors closed, the air conditioning works fine and the mosquito netting should be unnecessary. Although that means foregoing opening the sliding doors and stepping straight out of bed into the pool, so that's an individual judgement call.

The staff are very attentive and friendly, and the service is excellent. There's some nice little touches as well, e.g. every time we get back of an evening it was to fresh mosquito coils, the villa lights on and the mosquito netting drawn around the bed.

No hesitation in recommending this place. If you're looking to stay in Seminyak, in this price range, I haven't seen anywhere better yet. Forget the hotels, a villa is the way to go, and Pradha is an excellent choice.
title: Location, location, location

text: Our private villa and pool was the perfect escape for our honeymoon. We stayed 8 nights, and enjoyed every moment.  after staying in hotels for years we would recommend to anyone wanting to treat themselves and have complete privacy. Some days it was hard to even leave the villa! The staff were the loveliest people, so helpful and always smiling. They even made my husband a surprise birthday cake. The actual villa was beyond our expectations of spaciousness. beauty and cleanliness. We will definitely stay again even for a few nights at the end of our trip.
title: Honeymoon bliss

text:
Thank you to Pradha Villas for making our trip to Bali a memorable one. The location of these villas are fantastic - close to restaurants, the main shopping strip and Seminyak beach. We stayed in pool villa number 10 which was absolutely amazing. Loved having our own private pool, spa and spacious outdoor living area. The villa was very clean and the bedding extremely comfortable. 

The staff at Pradha Villas were very friendly and always had a smile on their faces. They went out of their way to ensure we were always having a great stay. It was lovely having our breakfast served daily in the villa, as well as our complimentary massages. Thank you for the surprise dessert on Valentines Day and personalised cake on my friends birthday. We will most definitely back.
title: Amazing stay - cannot wait to return!

text:
I would like to firstly express my gratitude to the staffs of Pradha Villas for their kind attention in detail, in making making our stay enjoyable, filled with warm smiles and dedication in attending to all our needs during our stay. Definitely a memorable stay that I will continue to patronise and recommend whoever to stay here. 

The advices provided for tours and the tour guide was commendable and informative about Bali traditions and history. The vicinity of the villa is walking distance to key tourist area such as Potato Head and beautiful Beaches. It is an ideal stay, making shopping easy for anyone. 

A romantic getaway-staycation, ideal for couples. Beautiful villa.
title: Enjoyable Honeymoon

text:
Location is perfect right in the heart of Seminyak - the alley to the villa runs behind Motel Mexicola so was easy to find. Literally less than a 2 minute walk to heaps of restaurants.

Stayed in Pool Villa #11 - very spacious and comfortable.
Pool was in shade for most of the day which really wasn't an issue as its so warm over there.

Our stay included breakfast which was delish and delivered to the villa whatever time we wanted.
Staff were lovely and very accommodating - would definitely stay here again.
title: Perfect location - in the heart of Seminyak

text: Very good location, only a short walk from the main strip and close to lots of good restaurants, and shops. Villa and pool were great and very clean. The staff were extremely accommodating and friendly, always happy to help! Recommended!!
title: Excellent

text:
We really enjoyed our stayed and extended.  We have stayed before and I am really tempted to write a poor review so Pradha is always available when we want to stay!  Super location, fabulous stay - very helpful.  Really clean.  My only limitation is the breakfast is limited for a longer stay.  
Thanks for having us!
title: great villas

text:
Excellent villa in the heart of Seminyak. Just a short walk to great restaurants, bars and shops, and a short taxi ride (if you don't want to walk for 10-15 mins) to Potato Head Beach Club and W Hotel. Body Works spa literally just round the corner, but the Villa offers an excellent in-house massage which is well worth trying.
The Villas are lovely although a little tired. Mosquitos and bugs can be a problem but that's because the living area (and the bathrooms) is open. The staff make every effort to eliminate mosquitos by spraying the rooms and burning mosquito coils around the villa at dusk, which really helps.
My husband and I were travelling with our 2 year old daughter and in-laws. The separate bedrooms worked well for us as we were two couples however, if you're planning on having your kids stay in one room and you in the other then this might not work. The pool was a good size and has a ledge running around half of it which our 2 year old loved walking along, and it made it easier for her to play in the pool.
The only downside was the breakfast. Not great but to be honest you're so close to brilliant cafes - Grocer & Grind, Sisterfields, etc. that we just went there. 
All in all an excellent villa that we would definitely recommend. The staff were very helpful and great with our daughter.
title: Excellent stay and brilliant location

text: We returned in October 2014 as loved it when we were there in October 2012.  Still a great place. Great location, lovely staff, pool wonderful. We were lucky to have the same villa as before. Spacious, clean. But does need some updating as the kitchen is outdated and needs some repair, but it was still fine. Its great to have the separate open kitchen to the bedroom. Very relaxing around the pool. Bed still hard, but acceptable. Breakfast being cooked in the villa is so lovely. The location is so good, great for my husband who surfs every day at Seminyak in the morning, quiet location, but very close to Seminyak Square, Grocer and Grind and all the great restaurants and shops. Shopping is really good. Not far to taxi to Bintang Supermarker, however, we walked there (only 1/2 hour) and returned by cab. We would return here for sure. Prices are a bit too high though, and that would be the only reason we would look for somewhere else if price goes up again, mainly because it needs updating. Dewa and Putu staff great. Overall, lovely place to stay.
title: Still wonderful

text: Wonderful. My daughter's birthday and the staff brought in a surprise cake.  Very good breakfasts and food on site.  Would stay here again. Staff were lovely and they had a shower room for before your flight (after you'd checked out)
title: Great location and villas

text:
Enjoy my stay very much,had a pleasant surprise of being upgraded to the luxury villa.
Breakfasts was great esp the musseli, will definately recommend my friends to stay at the villa is they visit Bali.
Felt greatly taken care of thks so much for everything!
title: Very wonderful stay,all the staffs are very nice n polite

text: The villa was great in terms of size and "traditional" Balinese layout, although I doubt in most bali villas you walk across a pond to get access and have a luxury pool wrap around the buildings in the compound.  So call them "luxurious"traditional bali villas.  The staff certainly treat you like royalty.  So happy to assist and get to know you a bit - a real Balinese hospitality experience which does not feel forced or over done. We had in villa dining and in villa massages.  Both were fantastic.  The villa we stayed in had a "lived in feel" but was comfortable and clean.  It is not the newest kid on the block but had been quality built, designed and furnished.  All in all a great facility for the money.
title: Great villa great location fantastic staff

text:
The villa was a brilliant lay out with a huge outdoor lounge room overlooking the big warm pool.  You could be in the pool and checking on the kids watching a dvd in the lounge room.

The pool was warm with a nice basic spa with about 5 jets at the end. The location was awesome,  a shortcut lane brings you out 50 meters from grocery & grind corner or the standard entrance is 50 metres from body works.  Those who don't know Seminyak,  this is a great spot with easy access to all the best restaurants of eat street and also pettinget.

The staff here were fantastic, we are not normally people who would overly care or notice but this was just a perfect amount of assistance but being left to enjoy the villa in peace.  You can see in the photo they put up a net to help keep the kids away from the pool ( their suggestion). They hooked up a DVD player in the lounge room (one in the the indoor lounge/bed room too). - we have kids so this was a priority. Happy to make calls for us when jetstar cancelled our flights etc.

Food there was really good for hotel restaurant and cheap.  The beers in mini bar were same price as circle K.

Fantastic, we will be heading back for sure.
title: 10th trip to bali - the best villa by far

text:
Although its been a long time since my visit, I still look back on it with fond memories(i visited in 2013 but it wont let me go back that far!). The villas themselves were pristine and exceptionally private. 

The staff were fantastic; anything you wanted was delivered straight away and they were extremely polite and helpful. My boyfriend and I would always forget to order our breakfast the day before and used to do it after getting home from an evening out, at about 2am, and the staff always had it delivered on time and didn't seem annoyed by us! We also got a fantastic complimentary massage which took place in our villa - this was a lovely touch.

Locatiion wise, its brilliant. Far away enough from main things to be really quiet but you have all the special resort bar/restaurants near by - Ku de Ta was a personal favourite.

Overall, it was unforgettable and I would love to go back one day!
title: Paradise

text: We booked the honeymoon package at Pradha and had such an amazing time which included in room massages, a romantic dinner,  daily breakfast, and dressing up in traditional baliense wedding costumes. The staff is so nice and attentive, they spoiled us and we truly loved every moment we spent there. The location is great and the villa is just so beautiful and spacious. It was probably the highlight of our trip. We will definately go back to Pradha on our next visit.
title: Romantic Honeymoon

text: we stayed in Pradha villas for 3 amazing days. From the moment we got there the service was incredible, and the room was beautiful. To have our own pool was a total treat. The room service was really good value and small touches like the big tank of cooled mineral water and amazing breakfasts made this a fantastic villa. Would recommend to anyone!
title: Perfect hotel, amazing service

text:
I stayed in Pradha Villas with my partner last week and it was great. Service was absolutly fantastic, nothing was to much trouble. We got fresh squized orange juice on arrival which we very much appreciated as it was hot like in hell that day. And they also organised transfer to airport for us. 
Food was really good and portions are very generous. And mini bar was replenished daily. We also recived complimentary drinks which was a nice surprise.
They also had treatment at our villa and it was great. We had to book treatments in advance but it was worth it. 
Villa was very clean and towels were change daily. They also sprayed villa daily so we did not have any moscito bites. TV in a living area did not work but let's be honest nobody book villa with private pool and jacuzzi to watch tele. Villa wasn't new but I like a little bit of character. Specially for the price I think it was great.
Villas are very close to the beach and very quite which is a nice opposite to very noisy Seminyak. If I would decide to go back that's where I would stay
title: Great service, great villa

text:
First time in Bali and this was the perfect location for us.
Close to the beach, Seminyak Square, Eat Street and all great places like La Lucciola, Ku De Ta and Potato Head. Basically next door to Body Works for massages and Motel Mexicola for easy lunch, but still very secluded and quiet for relaxation.
The staff are all friendly, polite and extremely helpful. The meals cooked in our villa were delicious and there was an abundance of choice.
The turn down service each night included effective mosquito eradication.  Coils were lit and plug-ins turned on, along with insect repellant spray used to help those of us susceptible to the mozzies.
We spent a few days day-tripping around Bali and many others simply relaxing in the Luxury Villa.  Each night we walked to amazing nearby restaurants and overall had a great 8 nights at Pradha Villas.
title: Great stay for first time travellers to Bali

photos.caption: Breakfast cooked in our villa each morning
Living area of villa at night
Large bathroom with bath and access directly to pool

text:
When you first visit a hotel you've booked online, there's always that trepidation that the place was misrepresented in the photos. This did happen with this place - it was so much better than we expected!

Brilliantly designed, great features, attentive staff, and the glorious pools made this a highly enjoyable stay. 

From the cooked breakfasts (either in room or delivered), to the complimentary juices delivered, to the convenient location, it all went together so well.

The minibar prices were almost as cheap as buying from the convenience store!

All in all, I cannot recommend this place highly enough.
title: The perfect Seminyak retreat

photos.caption: It really is as good as the photos

text:
Love these villas so much and their location! If you want an affordable private villa with a pool within walking distance to everything seminyak has to offer- look no further ! Not even a KM away you have Bodyworks, Ku de ta, Potato head, sea circus, grocer and grind and more. 

Pros include the space as it was massive! Beautiful pool, good daybeds and temperature of wAter. DVD player was a nice touch & TV clear. Plenty of powepoints and hair dyer included plus robes. The toiletries smelt AMAZING and outdoor shower gorgeous.

The only things that made it a 4 star instead of 5 star are:
- Wasp nests above the outdoor shower (rm 10) so please look into it. They weren't bad and are newish so I'm sure the hotel removes them regularly but maybe need to do it more often.
- Staff came into villa unannounced a few times like in the middle of the day to do maintenance works (painting etc) but didn't tell us so we got back from shopping and found workmen there. Also at 8pm one night to spray the Mosquitos down. We love that they do that but please do it at a more reasonable time, maybe 6pm when people are at dinner or watching sunset as jet lagged travellers or families will be in bed by 8pm! 

If those small things are fixed it would have been perfect as the room service food we had were yum, drinks & food reasonably priced and as said loved the room and location. 

We will recommend and will be back! Thank you PradHa Villas!
title: Perfect place to stay (with a few improvements)

text: We stayed at Pradha Villas for our honeymoon and were delighted by the stay that we had. The service was fantastic and they cook your breakfast and bring it to your room (I don't think I've tasted a bowl of muesli that was better than that). The villa was beautiful and very well maintained and the shower and bathroom facilities were a pleasant surprise as to how good they were. We stayed in Villa 14 which was right next to the alleyway that leads to the road near Seminyak Square, which was so convenient. You get the occasional traditional Bali sewer smell in the mornings and after it rains, but it's not over-powering and it never lasted long.
title: Superb Villas in a Great Location

text:
We stayed here as two couples with two babies (6 months and 20 months) for 7 nights. The location was excellent, within walking distance to many restaurants, beach clubs and more. The villas were great, as seen in the pictures. The only thing that was slightly annoying were the mosquitoes. They do their best at the villas to tame them, by weekly foogings and spraying of the villas, rooms and lighting coils. We did turn down the spraying of the villa and rooms because we were with two babies and didn't want them breathing in the repellent, so perhaps this is why we had more mosquitoes. A simple solution for the villa would be to attach mosquito nets on the ceiling and let them drape over the bed. At least at that point, they may still be in the room but they won't be biting you at night (which is obviously when most of that occurs). Other than that, the staff were courteous and the shuttle driver was a very lovely, kind man.  
If they forgot to bring us anything during breakfast, they were certainly prompt in bringing it to us. Overall great stay, lovely staff and perfect location. The pool was kept nice and clean as were the rooms. Thank you for a fantastic week.
title: Great location

text:
I have just returned from a 5 night stay at the Pradha Villas and was very impressed. All the staff were lovely and happy to assist in any way. We took advantage of the in villa massage service and the standard was very high. Located down a peaceful and beautiful Gang yet close enough to some of the best cafes in Seminyak, 5 minutes to the beach and Seminyak Square and with the shuttle bus provided we hardly had to catch a taxi during our stay. The villa pool was a perfect temperature and not too shaded as in other villas we have stayed at.
I am already planning my next trip to Pradha Villas with my young family after this time staying with a friend. Highly recommended and good value for money.
title: Great location, lovely staff

text:
We stayed at Pradha Villas for three nights. The villas are located very close to Potato Head beach club, the beach, and a lot of restaurants and shopping. Each morning they gave a choice to have breakfast cooked in their kitchen and brought to the villa or have someone cook breakfast for you in your villa. The breakfast was adequate but not always filling. 

Each night they would send someone to spray for mosquitos and start burning a coil. We never had a problem with bugs during our stay which was great. The pool was also very clean and warm. As others have mentioned the items in the fridge are cheap enough, but there is also a little convenience store about a 5 minutes walk away. We had a couples massage at the villa that was great. The villas are a bit more expensive than others in the area, but they are secluded and within a short walk of everything you need. The room was also very quiet.
title: Great Stay

text: We are a family of four who stayed at Pradha for 8 nights. We enjoyed every minute in our beautiful, quiet, comfortable villa. The staff was very friendly and accomodating. We felt like they were there only for us. For our son's birthday, the staff came in with a chocolate cake and sang Happy Birthday! The breakfast was prepared in our villa and we had a good choice of main dishes, juices, fruit, and more. There was a free shuttle service depending on availability, and it was available most of the time. You only need 5 minutes to walk to the beach, and a couple more minutes to Potato Head.
title: Still brings a smile to my face

text:
if you haven’t stayed at Pradha then you don’t know what it is to have experienced the best. From the stunning villas to the flawless, warm, genuinely personal service, Pradha represents excellence in every way. We want to thank everyone in Pradha family for making our stay so wonderful – you’re more than world class, you define the standard. Whenever we are in Seminyak, Pradha is the only place we will consider staying at. Special thanks to the Manager, she helping me to solve our problem with our agent about the cot, very professional service was deliver from her. We spend our 2weeks with Pradha, we feel don't want to leave. My Family really had a great time.

Very recommended.
title: FABULOUS

text:
We spent quite some time researching for a suitable place to stay in Bali, and overall we were pleased with our choice of Pradha Villas in Seminyak. 
PROS:
It's well situated with a 5 minute walk to the beach (turn right) or Seminyak Square (and restaurant street) 5 minutes to the left. It is set back from the road and is therefore a quiet location. The staff constantly tried to keep us happy, fulfilling every request with promptness and a smile. Nice setting with a balinese style about it - the open common living area was great. The in-room breakfasts were a relaxing way to start the day (compared with the resort style buffets that mean you have to 'get ready' to go to breakfast!). The private plunge pool was jus the right size for a dip. Having two separate buildings as the bedrooms (and their respective bathrooms) ensured privacy for us and the 2 teenage boys! The Wifi worked very well. The staff will organise any transport needs, and any activities (we had a day at Waterbom Park). Highly recommend the 10 minute walk to Ku De Ta as the best beach spot to camp for the day. Plenty of restaurants to choose from Seminyak Square southwards. The cheapest was The Kitchen Club opposite Ginger Moon - great feed, and never crowded (don't understand why though - it's fab).
CONS:
The main negativity was about the state of the walls, doors and floors - clean where it counted, but dirty hand-marks on doors, floors under cabinets (in the bathroom) not clean, and some walls in need of a touch up. If these sorts of things bother you, then you need to pay a little more and go somewhere else.
title: Great Location: Comfortable without pretentiousness

text: Staying here for 4 nights. Very nice villas and friendly staff! Awesome place to come back to and relax in your private pool after a stroll through town. Unbelievably quiet considering proximity to hustle and bustle. Very clean.  Daily breakfast and afternoon drinks in your villa. If you book on booking.com you get a free massage!
title: Great stay!!!

text: We stayed at Pradha for 7 nights. It is located nicely between the beach and the shops in an off street, so no noise. The individual private villas have their own pool and Alfresco cooking, lounging and living area. Up to 2 separate bedrooms in each site with outdoor showers. Perfect if you do not want resort accommodation and staff cannot do enough for you. If you go as a group, they have villas with adjoining doors through the brick walls.
title: Quite, Peaceful, Excellent Accommodation

text:
The Pool Villas are definitely huge, however they are quite dated. Because of the design, they are extremely open which is nice, however the mosquitos are a real issue (to such a point where you can't really utilise most of the space). 

The Hotel staff are very friendly but not overly efficient and we had a variety of mistakes with some of our requests (such as Taxi bookings etc.). The hotel are able to organise a scooter for you which we did, however the person who provided the scooter wasn't the best. Firstly the scooter locked up and needed to be replaced and he was going to organise a transfer for us and was purposefully deceptive. 

The breakfast isn't great and there is no actual restaurant onsite, they simply cook the food in the kitchen and bring it to you. The location is very good however and you are just around the corner from a variety of great food spots. 

All in all the hotel is by no means horrible, but for the price you can definitely find something better.
title: Overpriced - Better Alternatives

text:
Loves every moment, beautiful villas, very well maintained and the staff were great. Near to all the shops and bars.... But far enough away to be silent at night... I'd Deffo go back :) 
Bali itself was great fun a must see on a scooter!! Felt very safe there.
title: Relaxing in Style

text:
Quaint and private villa, located just 5min walk away from seminyak square and the main beach area where good dining spots can be found. The villa has a good decent sized pool and deck area where you may arrange to have your massage done (right in your own comfortable villa without having to travel out). Breakfast is also served in the villa. Friendly and hospitable staff that will make you feel really comfortable and loved. They do come to your villa to clean regularly to keep away the mosquitoes which is really thoughtful. Overall, it is a wonderful stay at 
Pradha Villas and it is a place that I would recommend you to try out when you are in seminyak, bali.
title: Quaint and affordable private villa with pool, away from buzz yet near to the action

text:
Underwhelmed is probably the best way to describe the Pradha Villas, like all accommodation there are good and bad points, but a supposed 4* villa there should be more positives than negatives.
Food was at best very average, the villas are totally open and with the amount of Mosquitos can't be used at night, all areas of our villa were poorly finished with peeling paint and damp patches throughout the bathroom.  We stayed for 6 days and it wasn't until day 4 they told us drinks were free between 1-3pm, we had to chase the staff for breakfast forms on 3 occasions (which have to be filled in daily). 
At the beginning of our stay we attempted to use the jacuzzi but unfortunately this drains nearly as quick as you can fill it, so without the water running constantly the jacuzzi is useless!!
Lastly the shower was terrible, nothing more than a dribble of water with both taps on full.

Although there are many negatives, there are also several positives, the location is excellent villas are in a quiet area even though only minutes away from the main area, pool outstanding and the staff always helpful and polite.

In our opinion with a bit of TLC and some modernisation the Pradha Villas would be worth it's 4* or higher, but unfortunately until then I could not in all honesty recommend this place.
title: Distinctly disappointed!

text:
My first wedding anniversary and its great. The most I like is the staff, they are really friendly and helpful. The villa is amazing and clean. My six months old really had a good time here.
But the food and the towel is not really good. 
Even the villa near city but it's very quite.
Thank You
title: Friendly Staff

text:
WE spent 2 weeks at Pradha Villas in July, August 2014 and it was AMAZING. The location is only 5 minute walk to beach and a short walk to shops and cafes in and around Seminyak. The Villas are spotlessly clean and the private pool was FANTASTIC (about 9mts long and sunny) The rooms are BIG and beds are very comfortable, the bathrooms are HUGE with rainmaker shower and spa. Breakfast was a eating sensation,fresh fruit, cereal, fresh juice,coffee,tea,toast and eggs all cooked perfectly in your Villa. The staff are VERY HAPPY and incredibly warm and are always available to offer their assistance. We DEFINITELY, HIGHLY recommend Pradha Villas, you WILL NOT BE DISAPPOINTED.  
Miss Mary-Ann and Mr Alan
title: AMAZING

text: We stayed here for 4 nights and it was amazing, we are already planning our next trip back.  It's tucked away off the main strip so it's super quiet.  Great location (2mins from Bodyworks, Mexicola and a short walk to Sarong and Potato Heads.  The staff are amazing and they make your breakfast in your own villa.  The place was huge and the pool also.  Can't fault the place 10/10.
title: Amazing Villa!

text:
This is the second time I've stayed at Pradha Villas and again I had a really enjoyable stay.
The villa itself is private, clean and equipped with everything to ensure your stay is super relaxing. The staff are incredibly warm and happy and always available to offer their assistance. 
Located in a perfect pocket of Seminyak, close to Seminyak square and the beach, everything is at your doorstep.
I would definitely recommend Pradha Villas if you're wanting a really comfortable holiday.
title: Great stay second time round

text:
We chose Pradha Villas for our last night before flying back to Singapore and booked it only 1 day in advance.

The Villas are absolutely beautiful and we were quite stunned when we walked in, finding out that we had our own pool and jacuzzi! There were also complimentary fruits on the table and we received a welcome drink and a free shuttle service to the airport the next day.

Even though it is right next to a busy road, during the night it was pretty quiet and we slept like logs in the big beautiful bed.

The bathroom is massive and open to the back where you can go for a swim in the pool - a dream!

The staff is exceptionally friendly and courteous which made our stay memorable.

We regret that we only had one night booked but can only highly recommend it and we would definitely come back!

We loved it!! :-)
title: Stunning!!

text: I recently travelled to Bail on business with a friend and we chose these villas after carefully scrutinising all of the reviews on trip advisor. When we arrived, we were met by a lovely, welcoming young woman who checked us in like we were the only guests on earth. Great start. We were then shown to our 2 bedroom villa with private pool (sorry folks, I have no recollection of the number) and immediately fell in love with the place. What's not to adore about an open plan space with equipped kitchen and lounge area, a fantastic pool that is entirely private, and separate and huge bedrooms with bathrooms that have showers that are open to the stars? We had a fantastic massage in our villa that evening and the following morning, our breakfast was cooked for us in our own private kitchen. Can't wait to get back for a longer period to lounge around like a princess.
title: Can't wait for a return visit

text:
We stayed in Pradha Villas for a total of 6 nights, rented a 2 bedroom villa.
The staff was absolutely wonderful!! They are warm, super helpful and hospitable. The airport shuttle was on time(thanks Deva!). Kadek, the manager is the best and gave us great suggestions for any of our questions on dining, sight-seeing and shopping. We wanted to do a 1day organized tour to Java, and she called the travel agent and got all the details for us.  The staff gave us locations of the genuine Currency exchange center, the local market, got us Bluebird taxis, and overall, helped us with anything we needed.

The villas have a nice spacious living room, kitchen and dining area. The bedrooms are large and so is the outdoor bath area. The private pool was much bigger than we expected. The location is very central, 5 min from Seminyak square and also from the beach and restaurants. They had a free shuttle to Kuta beach that was very convenient. Inspite of being in the heart of the busy area, the villa was very quiet and peaceful.

The complimentary breakfast cooked at the villa was good and always on time. We also ordered room service a couple times and the food was good. 
My daughter had some stomach pain and the staff who came to clean the room, brought over a bottle of Cajuput oil, that helped her. That was very sweet and kind!.

We would LOVE to go back to Bali and when we do, will definitely stay in Pradha Villa again!! Thanks again to the staff for making our vacation a memorable one!
title: Beautiful centrally located villa with exceptional staff

text: Booked this villa, finding from the review, we are so happy to choose to stay here, loved the villa, very big room, even the bathroom is very spacious, big pool and complete with heated jaccuzy in the end, make may stay very enjoyable. The service from staff is best, they clean our room, cooked our breakfast and arrange our need with their courtesy all of them make us feel save and comfortable. I wish we could have more time to extend our stay, but we will definitely coming back to this villa. Thank you for free upgrade to Luxury Villa, we totally recommend this villa.
title: Beautiful villa on great location with great staff

text:
Selected Pradha Villas for our stay after much research and turns out it was the perfect choice :) We were staying in the 2 room pool villa. 
Much emphasis on the hospitality! The staff is absolutely amazing and very helpful. I had a problem with one of the taps in the bathroom and it was fixed WITHIN half an hour of me calling the reception. They are incredibly punctual and breakfast was brought in every morning few minutes before time! I was quite satisfied with the choices on the breakfast menu and tried a different main dish every morning :) we ordered in lunch one day and quite enjoyed that as well. 
Since we had a baby with us, we needed help with blowing up his float so he could join us in the pool and the staff came and did that within minutes of our request. They're also SO friendly and playful with the babies, its really sweet :) 
It's only a couple of minutes walk to the seminyak square one side and to the beach on the other side. Wonderful choices of restaurants to go to! Highly recommend the moonlight cafe and zucchini cafe. 
I only suggest that they make sure there is hot water in the jacuzzi for the 2 room villa which we didn't have :(
But our stay was super comfortable and Definitely worth visiting again :)
title: Cozy and comfortable. Great stay!

photos.caption: american breakfast with fruit platter and watermelon juice. You also get bacon with your eggs
sitting area next to the kitchen and dining area

text: Apart from an overhaul on towels required and average breakfast the rest of the stay was superb and such a good location. (A short walk to Grocer & Grind, Seminyak Square, La Lucciola, Ku de Ta)  Staff very helpful and in-house massage facilities also great value and very good.
title: Fantastic stay with excellent staff

text: Our first visit to Bali with family who have stayed here several times in the past. Easy airport transfer, beautiful staff and lovely clean accommodation.  Very spacious. WE stayed in two bedroom villa with pool I could hardly keep out of. Could use a lick of stain on the decking, a fresh coat of paint and maybe some new bamboo blinds.  Would return.
title: Peaceful and quiet

text:
It was the first time we visited Bali and was very impressed with the level of comfort and space.
The airport transfer is smooth and all the staffs were very courteous and friendly, typical of Bali's hospitality.
We had a two room villas and the private pool with Frangipane flowers was a nice treat. Each room are house in separate buildings with its own open-planned en-suite, with bath and open shower, well shrouded from view to ensure privacy.    
Room service was reasonable in price and breakfast was brought to our villas and set out on tables individually. 
It was easily accessible to Seminyak square in less than 5 minutes walk where you get shops, restaurants and beaches. Overall, the place may have look a bit dated compared to the brand new villas next door, the place still offers very good value.
title: Comfort and seclusion and yet so accessible

text:
When booking for Bali I was extremely overwhelmed with how many Villas and Hotels there were to choose from, I basically just Picked one that looked central and had good reviews. 
As this was our first time to Bali but had been to Thailand numerous times we were not really sure what to expect of the accommodation and villa style. 

We were not disappointed at all, from the moment we were collected at the airport from the hotel (very cheap transfers and highly recommended as it is very busy) I could tell it was going to be a great stay. 

Our room was amazing, a lot bigger than I expected, it was a one bedroom luxury villa, the pool was great as it was shaded for most of the day allowing it to stay cool which was nice as it was so hot outside! Very private rooms and well appointed. 
After reading some reviews regarding the excess bugs as the villas are open planned, we took our own Aero guard but did not need once as the staff would come around each night and set up coils and spray the rooms. 

The breakfast was good, I stuck to the Ham and cheese toasted sandwich however my partner had the bacon and eggs and he said it was nice. The fact you get it delivered and set up in your room is quite a treat. 

The bed is extremely comfy, and the aircon can be adjusted. Bathroom is huge. 

The location is really good, we didn’t need a scooter, we could walk everywhere. the hotel had organised private day trips up to Ubud and the Volcano and then another to Nusa Dua and Uluwatu - i would highly recommend to do this as it is very cheap and a great way to see some of the island. 

There are a lot of massage places around - after trying many of them, we personally found the one as you walk out of the main gate of the hotel it’s just nearby in a little old house type of thing. The girls actually knew reflexology and were really good! 

My only advice to the hotel and I have seen this in other reviews would be to update their bath towels, they are a little old - clean but old. 

We will definitely be returning!
title: Wonderful Staff

text: Me and my partner went on the 21st September 2011 and stayed at these Villas for 3 nights. We stayed in a Deluxe Villa and it was absolutley lovely I don't have one bad word to say about it and would definately go again. The location is brilliant you are a 5 minute walk from the beach and a 5 minute walk from the town where there is lots of lovely resturants. The staff at the villa's can't do enough for you and they are very professional and friendly. We had room service for lunch every day and the food was delicious. We had sunshone everyday and it was perfect.
title: Perfect

text:
We arrived late into Bali and my partner and I were slightly nervous about the qualitiy of the Pradha Villas especially after driving down some small back streets at 1am to find our accommodation but we were nothing short of amazed once we walked into our villa. It was HUGE, well fitted out and really clean. The staff were friendly and helpful too.

It wasn't until the next morning that we realised what a great location the villas were in. We were walking distance to everything in Seminyak.

Couldn't say a bad word about these villas. Awesome!
title: Absolutely fantastic!

text:
After reading all the other reviews I entered these Villas with mixed expectations.  I have travelled to Bali many times and have stayed in several different Villas around Seminyak.  Now while the Prahda Villas are not the newest in Bali, and could do with a few things improved such as, water pressure – and it takes a long time for the showers to get hot, a bottle opener in the bathrooms for the supplied bottled water and new towels  – there are many pros to these Villas, such as the location and the staff. 
 We stayed in a Two Bedroom Villa – 4 friends – perfect for this trip.  The Villa is big, in a great position, the staff were extremely helpful, although the cleaners are a little hit and miss, yes the towels are old, but everything is clean.  Kitchen is well equipped with lots of drinking water, mini bar is well stocked and inexpensive, all TVs have DVD players, although there was no TV in the lounge and no Ipod Doc.  Room service was good – we stuck to the Indonesian dishes and breakfast is OK, not unlike what is on offer at the other Villas around town – but the variety does get boring, however Grocer and Grind is just up the street if you feel like a change.
For Value for money, customer service and position you can’t go wrong here.
title: Nice Villas in an awesome positon

text:
My girlfriend and i have been going to bali 3 times per year for last 14 years.Stayed at Samaya many times.Stayed next door at the Legian once(yuk)Stayed at the Oberoi in our early days but without doubt Pradha Villas is devine stayed there 10 times now.1bed luxury villa.Own Big pool/spa 5 star furnishings.3 mins walk to beach,eat st,seminyak sq,bodyworks,grocer and grind.Perfectly positioned and perfect staff.Never had there breakfast in room,so cannot comment.Nothing is too much trouble for all the great staff.
Will be back there 2nd sept for 2 weeks.Love it.our second home.
title: Superb

text:
Just spent around 2 weeks at the Pradha Villas and could not have been happier!

Why?
1. Perfect position - walk to everything in 10 minutes... the beach, eat street, ku de ta, potato head, la lucciola, bodyworks, you name it.
2. Super polite and helpful staff - they'll clean the room when YOU want it, always ready to help, booking restaurants, drivers. Special thanks to the lovely Nia and the super efficient Dewa!
3. Large villas - There were 2 of us and we had the 2 bedroom villa with the second bedroom locked and it was massive. Like coming home to a house each night. Large living, big bedroom, huge bathroom. Better than the pictures!
4. Superbly kept premises - Upkeep is very good on the common areas and gardens, chlorine in the pool every day
5. Great value - We shopped around before booking and if you stay anywhere else you are being ripped off!
6. Decent food - The included breakfast was not glamorous but was very edible and way more than we could eat each day. The chicken sandwich I had for lunch from room service was better than any I had in a restaurant while over there.

We'll be back!
title: When the only thing you can find to complain about is the slightly slow internet you know you have a winner!

text:
Well fellow travellers, here is my JBR from Bali.After doing a villa search and finally choosing one (Prada Villas) we were somewhat disappointed with our choice.  The position was good for us (near The Dusan villas, same street as Grocer and Grind) but the villa was tired/not maintained well and the staff although friendly were really not well-trained in service/hospitality.  Our Villa (2) had good facilities re room size and pool but had basic creature comforts.  I think a good measuring stick is the quality of the towels-these were at the "rough,grey and scratchy" end of the spectrum.  The bed was really comfortable,pillows good,linen clean, but again, on the older side of new. Breakfast - all 4 styles were edible but unremarkable!! The pool was large and in the sun and clean but no umbrella on offer and none available.  All in all,would I stay here again? Maybe if I got an amazing deal.... but with all the villas on offer in bali, I think/know we could do better.
I shall do a food review in a couple of days.  hope this is useful to other travellers, HelMelbourne
title: JBR from Bali heaven!

text:
my husband & I stayed at Pradha Villas for 4 nights at the end of January.   we booked via Asia rooms.   the vllla mgt were very efficient and contacted us to organise our airport transfers etc, we didn't have to contact them!  so thought off to a good start.    on their site they had advised within walking distance of everything which i must admit i was a bit cynical about -- well ....they did not lie!  the location was superb.    the Villas are within walking distance of the beach and some lovely restaurants & Ku de ta for a few drinks!   if you wanted to go further, taxis could be organised easily.
the villas themselves were fabulous!  we stayed in a one bedroomed villa, which was well laid out and had everything we needed.
our flight was not until the day of our departure and the staff were very accommodating and allowed us to have a late check-out which made a huge difference to us, and meant we had some extra hours by the pool.
would highly reocmmend these villas to anyone!
title: Excellent Location, Excellent Vila & great staff.

text:
We stayed in this accommodation after staying in the best hotel that I had ever stayed in. That said, the Pradha did not disappoint. If you like privacy this is the place for you. The villas had a nice private pool and Jacuzzi, an open plan living area with cooking facilities and a separate bedroom which, was across the grounds and it had an en-suite bathroom, which was also open air next to the shower. It was nicely furnished but had signs of damp in places. Bali is a wet place! 

The breakfasts were adequate and were served in your villa. 

The location was excellent just a couple of minutes from the beach and 5 minutes from the shops and restaurants in Seminyak. 

The staff was friendly and helpful. 

The only down side was our bedroom had a lot of mosquitoes. The staff did spray the room every night, but it did not seem to get rid of them. The open-air bathroom may have been to blame.

I liked these villas and would stay again.
title: Good location, private pool and open plan living

text: I have been to Bali many times and prefer to stay around the Seminyak area for its slightly quieter ambience and less overtly touristy features. Having tried a number of different places in the past, I decided to give Pradha Villas a go and was very pleasantly surprised. Its main attraction is the location, right in the middle of Seminyak, within walking distance of the beach and Seminyak village, and near a number of bars and restaurants including Ku De Ta, Breezes at The Semaya and La Lucciolla. Happily, it is tucked away from the main road so there is no outside noise audible from inside the villas. The villas themselves are a delight - large and comfortable, with beautiful swimming pools, living areas and outside bathrooms. I was slightly disappointed in the breakfasts - while adequate, they weren't anything special and seemed to be a Balinese chef's take on western food. Room service food was similarly uninspiring. However, the friendliness and service of the staff was second to none and nothing was too much trouble - the manager was able to organise a day trip for us at less than the rate found in the glossy brochures at the airport and was also able to accommodate us in another villa prior to a late night flight. Overall, a great place to stay for any lenghth of time in Bali and thoroughly recommended.
title: Beautiful villas perfectly located

text:
Have just finished a week at Pradha Villas. Was going to choose some other villas but changed my mind at the last minute. Very happy that I did.

The location is perfect for us, away from the hassles of Kuta. Yet walking distance to fantastic restaurants, spas, shopping, the beach etc. We walked to dinner every night, the beach is five minutes walk the other way (not the best beach I must admit, but we prefered lounging by the pool anyway).
We had a two bedroom villa with the second bedroom locked. The place was huge. The pool was fantastic, plenty big enough (not some small plungee pool) It was checked and cleaned daily. The villa got plenty of sun unlike others that you read about.

 The staff were wonderful as well, so friendly, they don't speak the best english so bare that in mind.

I would recommend to anyone wanting a nice relaxing place to stay. If you do want to go into Kuta you can get there by taxi for 30,000 to 40,000 rupiah which I was happy to pay to be where we were.
I
title: Great Location - Would recommend

text:
This property is a great deal.   I'd highly recommend it for anyone who wants luxury on a budget or for families that need a lot of space.

We had a two bedroom compound -- two individual one bedroom villas + a communal living room and plunge pool. 

Each individual compound is very secluded / quiet and tastefully decorated with a fusion of modern and Balinese design elements.  Bed rooms are basic but attractive.  Bathrooms are quite large (two sinks, a bath tub, rain shower).  The plunge pool was larger than I had expected (must have been 30-40 feel in length).  The communal living room has a kitchenette making it possible to cook if you prefer a night "at home."

Wireless internet is available (but very slow -- which is normal for Bali).  Bring your own adapter if you don't have a local plug.  I ended up charging through the shaver outlet.  Also, note that the hotel does not have umbrellas (and you will likely need them).

Service was adequate but not exceptional but at this price you can't possibly complain.  Also, be aware that the property does not have a central spa facility (though in-room service is available at good rates) or business center.

Villa Pradha isn't on the water but is within walking distance of the beach, great restaurants (e.g., Ku De Ta) and it is very close to the main shopping street in Seminyak.
If you are okay giving up the ocean view, this is a great option.  

I certainly prefer the rooms here over those at the far more costly Legian.  Waka Maya in Sanur offers similar value but in a more Balinese style.  I prefer the Oberoi for the ocean front views and would definitely recommend the Four Seasons if you are up for a bit of a splurge.
title: Great value for money in a very convenient location

text:
After much research, I believe this place is the best value private villa style accommodation in Bali (certainly in Seminyak).  Paid US$225/night (+tax) for a 162sq metre 1br private villa (#5), with own pool and jacuzzi.

Recommend for a romantic getaway or honeymoon.

PROS:
- Villa design is brilliant, mix of indoor/outdoor.  HEAPS of space.
- Central location, close to beach and centre of Seminyak restaurants, whilst being a block off the main road provides a little peace and quiet.
- Staff are friendly, lovely and kindhearted, offering the occasional free shuttle to any nearby destination.
- Privacy.  Brilliant.
- In house room service food and massage services top notch and very reasonably priced (not typical hotel rip off).
- Complementary water bottles every day, plus a large water filter, means you do not have to pay for safe drinking water at all during your stay.
- Security: always felt very safe, security guards at the entrance around the clock.

CONS (hard to find!):
- Average standard of English amongst most staff made some conversations a little hard to communicate.  Also, they are not quite knowledgeable of the local area and queries we had (may also be due to lack of English).  eg. Could not recommend location for cooking classes, yet we found a restaurant 200m away (Satay Bali) offered them.
- Internet is available to purchase by the hour or day.  WiFi is readily available for free in most cafes and restaurants in Seminyak.  WiFi internet should be provided free of charge.
title: Fantastic affordable private villa style accommodation

text:
Stayed recently at The Pradha Villas in Seminyak. Having never been to Bali before I was a little uncertain about what to expect regarding its location and standard. I was pleasantly surpised as to the standard, cleanliness and hospitality shown by the staff! Very close, not unpleasant walking distance to the beach, restaurants and taxis to head to Kuta etc. Reception arranged transport for day trips. You could get closer to the beach but would pay substantially more per night. The pool at the villa was quite large and great to get into after several hours at the beach. Air-conditioning in the rooms was very refreshing.
The value for money and great hospitality shown by the staff make it difficult for me to find any negatives. However if pressed I would say that the internet service was very unreliable, and in hindsight it was easier to walk the 5 minutes up the road to Coffee and Grind  have a drink and check email for free. The back entrance lane-way was very useful shortcut, but closed at 9pm for security reasons, meaning a longer walk around to the main gate. If they could put a security key entrance it would be much more convenient, esp after a few drinks! All in all a great experience and I would stay there again, Diwah and his team know what they are doing!

One thing to watch out for at least for us, was the departure tax, the amount was not the issue (150,000 IDR), rather i was not told about it, and having to track down some IDR at the minute was annoying. Knew about the incoming tax (US$25per person).

Found the level of traders hassling to purchase to be ok, lot less than what I've experienced in Thailand. It makes it all part of the experience. The beach area out in front of KuDeTa was really nice.
title: Great Value for money - great hospitality!

text:
The villa looks just like the photos, it is well maintained. 

The staff is super friendly and attentive. We wanted some music and asked to borrow a speaker, they brought a nice harman kardon BT speaker for us.

1pm: cleaning staff shows up in a group of 3-4 at around to quickly clean up the place.

Breakfast: they have local Indonesian option, vegetarian option, and Western options which also comes with coffee and fruit juice.

We enjoyed our stay here and the staff provided great hospitality

Location is close to many restaurants and amenities nearby. Floating Pool breakfast was a pleasant experience. better breakfast and coffee options nearby

The rooms are very spacious and housekeeping was exceptional each day. I would highly recommend if you wish to stay central to Seminyak.

text:

text:

Every morning we received a fantastic complementary breakfast, some days ‘floating style’, which is served in a large basket in the pool, which I totally recommend. 
Pradha Villas are in a great location, close to popular local establishments such as the Sisterfields and Revolver cafes and also the crazy busy Motel Mexicola to name but a few. Being so close to the action you would expect noise, and you do get a little, but it really isn’t disturbing at all. The staff were brilliant, they impressed us more and more everyday with their attentiveness and friendliness. 
All in all, I will definitely look to stay here again on our next trip to Bali.

text: We really enjoyed our stay in a two bedroom villa. The pool is a great size the staff were really responsive.I loved the flower art in the driveway made with the flowers that had fallen off the trees. The villas are very close to the beach and walking distance from all great restaurants;
title: Excellent

text:

text: We went for a short 2 night break, by far the best feature of this place is the location. Villa was clean and everything worked, maybe the air conditioning could be better. Not cool enough sometimes, staff are friendly and try hard which made us overlook the little grievances we had. title: Lovely stay

title: Best Villa in Seminyak

text:
