a little jacuzzi pool add the great experience in this villa.
title: Good location, clean and friendly staff

text:
We recently spent 4 days at Pradha Villas and from the moment we arrived had a wonderful time. The Pradha arranged complimentary transport from the airport and we were greeted oat Pradha reception by a smiling and very helpful young lady. Our 2 bedroom villas was very modern and our private pool larger than expected and lovely and clean. The lounge area is open to the elements with heavy drop down blinds for when the rain comes but lovely and modern. Bedding, towels and sheets were all of a high standard. Staff around the villas were extremely friendly and helpful.
My daughter read on trip advisor about the floating breakfast which staff served in our private pool. A wonderful experience.
We really enjoyed our stay at Pradha and would highly recommend it.
The villas are nice and quiet yet extremely well located close to restaurants and beach where we experienced lovely sunsets sipping on cocktails at one of the many bars/restaurants along the beachfront.
title: Fantastic well appointed and well located villa

text: These villas are great.  The pool was divine, well cared for.  It was very quiet, yet so close to all the great restaurants in Seminyak.  We only had to walk for <10 minutes to Motel Mexicola, Bikini, La Lucciola.  Excellent position.  Staff were lovely.  Only down side was no pillow alternatives (I prefer memory foam pillows).  Breakfast was so generous, we didn't need any lunch (and we left the leftover breads for the tiny birds who frequented our pool area!).  We had a very private villa, it was at the farthest end of the property, but I think all the villas would have been equally quiet and private.  There is a great bluetooth sound system, and there is unlimited drinkable water available from a water cooler.  The kitchen was handy for making our own cocktails.  Room service rates were very cheap and the in-villa massages were great.  The place could have done with a bit of maintenance, and the design of the tiles in the bathroom wasn't great (I stubbed my toe about 10 times), but it was otherwise well maintained.  Excellent value, you won't regret choosing this place!
title: Beautiful stay

text:
We recently returned from Bali and we stayed part of our holiday at Pradha Villas( 5 nights).  We are a family of 4 so the 2 bedroom Villa was very suitable.  All the staff at Pradha were fantastic and very friendly.  The location of Pradha is great , very close to restaurants, shops and bars.  The pool was a good size so was the lounge area.
Great property for families.
title: Ideal Villa in great location

text:
Great location, spacious rooms, nice decor. Thank you to the staff who offered all the help possible and made our stay a memorable one.
I would certainly recommend the place to all friends visiting Seminyak.
title: Memorable stay

text:
We initially chose Pradha due to its location, but there are so many other reasons to also choose to stay here.
 Due to a flight delay, we had a late arrival. Staff still waiting with smiles on their faces at midnight! We stayed in one of the luxury one bed villlas. Very spacious and well laid out. The bath room is huge. It is an open air living area and partial open bathroom, but the bedroom is enclosed and fully air conditioned. Lots of room to store luggage. Mosquito netting was provided around the bed.

We had breakfast included. It was generous and we enjoyed it. There is also a range of well priced in room dining options. The mini bar is very well priced, no inflated prices here. I like the fact they include taxes and charges as part of the price, so you know exactly what you are paying. I also had an in villa massage. Again, very well priced and it was a good massage.

Location wise, it can’t be beaten. It is literally a 5min walk in either direction to a huge range of restaurants and bars. Right next door is a great little Warung called Mina. Lovely food and acoustic live music in the evening. If massages is what you are after, Bodyworks is 2mins in one direction and Spring Spa is 5mins in the other.

Whilst there is some occasional traffic noise, it is minimal and there is still the sense of a lush oasis when you walk into your villa. The gardens surrounding the villas are gorgeous and well cared for. All staff are friendly and responsive to any requests - from ground staff to reception, they go out of their way to help and anticipate your needs.

Thank you! We plan to return next year.
title: Wonderful stay

text: Stunning villa, exceptional service from staff available 24/7 - exceeded my expectations above and beyond, awesome location. Definitely recommend to take up the airport transfer from the villa as the location is slightly hidden. Zero complaints! Had an amazing stay with friends. Would highly recommend, and I will be back.
title: Simply stunning.

text: My partner and I stayed at Pradha Villas for 4 nights in July on our first trip to Bali. We loved everything about it. The Villa was beautiful, the pool was big, bed comfortable, service amazing and in the best location. We can't wait come back to Bali and we will definitely be staying at Pradha Villas when we return.
title: The perfect stay in Bali

text: Still here in Seminyak Bali. We stayed at Pradha Villas just under a week. We're leaving tomorrow but it has been a wonderful stay. Pradha is in busy Seminyak but you forget the chaos as soon as you arrive. It was like having a private sanctuary away from the hustle and bustle. The staff are friendly, courteous and efficient and lovely to talk to. We had breakfast included and served in our villa every morning on time and there was so much to choose from. The villa itself is extremely large with 2 bedrooms, outdoor loungeroom, pool, kitchen, huge outdoor showers and a pond with goldfish! Loved our stay here. Thank you to reception, cleaners, gardeners and breakfast staff for making our stay wonderful!! We hope to visit again :-)
title: Peace and quiet in Seminyak

text: Decided to stay here on a whim with my partner for a few nights at the end of our holiday - greatest decision ever. As soon as we walked into our private villa the price made total sense and was worth every cent. The villa is beautifully maintained and cleverly laid out, the bedroom wonderful and spacious and even the bathroom somehow made me really enjoy needing to practise hygiene. Spent a lot of time having drinks in our pool, sometimes wandered off to look around Seminyak or have a meal but when we didn’t even want to leave the comfort and luxury of our villa the room service was impeccable and we used gojek a couple of times to bring outside food in, too convenient. The staff were very friendly and polite, the wifi connected well. Only minor problem my partner had was with the air con as he doesn’t handle the heat well and didn’t find the air con cooled the bedroom enough but other than that he loved it as much as I did.
title: Private paradise

text:
Important note: 

Confirm exact location of airport pickup (information desk) on arrival as there are hundreds of pickups similtaneously.

Excellent free breakfast

Great complimentary afternoon cocktails

Fabulous location and spotless property 

Detail:

These are huge, comfortable villas in Seminyak which feel luxurious in every way. The Villas open to an expansive open living area. It is open in every way, being both large and connecting to the kitchenette, outdoor sun loungers and pool. The pool runs along the length of the villa and is a result, quite large for two people! The only downside to the pool (and loungers) is that there is a high wall around the narrow pool and so sun hours are limited for all Villas I imagine (we were villa 14). 

The bathroom and bedroom are both large and the beds are extremely comfortable. In saying this, Seminyak is quite noisy and so be prepared for some noise in the night. Villa 14 is near the road, but in spite of this noise, this was not a huge problem (we were woken up once or twice per night). 

The breakfast is fantastic and delivered to your villa promptly at your desired time every day. The service is excellent and all people were very welcoming. 

Finally, the location is great and near to loads of lovely restaurants including sisterfields and grocer and grind. Turning the other way out of the Villas (right) you can pass the lively bar, Motel Mexicana which is a 5 minute walk or the main Seminyak beach only 10 minutes walk away.

Overall, I would say this is a great luxury hotel, it just needs to work on the airport pickup (which was late) and noise (if possible).
title: Calming Villas in Crazy Seminyak

text: The villa was clean and spacious. Nice size pool with sun most of the day. Staff were excellent and courteous. Cleaned room everyday. Breakfast served at your convenience. Close to all amenities in Seminyak. Excellent security also. Excellent price also. Would recommend this to anyone. Thank you to all staff for there excellent service. Would stay again.
title: Excellent stay.

text: Stayed in one bedroom Villa number 14 - was fantastic, nice big pool and relaxing/living area. location was great access to shops, supplies and beach is a solid 10 minute walk - suggest going to Ku De Tah while near beach - it is a great beach club. Breakfast was always on time and kept me going to well after scheduled lunchtime. All the staff were great. I will be going back!
title: Oasis in an Oasis

text:
We had a great holiday in Bali. 
The Pradha Villas are very luxurious and the staff friendly and polite. 
Great location in the heart of Seminyak. Walking distance to the main shopping street and the beach. Lots of quality restaurants nearby. 
Highly recommend staying here.
title: Excellent family villa.

text:
Location was fantastic. 5 minute walk to Seminyak Square and to the famous Jalan Kayu Aya and 10 minute walk to Petitenget Beach. 

Lots of good cafes, restaurants and quaint shops within walking distance. 3 minute walk to sisterfields cafe and 6 minute walk to Revolver Espresso. Villa is beautiful and well kept. Staff are friendly and attentive. Always looked forward to the wide variety of well cooked breakfast choices, delivered to the villa.  

Bear in mind that the villa is a slightly more "open concept" especially for the showers and living area. Some form of insect life and ants can be expected. Heavy rains will require an umbrella to move from around from your room to the dining area.
title: Great villas in the heart of Seminyak

text: My family and I stayed for two nights at Pradha Villas. We stayed in a two bedroom suite with private pool. The design is contemporary and the location is ideally located next door to Motel Mexico (a popular restaurant and bar with music and dancing) and Body Works (a popular day spa). The staff is very friendly and the service is wonderful! The staff prepared a floating breakfast in our pool each morning and Dewa, one of the staff,  drove us in the villa's free shuttle to Potato Head Beach Club, which was one of our most favorite experiences during our trip. On our last day the front desk staff assisted us in arranging a massage with pick up from our villa and drop off to the airport. The best part about staying at Pradha Villas was the very hospitable and friendly staff! Thank you, Pradha staff, for your hospitality!
title: Friendly and Hospitable Service!

text: We loved everything about Pradha. The lovely staff, the peaceful haven from the busy Seminyak streets, just over the wall - the generous size rooms, large pool and lounge kitchen facilities (we really liked the open kitchen lounge by the way). Nice bed too. We had a two bedroom Villa (just the two of us, so one bedroom was unused). It was so tranquil. Very handy to everything - just a few minutes walk down to Petitenget Beach (and the fantastic Mano Beach House bar and restaurant), and a few minutes walk the other way to a huge choice of shopping, restaurants and bars around Seminyak. The only thing we would recommend - both our cab driver when we arrived, and our driver when we departed, had trouble finding Pradha. Better signage out on the Street would help. If you are looking for Pradha - find the Mexicola (very distinctive in JL Kyu Jati) - you are nearly there - small alley way runs down about 10 metres east of Mexicola (ie away from the beach). Great reasonably priced massage/manicure/pedicures too.
title: Oasis in busy Seminyak

text:
We stayed in the Luxury 1 Bedroom Pool Villa & everything about it was amazing,

Everything was so clean, comfortable  & the service of the staff was wonderful. The breakfast was amazing, they had a huge variety to choose from and all was delivered to your villa in the morning at a time of your choice.

We didn't have any trouble with bugs or mosquitos despite the living area not being enclosed. The staff would come and spray our room every night and we had no problems. The villas were quiet with little to no street noise or noise from other guests.

The location was perfect. It was just a short walk to the beach in one direction and Seminyak square in the other direction with so many great places to eat.

I would recommend Pradha Villas to everyone and would 100% stay there again next time i travel to Bali, it was amazing.
title: Amazing service & experience

text:
Wonderful accommodation in a great location which was away from the street noise but close enough to everything in Seminyak that we could walk everywhere that we needed to. Great restaurants were plentiful nearby along with excellent shopping, massage/spa options and the beach. Our villa was clean, absolutely private and secure. The service was faultless and super friendly - nothing too much trouble, including twice daily room cleaning / turn down service and lots of attention to the mosquitos / bugs which meant they were not a problem! Breakfast was generous with lots of options, room service was quick and yummy and the laundry service was affordable and prompt (within the day). The pool and spa were great and the setting was beautiful. The WIFI was free but a little unreliable - not uncommon for Bali though and good enough for us to check our emails, social media etc. each day which is all we really needed to do.
Overall we could not have asked for more and felt we received great value for our money - we have stayed in Bali several times before but this was our first stay at Pradha and we will certainly be choosing again for our next visit!
Highly recommend!
title: Loved everyhting about our stay at Pradha

text: Stayed at One bedroom luxury pool villa, which got hot water jacuzzi. Price was not too bad. Decent sized pool. Staffs are very professional, friendly and polite. They are so helpful. Location is ok. Walkable distance to Seminyak Square. Nearby restaurants make it bit noisy at night (not really bothering in bedroom). Overall, an excellent experience and is highly recommended.
title: Excellent stay and service

text: Loved Pradha villas and would definitely stay again, Great location, right in the heart of Seminyak, exceptional villa, bathroom and pool, all of generous size, friendly and efficient staff. can't find a fault. Wholeheartedly recommend the place.
title: Fantastic location, great accommodation, lovely staff

text:
We are currently staying at Pradha villas our second visit and it is excellent
The staff are very friendly and attentive nothing is to much trouble 
The villa is immaculate and the pool and gardens perfect 
The air conditioning is great and the bedroom comfortable and inviting
Out door bathroom that is a great experience
Close to eat street and beach 
We will be coming back over and over again 
Thank you Pradha Villas for making us feel so special
title: A piece of paradise in Seminyak

text: Staff are super friendly, location is central and villa is spacious and spotlessly clean. Extensive room service menu very reasonably priced, spa treatments also reasonable and they come to your villa. Laundry is also very reasonable, prompt and well done. We will definitely be coming back.
title: Fantastic location, staff and villa

text:
Quietly tucked away in central seminyak

5 mins to beach & main village square
Coffee houses excellent & conveniently located 
Recommend highly! But try for yourself - won't be disappointed!

text:
+

title: Amazing people and equally amazing villa

text: Quiet place to stay (villa #10).  Villa has big footprint - large open air lounge, dining and kitchenette.  Mozzies and other insects weren't much of a problem with coils and daily spraying by staff.  Private pool and spa were most welcome day and night.  Air conditioned bedroom in separate building with open air ensuited shower, large bath and toilet.  Scrumptious breakfasts brought to villa each day by pleasant staff.  Luxurious in-house massages.  In-house goods and services reasonably priced - eg beer at better than local shop rate.  Would certainly stay again here. However Seminyak much more expensive than Kuta - accommodation, dining, drinks, market goods.  Good cafes within walking distance with Australian-standard espressos.  Plenty of restaurants and boutiques within walking distance.  Seminyak Village and Seminyak Square a few minutes' stroll away.
title: Pradha Villas Seminyak

photos.caption: View from front door across lounge and dining
View from near front door into covered main area of villa
Open air dining room looking across to bedroom building and pool area
View of villa entrance from inside. Walk across fish pond.

text: One of the best stays we've had in Bali! Tucked down a laneway next door to motel mexicola this complex is just lovely. The staff could not have been friendlier or more helpful. Nothing was too much trouble- they even supplied a cake and came to the villa to sing happy birthday to my friend. The pool is quite big for a villa and the outdoor bathroom and tv/kitchen areas are also very roomy. The location is fantastic - across tbe road from bodyworks and sea circus and walking distance to la lucciola and kiln. There is also a shortcut halfway down the lane that brings you out near grocer & grind, so a much quicker route to seminyak square, sisterfields and eat street. Would definitely recommend!
title: Stunning Villas in a fantastic location!

text: We stayed in the 2 bedroom villa with private pool and jacuzzi. The villa was huge. It has all basic amenities. Do not worry about mosquitoes as they provide electronic mosquito incense in all of the rooms and the toilets and also mosquito repellent coil in the living and dining area. Breakfast are provided by the establishment and it had a wide variety of meals to choose from. There is also room service from massage to in-room dining. Very cheap indeed. The villa itself is very close to Seminyak Square and Seminyak Village just a walking distance. The staff were very helpful and friendly and cater to all of our needs.
title: Privacy and fun

text: The best location - walking distance to everything but still private and quiet. Huge villas with plenty of space, comfortable beds, lovely accomodating staff and plenty of in house services. The wifi isn’t super strong but not the end of the world!
title: Second time staying

text:
Pradhas villas are stunning, we stayed in the luxury one bedroom villa, layout was perfect and clean. Totally a different experience from staying in a hotel, although you do see lizards and bats in the living area sometimes, we never seen any insects etc in the bedroom ever. 

Location - i think this is the best area to stay in for couples, all the restaurants and beach is a few minutes walk, i highly recommend motel mexicola, potato head and ultimo restaurant. And also ubud day trip.

Weather - we went end of november and did experience alot of rain in the afternoons, and also 1 full day of rain... perfect time to get massages in your villa, a 90 min massage costs about £14 great value. 

Breakfast - you pick what you want the night before and is delivered to you at a time you want. They set your table up for you, breakfast is nice and plentiful.

Overall i think pradha villas was a perfect choice for us, i definitely recommend for people of all ages. I booked on there website direct, which was cheaper than all uk websites for the luxury villa, and they also give you free transfers if you book direct. They always email back straight away to any questions before you travel, customer service was excellent from the minute booked to the minute we left, workers are always helpful and smiling. Thank you pradha villas for an amazing experience and keep up the hard work.
title: Beautiful stay

text: From the moment we arrived till the time we checked out, all the staff were fantastic, pleasant and very helpful. Well positioned with in Seminyak the Villas are beautifully designed and well fitted out.
title: Bali family holiday

text: I stayed here for a week with my best mate, and it was absolutely terrific. We wanted to have a chilled out relaxing week in Bali, and Pradha Villas turned out to be the perfect choice. It is within walking distance to Seminyak square and all the busy parts of Seminyak, yet it is so peaceful and secluded. The Villas are very private and completely enclosed, I loved the layout, with the living area, kitchen and dining room being in the open (covered by just the roof). the Private pool was clean and bigger than I was expecting, However the highlight was definitely the jacuzzi, with I barely left for the whole week. The bedroom was fine, nothing special, and I loved the bathroom, there is a huge bath and a big shower, to my surprise there are two toilets. the kitchen has a fridge and a cooker if you'd like to cook your own food, and has everything you need to cook and present a meal. The staff were amazing, always ready to help and also extremely friendly. I loved that you order your breakfast the day before, and you pick which time you want to have it. They always Brough it to our room bang on time, they don't just hand it over, they bring it in, set the table and serve it. It was always delicious and there is a good variety. Everyday our villa was cleaned, and the pool was cleaned every few days. Honestly I cannot fault the staff in anyway, they even came to kill and remove a couple of bugs that found their way into our villa. One amazing touch was that everyday somebody would take the time to arrange fallen petals along the path that lead to all the villas, its the little things that make you appreciate the effort the staff went to, to make your stay memorable. We got a really good deal on Agoda, and I hope one day to return. I've run out of superlatives to describe this place and its staff.
title: Highly recommended!

text:
I stayed for 3 nights at Pradha Villas. Top notch service and lovely villas with private swimming pools.
All the staff were lovely. A nice touch of complimentary afternoon tea.
Walking distance to so many great restaurants and cafes in the heart of Seminyak. Also just a few minutes walk to Seminyak Village shopping mall for ATMs and air-conditioned shopping..
Highly recommended villas in Seminyak.
title: Awesome luxury private villas in Seminyak

text:
Chose Pradha Villa for my mini moon with my wife. 

First impression, all the staff were very friendly upon our check in. You’re able to choose a variety of breakfast daily and they will serve it to your villa every morning. 

We come back every night & the staff had already placed the mosquito coils at a few corner of the villa, very thoughtful! 

Location was great, walkable to the very chic Motel Mexicola restaurant & also Sisters field for brunch. Near to roadside but not noisy at night. Great pool for lounging as well! 

Overall, we would definitely return back if we were to visit Bali in the future!
title: Awesome stay

text: The villas are in the perfect location close to all the main shops and restaurants around Seminyak Square but private enough to feel like you’re out of the hustle and bustle. The rooms and pools are beautifully appointed - clean, luxurious, and private with great amenities. The staff are just beautiful and made us feel very welcome. We will definitely be back!
title: Amazing!

text:
Let me start with the positives, for Seminyak this is probably a good value proposition given the high prices of the hotels in the area.

Location of villa is ideal and set up with a pool, living area and two well appointed bedrooms is also good. Staff are super sweet and helpful.

The downside is however that the living area is outside and although they try make every effort to put insect coils out every day, the bug situation is a bit uncomfortable and it gets very hot in the living area. We found ourselves ‘hiding’ in our bedrooms half the time.

The bathrooms are also not the best, could do with an upgrade.
title: Good value for the area

text:
Brilliant location: easy walking distance to most of Seminyak's great bars, restaurants and shops.

We were part of a larger group staying at the Pradha Villas and were given a 2-room villa for a couple. The 2nd bedroom was locked during our stay but it really didn't bother us as we didn't need or use it. We stayed in villa 6 which is directly across from the shortcut that leads to the road towards the Seminyak shopping village. Although we heard the music from the street bars and restaurants when walking to our villa, we heard very little once we were inside.

The open plan layout of the lounge and kitchen area gives the villa a contemporary, open air feel and we really enjoyed it. The swimming pool was fantastic: private, clean and well maintained. The bedroom itself was a good size with clean linen and a great turndown service every night. This included setting up various mosquito coils, which really helped with the little critters. We found a couple of insects / crawlies in the open bathroom area, but this wasn't a biggie and we really enjoyed the open air shower and bathtub. One thing to note is that there does seem to be a lot of ants around so don't leave anything edible or sweet out for any period of time.

The staff was friendly and helpful. This started with the usual cold towels and refreshing welcoming drinks at arrival and extended to helping us organise a scooter for the day. They helped negotiate extended time in exchange for the full tank of petrol we ended up leaving in the scooter. 

Breakfast was reasonably good. There are a lot to choose from, but we found the poached eggs a bit vinegary so stuck to fruit, yummy banana pancakes, corn cakes (delicious!) and fried rice. Good Balinese coffee and fresh juices.

We will definitely stay there again.
title: Fantastic location, friendly staff

text:
Seminyak was our stop before heading to Uluwatu, we picked Pradha for its location and the price was really affordable too. Reviews were positive as well.

We arrived from Ubud and check in was pretty swift, we were then shown to our villa- we had Villa 14 which was right beside the little short cut to the main road. Villa was clean, very spacious. The bathroom was huge as well. We were welcomed with a cake in the villa. We loved the semi open living space with the sound of birds and the water from our pool. There were complimentary afternoon drinks which the staff will take your order through the phone and deliver to your villa. 

Staff will come to our villa for turn down service, they will set up the mosquito coils and spray some insect repellent in the bedroom which I did not like the overly fragrant smell. We requested the staff to not spray our bedroom the nights after. There were occasionally some lizards but it didn't bother us. Bedroom was comfortable but since our villa is next to the main road, we could hear live band/music from the surrounding eateries.

Breakfast order were taken the night before and delivered to us at our nominated time. It was good. Do keep an eye out for bird droppings, we had a few on the floor and dining chair. I loved soaking in the jacuzzi while reading my book and the privacy of our own pool. Location of the villa is great since it's a short stroll to the beach, motel mexicola, seminyak square. 

The receptionist, Aga was helpful to arrange our transportation to Uluwatu. Great thing was I found the book I've been wanting to read at the reception area!
title: Great location and very spacious villa

text: We stayed at Pradha for 2 nights. We liked the place (clean huge villas, jacuzzi, airy living room, huge kitchen, air con etc), the housekeeping staff was great but what we didn't like and hated the most was their attitude towards us. On the day of checkout we realised that our flight got cancelled. We went to the reception to help us make phone calls to the airline company. The hotel instead of helping us, kept on incessantly calling us on our villa phone asking us to vacate the room even before the checkout time. We have been to many hotels across the globe and every hotel allows you to stay for at least 30-40 mins even after your checkout time. But here, they went crazy and frantic and began this nonsense even before the checkout time. Finally, we had to give them a piece of our mind and made them understand the severity of the situation. They also charged us 3.5 USD for a 3 minute phone call to the airline company of which they didn't inform us before making the call. The free shuttle is also pointless as it doesn't run post 4pm which is when you would need it the most. The villa doesn't provide any bathroom slippers as most other villas in Bali do. The housekeeping staff is great but the girls at the reception lack empathy and care towards their guests. Never Again!
title: Big villas with tiny hearts

text: Cant deny this was one of my best experience staying at Pradha Villas. Starting from the privacy to comfort to breakfast cant deny any of the services. Amazing location and amazing welcoming staff. Must stay without any double thoughts.
title: Amazing Property

text:
Our accommodation at PradHa Villas was not a great experience. In fact, it wasn't a good experience, at a stretch I'd rate it poor. But it's important to note that the issues documented here, were raised with the management of the Villas at the time who acknowledged the problems and tried their best given the circumstances. 

We had a myriad of issues with this place and during our 11 night stay we moved through four different villas as the negotiated resolution to stop us from checking out and seeking a full refund. My original review of PradHa Villas turned out to be a long essay, so I think it's best summarised as follows:

• it's noisy due to neighbouring venue playing live music each night and construction works throughout the day
• significant underinvestment in the property's upkeep and general maintenance such as tiles loose in the pool, wooden panels needing painting or oil/varnish
• things not working as they should such as the air conditioner breaking or sink drainage or wifi connectivity 
• towels in the villas were well used, threadbare, stained and five years past their used by date.

This place has the potential to be great but just needs a seriously good make-over. In the 12 visits made to Bali and staying in various hotels, my advice would be to book with caution. There are better alternatives than PradHa Villas.
title: Renovation Rescue

text: These villas located in Seminyak are great. The swimming pool is excellent and the open living room is really awesome. The bubble bath is a bit too small to sit in though, and the interior of the villas is a tad worn. That said, I really recommend these villas because they give you the feeling you are in an oasis. Though the lock on the front door is not really secure, the security officer guards the villas really well.
title: This villa is a great location from where to explore south Bali

text:
This was my third visit to Bali so my accommodation search revolved mainly around the Seminyak Square area as we wanted to be positioned within an easy walk to the many restaurants/bars, the great coffee shops (Sisterfields, Grocer & Grind, Revolver Espresso, Corner House, +many others), the shops along Jl Kayu Aya, massage places, sunset drinks along beach, and avoiding the need for many taxis.  

Pradha Villa met all our requirements plus a whole lot more.  From the get go, the staff at Pradha answered all our direct email queries promptly and made us feel relaxed about our choice of accommodation prior to arriving.

On our eventual arrival we were greeted with refreshing drinks and were provided with a tour of our 2-bedroom garden/pool villa.  Everything was explained, such as the breakfast in-villa choices; security detail; procedure to contact staff; shortcut to main street; etc.  The villa was extremely clean and we were amazed at the lengths the housekeeping staff went to change our linen each day of our 5-day stay, spraying & lighting discreetly positioned mosquito coils in our alfresco living areas and indoor/outdoor bathrooms.

My friend and I felt very safe at all times and experienced no issues whatsoever.  Any time we had a query, or needed anything, our request was dealt with professionally and an answer was forthcoming at the promised time.

A driver was available each day to take guests to various locations, but we ended up walking to many of our destinations.

We enjoyed our friendly chats with many of the staff and will always be grateful for their offers of assistance, even after leaving Pradha.  

We really felt sad when saying goodbye. Thank you to Eka, the entire reception team, our chefs, housekeeping and the airport drivers for being so patient on our flight arrival delay.  

The things I liked least ... not warm enough to use the pool and jacuzzi and perhaps, like many things in Bali, it's time to address the weathered timber window frames and decking.  In raising that, by no means did it affect our happy stay at Pradha.
title: Superb, peaceful location with Genuine Hospitality ++

text:
We recently stayed 4 nights.  Great sevice from staff. My husband got sick last day of our stay and they helped me find the pharmacy, gave me ride to pharmacy to get medicine. Thanks Putri and 
Dewa for your help.  Breakfast was good. Location is great. Close to beach and all the restaurants. 
We liked our villa. Very spacious, huge swimming pool. We Didn't use kitchen . There were mosquitoes. But  with mosquito coils and mosquito net it was ok.
title: Spacious villas.

text: Brilliantly located villas just minutes walk to the beach, shops, cafes and everything great about Seminyak. My wife and I stayed 9 nights in Sept 2014 in a one bedroom luxury villa. It had everything you need for perfect relaxation. Outdoor living by day around your own sunny pool, a cool and secure bedroom by night without any irritation from bugs and extremely kind staff. We could not fault Pradha. They provide a great breakfast each day, modern airport transfers, a quality selection of in room dining, very affordable in room spa treatments. Pradha has everything you need. If you come away with complaints you have spent too much of your holiday looking for faults. Get to Pradha, relax, explore Seminyak and enjoy yourselves.
title: Perfect Seminyak Haven

text: My family and I are staying at pradha villas at present in a 2 bedroom pool villa . The location is perfect short walk to the cafés shops restaurants and everything that seminyak has to offer The beach is 5 minutes walk . The villas are spotlessly clean the staff super friendly and helpful nothing was too much trouble for them The breakfast is more than adequate brought to your room and the eggs cooked perfectly in your room. If you want more elaborate breakfasts which are so popular in Australia great cafés are 2 minutes walk with excellent coffee. The rooms are large the pool is sunny and some 9 metres long , bathrooms are also large each with a spa and rainmaker showers. The decor is a little dated and may not be as impressive as some nearby more modern villas but the price of the villas reflects this. As I said before very clean great comfortable beds, what more could you want
title: No issues

text:
My husband & I booked a 1 bedroom pool villa for 1 week. We have stayed at the Pradha Villas several times previously & had enjoyed our experience. Given this trip is the last trip we will go on before our first child is born, we were very much looking forward to relaxing by the pool in the sunshine.
We arrived & checked into our villa, only to find that we had been downgraded from our original booking. Far from the 1 bedroom pool Villa we had been expecting with full sunshine all day, we were so disappointed that our 1 bedroom 'luxury' villa had a small lap pool beside a wall which saw the sun from early to mid morning only.
We discussed our dissatisfaction with management & the only solution offered was to move us into the villa we had originally for 3 of the 7 nights we had booked mid stay & then move us again back to our 'luxury' villa. Not content with this option, we contacted the booking agency we had originally booked through and they offered us a full refund to compensate us for the disparity between the description of what we had booked and what we had received.
Most disappointing however, was when a staff member from Pradha Villa told the booking agency that the only reason there was no sun in our villa was that it was a very cloudy day. This was a blatant lie as the sky was blue and sunny! 
10/10 to the booking agency for their excellent customer service and 0/10 to Pradha for false advertising and deception.
Book with caution! We will not be staying here again
title: Deceptive & disappointing

text: Great location in the heart of Seminyak.  Slightly dated villas but still very comfortable.  Beautiful large pool.  What makes this place really stand out is the service! The staff get it! They are so hospitable & polite, they made us feel at home.  Well done guys!
title: Location & staff

text:
Our fourth visit to Bali and by no coincidence our third stay at Prahda Villas.
 
The Villas are fantastic with all of them looking as great as the photos.

What makes Prahda Villas so special to us are the Staff.

From accommodating a sudden change in our booking dates to a most welcome upgrade to 'our' luxury villa #12.
Our friends were upgraded too, we are ecstatic that their first trip to Bali and for one, first trip overseas has been made extra special by the Fantastic Staff here at Prahda Villas.

The Villas are in a prime Seminyak Location easy access to the beach (5 min max.) and the same to Seminyak square.
title: Excellent Once Again

text:
Spent four nights at a one bedroom villa and truly enjoyed it. The staff was excellent and super friendly, arranging transport, laundry, spa services, food and beverages at any time.

The villa itself was beautifully appointed, somewhat Indonesian plus modern chic. The living area plus pool and sunloungers were great for hanging out during the day. The bedroom was the only airconditioned area in the villa, which for us was sufficient. Bedroom and bathroom are large and truly wonderful.
It can be a bit noisy as the street is right behind the hotel and locals like to honk a lot, but it was a minor disturbance.

All in all, for these prices you get a wonderful private villa with great services for total relaxation. I would stay again.
title: Great place close to the best of Seminyak

text: We returned to Pradha and continue to be impressed with the friendliness and helpfulness of staff, comfort and cleanliness of the accommodation and the excellent location. Pradha is walking distance from some fantastic eateries, 5 minutes to the beach and Seminyak Square. Thanks again to the wonderful staff. D and G.
title: Another great stay

text:
Personally, we do enjoyed our stay there. It is our first time villa with pool experience. Enjoyed the pool most, and the tranquility of the place. Yet it was very accessible to Seminyak Square and the many eateries outside.  Except that felt the villa was not very well maintained which I felt it was a pity. its a villa with lots of potential I believe if it had been better maintained. Generally the towels seemed tired, not exactly the whitest condition. Was bit greyish with some stains. Did not use them in the end. So its still advisable to bring your own travel towels if possible. 

Breakfast is done in house, with the option of done at kitchen and then served at your villa too. Not too impressed with the selection, felt bit restrictive and limited choices. 

But I do appreciate the "holding/resting" room resort has for you after checkout.
title: Good location

text:
I picked Pradha Villas because of the excellent reviews. Was not dissapointed and actually far above my expectation. Well done Pradha Villas. From pick up from the airport to checkin all staff could not have been more helpful.
. We travel a lot and are very over small hotel rooms this was perfect. Breakfast was amazing, my husband was very impressed having ordered soft boiled eggs and poached over the 4 breakfasts , and they were delivered to perfection. We had room service 1 night also excellent food. 
A very nice touch at dusk the staff came lit mosquito coils for living area , turned down the bed and closed the bedroom doors and sprayed for bugs, so effective.
If we visit Seminyak again will revisit and will also recommend to our friends.
title: Pradha villas seminyak

text: I have been to bali many times and stayed in all kinds of accommodation. This time I was hoping for a lovely relaxing holiday at pradha villas with my friend and that's exactly what we got. We stayed in a 2 bedroom villa and it was really, really spacious. The pool is bigger than any I've seen at a hotel villa. It was so quiet, hard to believe it was smack bang in the middle of seminyak. The beds were awesomely comfortable with fabulous aircon and great ensuite bathrooms. I've read some reviews from tripadvisor which note the villas are old ... Yes, they are not brand new and sparkling, but personally I think it adds to the charm. They were certainly very clean. The breakfasts were perfectly adequate with generous serves and a reasonable selection. The staff were just lovely,. Putu and Dewa were standouts, very charming. The only negative is that our plane was delayed to 1am and I was charged well over a half days rate to stay to 10pm and that was with with one bedroom locked. A little disappointing. And I don't like slippery cushion covers in the lounge :) but overall a lovely experience.
title: A lovely experience

text:
Our villa is for four of us, and it is an amazing stay for us during the 4days of stay.

There is a private pool (although the filtration system is not great, but the water is still considered clean). Whenever we come back after a long day, the villa would be cleaned and tidied already, and we could just get changed and hop into the pool and chat till late night, with the tv turned on (the channels are like the usual Starhub channels). No one would stop you from using the pool because it's part of your villa.

Breakfast would be served the next time at the time you favour. Just get to the lobby and choose the variety of breakfast available. You can choose for them to cook on the spot in your villa's kitchen, or already prepared in their own kitchen then served to your villa. (The English breakfast is the most filling selection.)

The rooms are beautiful, and there's side door that is directly in front the pool.
The master bedroom needs about 8 steps of non-sheltered walk from the living room. Master bedroom is beautiful, there's a tv in there too. The bathroom is just slightly smaller than the rooms. It is an outdoor bathroom, so my friend and I, both females are afraid that someone from somewhere might just be peeping at us. But it wasn't so bad. Wardrobe were also at the outdoor bathroom, tgt with the safe. And I really wonder why. Because the door linked from the bedroom to the bathroom has only one lock, and it's from the bedroom side. (The bathroom can't be lock from the inside.)

From my friend, the villa is $70/person/night, which is reasonable, the location is walkable from Seminyak Square, but still slightly far. If you reach before 11pm, the backdoor would be open, then it's not so bad. (Just that you'll have a hard time recognising the backdoor.

Staff were all smiley and friendly. Even the security guard. There's this lounge with (door-less) bathroom sofa and tv for us, after the check out time, while waiting for our flight back at night.

Just head over to the counter for any enquiries during your stay! <;
title: It's all yours.

text:
I booked directly with the villa and enjoyed the free airport transfer they provide to guests. We stayed a few days at Nusa Dua and arranged for the the pick up from our hotel in Nusa Dua. 

When driving there, I thought the location was inaccessible.. until we walked out on our own we realised it's really convenient. Beach 10 min walk away, massage/spa just outside villa, food a corner or two away, bike rental along the stretch of the villa. Great location!

Everyone there are very friendly and helpful.. and was even given a little perk which I shall not go into detail as I wouldn't want to "spoil market" and make their lives difficult from now on. 

Looks slightly tired (just a little for a 6 year old property), but we were really happy with almost everything at Pradha Villa. The chef came into our villa to prepare our breakfast in the morning, nice size private pool, jacuzzi (I didn't use much of it), and I love their outdoor shower. 
The only thing bad was the dirty bathtub so we didn't use it (a pity).

Mosquitoes normally like me very much, but I didn't get one bite. Thumbs up!
title: Villa #9. Felt at home.

text:
We have again returned to the Prahda villa in Seminyak our third stay. The reasons that we continue to use this property is first, the location. Great area within walking distance to a great selection of restaurants and only 10 minutes from the beach. Second the quality of the villas, all with a great sized sunny pool. Third the staff, great service, I would like to mention Yuni who was once a butler and now is a receptionist she helped us when we had problems with the internet and in general gave us really good service. One day Yuni will be a manager!  I have only praised one member of staff but all the staff did a great job. They work well as a team ensuring you get the most out of your stay. The anti mozzie protection that the staff do here is exceptional, in our three visits neither myself or wife have been bitten! 
On leaving the Prahda we again booked for October.
title: Great location

text:
We had a wonderful stay at a one bedroom private villa with private pool.  The villa is huge, lots of space, well equipped and nice design with direct access to a very generously sized private pool. 

The villa needs some upgrades as it can feel a bit tired and in need of some renovations, but the exclusive private feel and big pool makes up for this.

The location is amazing right in the heart of Seminyak, can walk to all the nice and trendy restaurants, and spas.

We can only recommend this great property.
title: Chic and private villa

text:
this time i gave up booking through agoda or booking.com but directly with villa as i would like to enjoy the free airport pick up service.

as my cousin and i took a budget flight (tiger) from hk to bali, we arrived at the airport quite early at about 7am (earlier than expected time~), but the driver came a bit late to pick us up maybe due to misunderstanding, we did feel a bit nervous when we were waiting for the driver, lucky that he really showed up at last, he was nice and did apologize so we soon forgave about this minor issue.

all the staff of the villas i met are nice, they even allowed us to checkin in the morning, my cousin was very happy with this arrangement as she reminded me for thousands times that she needed a good sleep after the 5-hr flight!!! 

do prepare enough anti-mosquitoes stuff if u attract insects a lot! i did meet 2 cockroaches and many ants in the washroom@@" a staff did leave us a can of spray to kill the insects, but i nearly killed myself too as i forgot to open the door when i used the spray*_* i also met birds, frogs, reptiles and even a cat in our own villa! u can fully enjoy your holiday with the accompany of different types of animals, ha!

the private swimming pool is clean, the bedroom is clean too with enough cooling as the air con is quite efficient. strong free wifi signal everywhere in villa is very gd!

tv channels are adequate i think, 1 tv is installed in bedroom, there are 2 fridges too, 1 in bedroom and the other one in private kitchen. oh yea, you can request the chef to cook the breakfast in your favourite style in your own villa. 

this villa is great in location, very close to seminyak square and some shopping streets, also close to the beach and do spend an afternoon in a pub located just next to the beach to wait for the sunset~ 

the villa also provides free shuttle bus to send you to kuta, a busier area than seminyak, but the water quality of the beach there is not that attractive compared to the seminyak beach though kuta beach seems to be more popular.

All and all, i feel happy and want to praise myself that i have chosen to stay in Pradha Villas for my 1st Bali visit after spending many nights to read different websites and justify the comments from different travellers. With such a reasonable price and i nearly have no negative feelings here, i will definitely recommend you to give yourself a chance to spend a few days and relax here.

p.s. to all the staff that have served my cousin and me before, sorry that i couldnt leave my comment here earlier since i am very busy to start working again once i went back to hk -_-" and guess what? i'm still in office to type this comment,that's why my comment here is not quite organized :p
title: Wonderful stay in Pradha Villas

title: Holiday in Pradha Villas

text: We stayed in the Pradha Villa's over the Jan New Year although we had some terrible days with rain the staff were always there to help provide umbrella's etc. This was our first stay in Bali for over 20 years and first time in a Villa style accommodation. The Villa's were great perfect for our family of four. Our selection with Pradha came from TA some say they are old and tired, however I wouldn't say old and tired maybe a little bit of paint but really nothing to dampen your holidays. The staff were fantastic in assisting you with anything that you required from Doctors to telling other Patrons to be quite which this did happen to us on two occasions but Security sorted this out and we enjoyed the rest of our trip. I enjoyed the easy walk to shops and close to some good restaurants. A much enjoyed holiday. Thank you to all the staff at Pradha Villa your smile and friendly nature made the holiday enjoyable and will be back hopefully my husband will not need a doctor the second time around :-)
title: Friendly Staff and great location

text: Pradha has provided great service. The weather was really bad during our stay in bali but the helpful and friendly staff have made our honeymoon nothing short of perfect. Thanks Pradha. We had a great time.
title: Wonderful honeymoon
partner_attribution: Ulasan dikumpulkan dalam kemitraan dengan hotel ini

text: We stayed for 7 nights last week and couldn't have been happier. We booked Pradha based on TA reviews and were not at all disappointed. The villa was well designed and a great place to just hang out in.....very very comfortable bed. great pool and lots of spots to relax.  The staff are amazingly friendly and come to your villa (at whatever time you choose) to make you breakfast daily. They're always on hand with an umbrella if you get a wet season downpour. Great location between the beach and the restaurant strip. We couldn't fault it.
title: Great place to chill out in Seminyak

title: Great villa, wonderful staff

text:
Villa: 7
Length of stay: 3 night / 4 days (Nov 16-19)
Family size: 5 (3 young children)

I've been to Bali more times than I can count and have stayed in numerous hotels and villas from Kuta to Ubud. Truth be told this villa has the potential to be great, the staff we're beyond fantastic, the centralized location was perfect, overall size of the villa and pool was superb and I love how I can park my car near the villa and not worry about having to walk so far from the reception / parking area like other villas (this was especially useful as on this trip we had our 6month old with stroller and baby gear in tow) but there was a few things which was very disappointing. 

During our stay we had an opportunity to have a peek inside the one bedroom villas and it was vastly updated versus our two bedroom - I didn’t quite understand why the two bedrooms felt so worn down when their one bedroom was beautiful, it suddenly felt like we we're staying in Pradhas substandard villa. This was my own personal view and perhaps someone else may not feel the same way, but I feel that if you’re going to maintain your property, perhaps its best practice to keep everything uniformed rather than "what you don’t know won’t hurt you" mentality. 

Now the nightmare started on our second and third night - it rained on both nights but fortunately we we're out around town, on the way back we talked about how we'd all have a swim at night. To our shock the villa was swarmed with hundreds if not thousands of flying ants which crawled out of the wood works because of the rain, there was wings everywhere, the wingless flying ants crawling all over the villa floor mating and a few dozen bats flying attracted by the free meal way flying in and around the open space of the villa. Needless to say the we all ran into our rooms and waited for the staff to show up to help clean up the mess. 

After the cleaning was done I spoke to the staff (I do speak the local language) and he informed me that this is a normal thing to happen and is expected? I'm a bit surprised to hear this because at this magnitude its more of a problem rather than an inconvenience (pest control anybody?) once the cleaning was finished we wanted to take a dip in the pool but unfortunately because it was dark and drizzling the pool was filled with these flying ants and had to skip our evening dip. Even though the gentleman did his best to clean up the villa you can’t help see dozen of these flying ants (bodies, wings etc) still scattered EVERYWHERE, we were also advised to keep the lights off in the Villa so that they don’t come back. So in the end we spent the night inside our rooms doors closed not able to enjoy the pool or the living area, it felt like we stayed in a hotel rather than a villa. 

In the morning we got up to have our in villa breakfast cooked and while sitting down saw one of the servers / chefs pick up two dead bats and throw them in the bin before going back to serving our food - obviously the family was turned off from eating as the gentleman clearly didn’t even wash his hands between picking up the carcass of the bats and serving us our scrambled eggs *yuck* 

For some this may seem like a minor inconvenience but at the price you pay and the vast amount of options available in Bali this villa dropped from a 5 star to a 2.5 at best. Don’t get me wrong overall the location is great and the staff generally superb but I'm surprised the management have let the state of the villa and infestation build up to this level and not have acted on it. My only real regret is that in the commotion of getting the baby in the room to avoid the flying ants and bats along with the cleanup I didn’t get the chance to take a picture of the villa in its ridiculous state. Would I stay there again - nope and sadly can’t find it in me to even refer friends and family to stay there cause I wouldn’t want anybody going through what we went through, oh well on to the next villa.
title: Great villa but could have been better

text:
My family (myself, husband, two teenage girls 14 and 16) stayed here in a 2 bedroom villa for a week in late September this year.  PradHa villas are indeed very well located being walking distance to almost everything that matters in Seminyak.  They are set back in a laneway so that they are well away from the hustle and bustle of the main streets.  They are about 5 minutes' walk to Seminyak Square and to Seminyak beach,  a minute or so's walk from Grocer and Grind (a good cafe for breakfast and lunch - they do serve dinners but I didn't think much of them for dinner), about 10 minutes' walk to' Eat Street' (Oberoi) and 10 minutes' walk to the main part of the street called Pettingret where there are also some good eateries -  Potatoe Head (very upbeat: teenagers will love it) being probably  the most well known on that street, although our teenagers also liked The Deck.  Gourmet Cafe further up  Pettingret is about 15 minutes' walk from the villas but the walk is worth it as it is a really good cafe. The villa is within 5-10 mins' walk from La Lucciola restaurant (very good), and about 15-20 mins' walk to Ku Te Da (lovely) - both of which, like Potatoe Head, have excellent beach aspects. There is a very good hairdresser/treatment place just 2 minutes' walk from the villas walking towards Grocer and Grind,  and 'Cool Spa'  (also just near Grocer and Grind walking towards Seminyak Square)  too is also very good indeed and reasonably priced.

Anyway, I digress a little.  So, Back to the villas  - first the plusses:

 The villas were pretty comfortable and the pool, which both bedrooms immediately look onto was warm, larger than I expected and a lovely treat after the heat of the Bali day.  
The lounge/dining area was spacious with a large overhead fan and there was a quite modern kitchen with a fridge and hob, and filtered (but not chilled) water, but no microwave.   
The bedrooms were airconditioned and this worked well, and the beds were comfortable and the two ensuite bathrooms were large both with showers and baths and the main bedroom had an outdoor shower which was nice. Both bedrooms had TVs and DVDs and there was a TV in the dining room area too.
 Many people have complained on this site about the breakfasts (which for us were included in the price), but I thought they were overall pretty good especially the Nasi Goreng and Mi Goreng and the banana pancakes were delicious - although it is true that after a few days, the lack of variety did start to become very noticeable. I had assumed the breakfasts were cooked in your villa, but this did not occur, and the breakfasts were brought to you on platters at the time you requested the day before from a menu. You could even have breakfast at different times according to the needs of your family - so one day, my husband and kids ate very early, but I had my breakfast two hours' later - this flexibility was most appreciated. However, I could not understand why they never left us a menu to select breakfast for the next day in our villa or even when they brought the breakfast - we always had to ask reception for the  menu to select from. 
The staff at the villas were pleasant, helpful and courteous almost all the time and helped us book tours. We were also able to book a driver for a couple of days  when we wanted to explore the surrounding areas (we went to Sanur one day, and to the Bali Safari and Marine Park (excellent) another day - our driver was Noman, the uncle of Butu who works at the villas, and he was exceptionally friendly and efficient and reasonably priced and I recommend you ask for him. 
The in-room dining option was also  very good - we had some friends over for dinner one night and had the villas cater a three course meal for us from a wide menu, and it was well priced and the good was mostly good.
 I used the in-house treatment service the villas can arrange for you offer and had manicure in my villa which was reasonably priced at about $10 for 45 minutes and the lady who came  was pleasant and did a good manicure.

The main reason I am not giving the villas a "very good" rating (I don't care for the "average" tag Tripadvisor uses, preferring to rate this villa as "good")  is because of the minusses for the villas overall, which meant that I feel the villas are overpriced compared to other villas available  for the same price in Seminyak which are more modern and upmarket and offer more in the way of inclusions (for example no massages were included in the price we paid, although other similar quality villas in similar areas in Seminyak did include these). 

 The minusses are as follows:

The villa we stayed in was definitely showing signs of age all around.  
The drawers in the main bathroom smelt really musty and moldy upon opening them and this smell never went away the time we were there. 
The furniture in the bathroom and around the villa generally was starting to look chipped and worn in many places.  
The floor in the lounge/dining area seemed to me to have a lot of stains/dirty marks on it.   There was ash on the floor when we arrived that was never cleaned away. 
 I felt the decor of the villas generally was rather dark and rather dated, and the lighting arrangements
were mostly pretty poor so that at night there did not seem to be enough good light to read by. This was particularly true in the bathrooms in the evening where one could hardly see enough to put on makeup the lighting was so inadequate. 
The housekeeping was not particularly efficient or practical:  I originally, and repeatedly, asked for extra bath towels as they only provided one bath towel per person, and each day, the housekeepers would take away all the bath towels and only give us one each again.  We originally were given one hand towel and one facewasher each, but after day one, the housekeepers gave us only one hand and facewasher between two of us.  There was never a handtowel provided for the third toilet and I had to ask them twice to put toilet paper in that toilet when it ran out as they did not seem to check this. There was no handtowel provided for the kitchen area either, and so I had to use the one from the bathroom.  
The toilet in the main bathroom was rather inefficient, requiring several flushes, and on two days, the toilet and bath in the main bathroom did not seem as if they had been cleaned properly by the housekeeping.
 One of the lights in the main bathroom broke, and I reported it, but it was never fixed.
 The shower in the main bathroom often dripped constantly. 
The wooden planks under the shower in the main bathroom where the water drained away were a little uneven and wobbled a bit. 
The option of providing filtered water through a machine in the kitchen and which was not chilled and was in fact often quite warm, rather than supplying bottled water each day,  wasn't very practical. We regularly had to ensure we had empty bottles of water available to fill up with the filtered water and chill in the fridge overnight. Not particularly helpful if you wanted a cold drink quickly.  
The mosquito protection provided in the bedrooms/lounge area did not work well at night and we were all bitten. There were no mosquito nets on the beds and given that the main ensuite  bathroom was partly open air, this meant that mozzies came into the adjoining bedroom at night a lot.
 We were annoyed that the transport we paid for which the villas has arranged to pick us up from Nusa Dua to bring us to Pradha Villas ended up being a very small car indeed and three of us were cramped in the back seat most uncomfortably on a long 1.5 hour trip in terrible traffic. Since we found out during our stay that the villas have some much more comfortable and bigger vehicles available, we are unsure why this very small car was provided to pick us up as it was not a pleasant journey.

Overall I do not think the 2 bedroom villa we stayed in was value for money because of the shortcomings mentioned above.  They may seem relatively minor, but these villas are not cheap and I think there is better quality around for the price.  

 I think that there are more modern/newer 1bedroom villas available at PradHa villas, but I think the 2 bedroom villa we stayed in (villa 8) was quite dated and older than the 1 bedroom ones ( I poked my head quickly into a 1 bed villa while I was there when it was being cleaned and it did seem smarter and newer than ours).  The two bedroom villa we were in was clearly in need of maintenance and an overall update. Once this is done I think these villas will represent much better value for money. They are comfortable and pleasant villas to stay in, but we felt they are somewhat overpriced.

By way of a side tip - avoid flying Virgin to Bali. We flew from Melbourne to Bali and back with Virgin and thought they were terrible, extremely disorganised and clearly trying to save money on quality service for the passengers.  They use very small  planes so you felt cramped the whole flight. There were only two toilets being available for over 160 people. so the queues were ridiculous (there was another toilet at the front of the plane but it was reserved for business class passengers).  There were long waits to check in both at Melbourne and in Denpasur airports and the check in staff seemed to be inexperienced.  In addition I would ask WHY Virgin  asks passengers to check in at least 3 hours' before the flight but does not have check in staff available at Denpasur until 2 hours and 50 minutes before the flight leaves????.  There were  no snacks available for purchase on the flights:  "sorry Ma'am, it's a fully catered flight" was the reply when I asked -  so if you didn't like either of the meal options, bad luck -  you went hungry (and they ran out of the vegetarian meal option early on so if you do go Virgin you might want to consider bringing your own food!!). The inflight wireless entertainment did not work on the flight to Bali and there was no apology and no entertainment tablets to purchase so it was a long, boring flight. Worse, we sat on the tarmac in Melbourne  for an hour while they took some people's luggage off whose passports were not in order (begs the question: who checked these people in for the flight in the first place Virgin?) and there were no drinks offered while we waited. Not impressed at all.

text:
The Villa was nice and I've no real issues at all. 

It had a few tired and worn marks around the place but nothing to be concerned with.

Again though no fault of the hotel, we had inconsiderate English neighbours again.  I thought going to the other side of the world we might have avoided them.  

I hope to god they read this. 

When on a relaxing holiday the last thing people want to hear is your uncontrolled kids screaming like hyenas all the time. Please try to express some discipline and control over them.  I'm not convinced they weren't left alone. 

The staff were all great.  Really lovely, cheery and helpful people. I include every single one I meet on our stay. 

Breakfast was basic but fine. It was brought to the villa at the time requested.  

We were offered no free rides like the previous reviews. We requested a taxi back to the airport and although they had their car on the drive, they did just reserve us a taxi we paid for. Driving is scary in Bali. Awful beyond words. 

I believe they only give you a free ride when you book direct. We paid 7.7M Rupiah for our 3 night stay in September through booking.com

The location is a little more than 5mins from the main street of Seminyak and the beach.  Both require you to walk on already over congested and dangerous roads. Even if you survive the walk, your ears will be burned off by honking horns of taxi drivers harrassing for a fayre. 

Don't consider this if you are not fit and able. 

A lot of people seem to love Bali, but I'm not one. 

If you have to go to Bali, Pradha Villas is a good choice.  

If you plan to leave the Villa during your holiday, I wouldn't consider Bali.
title: Nice Villa if, and only if, you need to go to Bali

text: Our review Dec 2012 covered a previous stay and gives details of the villas which are still the same high standard. This trip we were in Bali for a family celebration with activities centred around Seminyak for 5 days. The first part of our trip was beachside so we didn't need to be right at the sand, preferring the peace and tranquillity that Pradha provides, while being a 5 minute walk to the beach one way or 5 mins to shops and restaurants in the other direction. Staff are very helpful and meet requests promptly, room is serviced daily to a very good standard, and free airport transfers as well as the free one way Kuta shuttle work efficiently. title: One of the Best

text:
We spent 4 nights (wish it was longer) at the Pradha Villas with our 2 small children (4 & 18mth) and it couldn't have been better, beautiful spacious 2 bedroom villa with a large pool and very friendly & accommodating staff.
A pool net was put up for our children's safety and all the staff were so great with our 2 boys. The bedrooms are quite separate from each other, so if concerned about being separated from kids take a baby monitor or as we ended up doing 1 parent in each room.

title: Fabulous location surrounded by great restaurants, bars & shopping.... yet very tranquil.

text:
Returned from 10 wonderful days staying in a very comfortable two bedroom villa.  Great for families or couples sharing.
Staff: wonderful staff, very helpful and friendly 
Bedroom 1: (air-conditioned) comfortable king bed, flat screen TV &  huge bathroom (semi outdoors)
Bedroom 2: as above
Kitchen/living: indoor/out door area with spacious kitchen, gas cook top, large fridge, comfortable couches & ceiling fan (no air-conditioning)
Outdoor area: lovely private pool, garden area & sun lounges (two)
Location (walking distances): quiet convenient location, 5 minutes to beach, 5 minutes to Seminyak square & restaurants
Breakfasts: yum, lots of variety - huge breakfasts
title: Fabulous!

text:
This was my first trip to Indonesia and Bali. I couldn’t of been happier with the villas,  it was the perfect place to meet with my cousins who live in Oz. 

Location: 
Perfectly located only a few hundred meters walk from the beach, Shops, Seminyak Square & Eat Street. We couldn’t have asked for a more perfect location. We also hired a driver for a couple of days of our stay so that we could see as much of the island as possible, I would really recommend doing this. (This cost us approximately £30 per day, booked via Pradha Villas) 

Villas: 
Although the Villa wasn’t brand new it was modern, spacious, clean and perfectly laid out. The private pool was lovely, the Wifi worked adequately, and the beds were comfortable. The his n hers sinks and outside showers were a great touch. The 2 bedroom villa was perfectly adequate for the 4 of us, my only complaint is that we only had 2 sunbeds by our pool not 4. The kitchen was well equipped with cooker, water cooler, fridge and freezer (perfect for keeping our Ben & Jerrys!) so great if you didn’t want to eat out. (Thoughwith so much on offer in Bali why wouldn’t you!) I especially liked the incense that was lit at night for us to keep the bugs away.  

Breakfast: 
breakfast is delivered to your villa every morning, I wish this happened everywhere I stayed! We had our villa for 5 nights and breakfast was getting a little repetitive, but it did mean we got to sample everything, my favourite was the banana pancakes, freshly squeezed juices and the fruit platters…Delicious. 

Service: The staff were always friendly, helpful  and approachable during our whole stay. Though make sure you are ready to leave for 12 as they are very strict with the 12noon check out, they are very efficient and come in to turn over the rooms as soon as they can for the next guests. 

Thank you Pradha Villas for an amazing first trip to Bali. Go, you won’t regret a moment of it.
title: Location Location Location

text: We stayed at Pradha on the recommendation of another couple who come here at least once a year, they had their own villa here with us.  I had looked at several other villas in Seminyak and tried hard to persuade them to go somewhere with Yoga included.  Thankfully they resisted, we stayed in these lovely villas and had a yoga teacher come to us for private lessons instead!  I wouldn't choose anywhere else it is so convenient for shops, food, beach and the villas are the perfect size to allow you to hang out without having to be in the bedroom.  There is a beauty spa right next to the side entry, which was perfect for mani/pedi several times in 10 days.  We will be back to Pradha again.
title: Perfect location

text: We booked for a villa with 2 bedrooms - the villa is huge, comfortable and clean.However, the air conditional in the master bedroom not working properly(time to service it)and the floor in the master bathroom were sticky.We did mention it to the reception when we check out so hopefully they can do something about it.The other room was perfect! Choosing Pradha Villas for my familly vacation in Bali was the most incredible moments for us, Imagine you are stuck in traffic jam & unhappy somewhere outside a town.

title: Mega Incredibleeee !!

text:
Wow where to begin! We stayed at Pradha from 8th - 17th 2013 June for our wedding. We had 3 villas booked and i can not fault this place at all!

Starting with our Airport pickup to being welcomed with a refreshing strawberry drink to then walking into the amazing villa, thinking wow, let my holiday begin! We shared some amazing experiences during our trip- our wedding, honeymoon and our family on their visit to Bali.

All the staff were just amazing and ever so kind, each time passing reception, it was a big hello, smile and a wave!! (we walked past reception many times a day, so there was lots!!)

A big thank you to the staff for helping to make our wedding day ever so memorable. This was the first wedding that Pradha had hosted (we got married in Villa 3, but our family had villa 2 and 5). From helping with all the contractors we had setting up the villa on the day to a beautiful love heart rose petal display on the bed, bath filled with roses and rose petals scattered in the bathroom- JUST AMAZING!!

Pradha and their staff each and every day went above and beyond in their assistance of their guests. Breakfast each morning as they quietly potter around in the kitchen to set up breakfast (while we were swimming) to the afternoon turn town service and mozzy spray!

We had only booked 8-14 of june and went to another villa, but we loved it so much, that we ended up coming back to Pradha for the remainder of our trip. We also had a 12am flight back home, so we were able to leave our bags at reception from checkout, and come back have a shower and relax in their guest waiting room by reception where they also have a TV- talk about above and beyond service! 

If your travelling on your Honeymoon, with Family/ kids Pradha will suit all your needs and its such and tranquil quiet villa

Not a bad word to stay at all.. we hope to go back again for our anniversary, who knows there might be a mimi me with us then too…

title: Couldn't Stay Away

text:
There are so many lovely villas in Seminyak, so you should choose Pradha if you want to be near the beach (5 mins leisurely walk) and excellent service.
The staff at Pradha make it a point to get to know their guests, and they even remembered my daughter's food allergies after a few days and made sure that her breakfast didn't contain eggs.
The villa is very comfortable and spacious enough for our family of 5. The private pool is great fun, and there's even an outdoor shower in the master bathroom.
There is a good range of restaurants nearby, from the pricey KuDeTa to the more reasonably priced ones in Seminyak Square (with pretty decent live music on the Friday night that we were there).
title: Excellent service

text:
We decided to stay at Pradha Villas for our first time here in Bali and we are glad we did. The place is located off the beaten path but still within walking distance from Seminyak Square, where you can access some of the best dining spots in this area. Places like Potato Head, Kudeta and Sardines are just less than 5 mins via taxi and you take a stroll to bars like the quaint Motel Mexicola bar, Grocer & Grind and the lovely Sea Circus cafe for aussie inspired brekkie and bites. 

Pros : Great location, warm staff, good breakfast served in the villa, in-house massage in your villa plus room service till 10pm. Lovely little designer boutiques around the area. Peace and quiet with a large living room space for dining and entertaining. HUGE bathroom that directly connects to the private pool. Easy to access via cab as almost ALL cabs knew its location so we didn't have to worry about having to translate it to Bahasa Indonesia. DVD players both inside and outside the bed room and a kitchenette for preparation of small meals for your little ones if needed. Big pool and hot tub doubling up as kiddie pool too.

Cons: There are NO proper walking sidewalks all over Bali so be prepared to trek on muddy roads on your walk outside or even worse, get splashed on by inconsiderate tourists riding on bikes (The locals are much better at maneuvering the countryside roads). Do not attempt to walk further than the Seminyak Square in the hot sun if you are not used to walking in the sweltering hot weather.
Place is a little worn around the edges but well maintained to the best of its abilities. English speaking staff.

Tip: One of Seminyak's more popular spa is located right outside the villa's main road (opposite the Motel Mexicola) called Body Works but its almost 100% book while we are there so highly recommended that you making reservations first as the surly receptionist doesn't entertain walk in customers.
title: Warm staff, good enough service

text: The staff were excellent and the catered for all our needs. The villa itself is tired, can use a paint job. There was a lack of bath mats and when we asked for more they were gray and had seen better days. The breakfast was average and with no change. became boring when you are staying there for 7 nights. As there were 4 adults we only had 2 out door lounges, for 4 people another 2 lounges would have been good.
