text: We, with our 2 teenage children, moved from an Ubud 2-bedroom pool villa to Pradha 2-bedroom pool villa in Seminyak for our last 2 nights in Bali. Pradha Villas is relatively new and modern. The 2-bedroom villa is single-storey where the rooms are connected by a living/dining room/kitchen and the swimming pool. Having no common pool, each villa here has their own pools. We understand that the one-bedroom villas has a slightly larger pool then the 2-bedrooms but we were pretty happy with the size of the pool in our 2-bedrooms villa where you can swim in. Every room faces the pool. Modern dark-wooden furniture throughout - entering the Balinese double-door main entrance, you'll walk a few stone steps and a small pond to enter the living area where there's a large 3-seaters and 2-seaters sofa, a dining table for six and a kitchen with bar counter (no stove/oven) where a mineral water dispenser serves hot and cold water, an electric kettle, a fridge, cutlery and utensils all available for your use. Each of the bedroom has a queen-sized bed, a mini-bar fridge, a dressing area and a large attached bathroom with wardrobe, 2 sinks, a large bathtub and an outdoor shower area. The main bedroom's bathroom was bigger and the outdoor shower was really outdoors with high walls so that no one can see you but no roof above (thankfully it wasn't raining when we were there). My only gripe is the sharp corners of the beds that we kept walking into and the air-con in the main bedroom wasn't very effective in keeping it cool since this bedroom had the evening sun shining right in. There is also a small powder room so 3 toilets altogether in the whole villa! Extremely spacious villa. For those who don't mind walking in the heat and sharing the narrow roads with vehicles, the villa is a short 3 mins walk away from Seminyak Square where you'll find cafes and shops including a small gourmet supermarket. There is a short-cut from the middle of the long line of villas that lead you out to the main road and next to a spa where taxis are readily available (since it was the low season, we always got a taxi in less than 1 min). Because in Seminyak, taxis are readily available, the villas don't really provide a shuttle service although this can be arranged when the villa driver is available up till 5pm. Taxis costs an average of Rp25,000 (USD2.50) per trip. There are plenty of small shops and wonderful restaurants in Seminyak which somehow makes the whole place too touristy, losing some of its Balinese charm. Breakfasts are served in your villa, just order the day before. The pancakes were utterly delicious as were the omelettes! Coffee and tea are prepared in your kitchen. Food comes properly covered too.

text: While the service was prompt, friendly and professional, I think the product is getting tired and needs an update. We booked a 1-bedroom villa and was upgraded to a 2-bedroom villa with 1 room locked. We did not like that the master bathroom has an open ceiling at the shower area. That meant that we were unable to keep the mosquitoes out of the bathroom or use the shower when it rains. At the same time, the "open air" shower was not accessible from the outside, so we were unable to rinse off after a dip in the pool. Weird design. The wooden panelling around the pool deck is old, with some part of the wood splitting. Need to be careful otherwise you may get wood splinters in your feet when you walk on them. The pool is a good size, with a maximum depth of 1.4m. This was our favourite part of the villa and we spent most of our time in the pool. There is however, a hidden step at the deepest part of the pool. My hubby had on a few occasions stepped on the sharp edges of these steps, which were not marked out. Outdoor jacuzzi is nice with strong powerful jets, but a lack of hot water tap meant that it was a tad too cold to use it in the evenings after a long day out. Location wise, this villa is in the heart of Seminyak, so you can't really go wrong with that. We understand that there were 3 newer villas which were built 2 years ago, as compared to the ones we stayed in which were built 5 years ago. It may have been a better experience if we were placed in the newer villas.

title: Good value of money

text:
My boyfriend and I recently stayed here with another couple in a 2-bedroom villa.  Overall, the experience was great!  The villa was MUCH nicer than I had expected for the price and the location is great.  It is a short 5 minute walk to the main part of seminyak, so far enough where it is really quiet at night, but close enough to still feel a part of the action.

The villas themselves are really nice and have a modern feel to them.  They were very clean and when we asked about the mosquitos, the staff immediately tried to spray for anything we saw.  The morning breakfast was very good and they arrived on time every morning.  

The staff was very friendly and helpful.  We rented a car one day to drive up to Ubud and the hotel arranged everything.  We didnt even have to sign any paperwork.  It was the smoothest car rental any of us had ever experienced! 

The only con I would say is that I felt the bed was too firm for my taste.  I know a lot of hotels have firm mattresses... I just wished it was a little softer.

I would definitely stay here again and recommend it to my friends who are visiting bali!
title: Great Hotel and Location!

text:
For our last trip in Oct 2012, we picked Bali as our destination to try something new and we had been to quite a few places in Asia already.
It was not easy to find a hotel or resort to stay in Bali because there were simply too many! We were looking for a hotel which was good value for money, not necessary the top luxury or budget one. And we were glad to have chose this hotel.
First we were picked up by the hotel car from the busy Denpasar airport. After stuck in traffic, we finally arrived the hotel in late evening.
As a courtesy of our special occasion, we were upgraded to one bedroom villa which was recently refurbished. This looked much newer than those pictures saw online. Once entering the room, first we could see was living room which was linked to open private pool. The good thing about this was that we could swim anytime we like! 
Romantic set up with rose petals were placed in bedroom which was a nice touch. A heart-shaped cake was also sent to our room as amenity. 
We had pre-ordered breakfast to be sent to room, though it was just “okay”, it was a bit cold and taste was average.
The hotel was conveniently located and within walking distance to various must-go spots like Ku-de-ta and Potato Head. It also offered free shuttle service to beaches nearby. There was a massage place called Body Works which I would also recommend to try.
Overall, we were satisfied with the hotel stay and would also recommend those to try if you had limited budget but wanted to have a relaxing room with private pool in Seminyak area.
title: Summer Retreat in Oct

the prahda is the 5th villa we have stayed at in bali and was very good. Some of the others had hard beds but pradha had comfy beds.The only fault we found were the breakfasts.

I would definitely recommend another stay there: except for the customer service. Staff were never on time (for breakfast, cleaning, spa treatments, everything) and were overall not very friendly. title: Very relaxing time

text:
We had the opportunity to stay at PradHa Villas in December 2012.  We stayed in one of the 2 bedroom villas (with one room locked).  The benefits of this arrangement is that you get a MASSIVE Villa for the price of a much smaller one.

PraHda is located right between Bodyworks and Grocer and Grind, meaning that if you weren't too keen on scooter-ing around, you could walk to many of the Seminyak attractions without a hassle at all!  We did have scooters and were able to park them right outside out Villa door, making it easy to duck out for a spot of shopping or coffee.  Scooters through the Villa are about $5 a day, or just outside the Villa's side entry is a rental place where we got ours for $3.50 a day.

Breakfasts were included, and were absolutely perfect to get you going for the day.  The privacy of the Villas was wonderful too.  The only noise you could hear was the rooster next door who woke you of a morning!  There's a stack of construction happening right around Seminyak at the moment but PradHa is totally unaffected by this, making it a great find.

Design wise they were smart.  The sun beds get full sun from 8am till sundown.  So you can tan till your hearts content, or move them back to the grassed area under the shade if you start to smell the burn! hehe.  The 2 bedrooms are at opposite ends of the villa, meaning once you close your room doors, you are in total privacy and can't hear a thing (if you catch my drift!).

No hesitations in going back!!  

Enjoy!  

Jules
title: Quite tranquil villas slap bang in the middle of Seminyak

text: We really enjoyed the Pradha Villas. The villa itself (one of the older 2 bedrooms villas with one room locked as we'd only booked a one bedroom) we really liked, had a lovely 'tropical oasis' feel. The newer one bedroom villas are very fancy, but we thought they were so good that they ironically felt more like being in a 5 star Australian hotel rather than Bali...The service is very good and the villa is very close to Seminyak shops, Grocer and Grind etc. My only slight hesitation is that it is not inexpensive and the food quality of the dinner room service menu is a little average. text: Gotta say, we got it right with this place. Breakfast poolside was a great way to start each day. I doubt I'd want to stay anywhere else if returning to Seminyak.

title: Great villas

text:

The laneway leading to the villas is like something out of a movie set, the villa was spotless and like heaven on earth... We stayed in Villa 11 which is a one bedroom luxury villa. It is so quiet and in the morning we would lie in bed looking at our sparkling pool and listen to the birds chirping. The bed was so comfy - a four poster with netting. 

The staff were amazing, so helpful and polite and willing to help with any request with a smile.

It was so nice that our friends checked out of their villa and into Pradha villas! We also stayed an extra 3 nights instead of heading down to crazy legian.

A short cab ride away try La plancha beanbag bar on the beach....

We loved Pradha and highly recommed this place to anyone. We will be back!
title: Amazing

text:
Stayed at Pradha villas in October 12 for two weeks

Shared a one bedroom villa as part of the two bed villa however one room remained locked.  Dewa and staff at the villas are fantastic and willing to assist with any query.  The disappointing thing with the villas are that the two bedroom villas are very dated and need refurbishing.  Towels are Grey rather than white.. Either they need to change their laundry company or buy new towels.  You cant help but think things are a little grubby because of this.  The cleaning leaves abit to be desired and it is clear that there is no quality control over the villas cleaning standards.  It appears there is a checklist of things to be cleaned and thats all that is done.  For instance, there was an old icy pole stick stuck to our decking on the day we arrived.  It was still there a week later. similar was the top of the fridge, looked like it hadnt been wiped for months.  In the bathroom the space btwn the vanity and toilet was inches thick in dust and dead insects. Obvioulsy another area not on the list to clean.

It is such a shame because the location is good and the staff lovely but overall they charge way to much given the shabby and dated villas.

The one bedroom villas are quite new and much better condition although not sure that they Such small things to fix and this could become one of the best villas in Seminyak.

They either need to lift their game or reduce their price. You cannot ask 5 star prices and provide 3 star facilities.
title: Dated and needs refurb

text:
My husband, best friend and I couldn’t believe how lovely it was when we walked in to our Villa No 7. From the friendly reception staff to the attention from every other staff member from the beginning right to the end of our 7 nights, 13 Oct to 20 Oct. Can’t believe anyone could put in really bad reviews. Loved the open plan kitchen, dining, lounge room opening out to the wonderful pool. So private and we felt very safe and secure. The two bedrooms are separate buildings and designed very well. Spacious bedroom with TV/DVD (didn’t use it though) with a spacious bathroom. Only downfall was the bed was a bit hard, but we travel all over Asia and this is very common in every country, so are used to that. Still slept OK though. Don’t forget your mozzy spray! Great having late check out available as well.
Relaxed by the pool most of each day. Lots of nice restaurants and cafes nearby with Grocer and Grind right on the corner, so went there regularly for coffee’s.  We loved Chanti Restaurant, our favourite in Seminyak. Pradha is around the corner from Seminyak Square, 5 minutes from the beach and lots of lovely shops nearby. My husband surfed every morning and got some good breaks some days. We enjoyed the breakfast each day, having it brought to the room was a lovely treat and the staff were so friendly and we felt like we had known them all for ages!  Catered for my allergies to some foods. Thank you for making us feel at home. Keep all the staff, they are wonderful, each and every one of them. Free shuttle service was great, giving an hours notice is quite OK with us to go to Kuta, Legian, airport and other parts of Seminyak. 
Massage place called ‘Cool’ around the corner near Grocer and Grind, amazing! Ambience was so tranquil, best massage in Bali, ask for Lilli, she was great. Facial needs a bit of tweaking though. Try their Hair Spa. One hour of head massage and wash and dry. Nearly fell asleep.
We will definitely recommend Pradha Villas to all of our friends and will be back, if not next year, but year after! Thank you for such a lovely holiday!!
Jen, Gazza and Jaci.   : )

text:

title: dream come true

text:
Pradha had the worst customer service I have ever experienced in all my travels. Right from the start when we checked in, the front desk lady seemed upset with us because we had booked a great rate using a deal site. After experiencing genuine smiling faces during our entire Bali trip, her constant frown and negative attitude were quite off-putting  When we arrived at our villa, we immediately noticed that it was not well maintained. The empty hot tub was disgusting with rust, mildew, and mold covering the tiles. The pool floor was covered with algae, so we never once got in it. The shower was no better as I was forced to buy shower sandals from a nearby street vendor. When I complained about the condition, the front desk lady replied "why would you complain when you're paying such a cheap price?" Shocked by her reply, I told her I would note that in a negative TripAdvisor review and she bluntly replied "I don't care."

At this point, it's fair to say our stay in Seminyak was ruined, but the terrible service continued. The beds were uncomfortable and our breakfast was always served cold (and frankly didn't taste that good.) Then the dirty dishes would be left out for hours attracting bugs to our open villa. By our last morning, we opted not to get the free breakfast and instead went to a local coffee shop.

On our last day, we requested a late check out (our flight was at 6pm) and were denied. The front desk lady then reminded us twice that we had to be out by 12 noon. Later when we got back from breakfast, she asked when we were leaving and we told her a cab was coming at 12:15. She got upset and told us check out was at 12 not 12:15. We told her we didn't know how long the check out process was so we asked the cab to come a bit later. She relented but once again reminded us to be out by 12. As we were walking out of our villa at 11:58, the phone rang and it was the front desk lady asking us why we hadn't check out yet. Upset, I told her we had 2 minutes left and hung up on her.

Reading through the other reviews on Pradha, I simply don't understand how we had such a wildly different experience. If I could rate Pradha with 0 stars, I would in a heartbeat. Having traveled throughout Bali and experienced amazing customer service at every other villas, I'm surprised Pradha is even able to stay in business.

title: Absolutely Fantastic

text:
Here we are at the PradHa villas in Seminyak.  It is our first family holiday in many years and we were hoping for something truly special and that is exactly what we found!!!!

title: Superb As Usual

text:

text:

title: Perfect Location - Bliss !

photos.caption: The staff even organised free pool flowers!

text:
We are fussy and well seasoned travellers and regularly rely on TripAdvisor but this is our first review as we felt the need to thank Dewa, Fitri and staff for a truly excellent stay and great value for money! Our first time in Bali so we had researched Seminyak, in particular the trendy Pettitinget area very thoroughly and we definitely chose the right place to stay.  Villa 2 was absolutely stunning and the staff catered to our every need.

The location of the villa is EXCELLENT for all the beach clubs, restaurants and shopping that funky Seminyak has to offer.  Our favourite places in immediate proximity are Sea Circus cafe and Esthetic beauty salon (skip Bodyworks and although +spa across the road looks nice, could find better for their price). La Lucciola is also worth going along to for a meal right on the beach front. We spent some unforgettable nights at Pototo Head, Ku De Ta, W hotel, etc...all very nearby in a taxi which costs the equivalent of $1 per trip! For best manicure and pedicure, don't go past Amo day spa across the road from W hotel.

As a young group of 3 women, we chose to stay in the one bedroom with rollaway bed to save on costs (the second bedroom stayed locked) however this was still very spacious, especially with the double vanity and huge indoor/outdoor shower in the bathroom. 

Nothing was a problem for the staff - extra sun bed, power adapters, iPod cords...we are a demanding lot but they didn't mind :) they also brought in a reputable money changing agent to the hotel and helped us exchange our money which was much appreciated for us first timers.

For in room breakfast, go for a veggie omelette or the sensational banana pancake, otherwise head to Sea Circus around the corner for awesome coffee and food! Also we really enjoyed the nasi goreng via room service - the servings are not overly huge but very affordable prices.

Also have to mention the complimentary in room massages that were included in our stay. THE BEST WE HAD IN BALI, We need it again, thank you!

We want to give special thanks to the head of butlers, our main man Dewa, who was so very hospitable and nice to us throughout our stay. From the moment he picked us up from the airport to our last day, he was extremely helpful, kind and genuine. He knows his way around really well and was very happy to take us to our destinations everyday. Thank you our dear friend, and we will see you again for another breakfast at Grocer and Grind soon!

We've fallen in love with Bali and will be back to Pradha ASAP, thank you again for providing the best home for us during our amazing adventure! 
Love, 
Mona, Jasmine & Sonia

title: Heaven on Earth - on the island of god

text:
This was our first time in Bali and after much searching, asking and comparing, my sister and I decided that Pradha Villas were the way to go.  As soon as our driver picked us up from the airport, we knew we had made the right decision. Our concierge, Dwa, greeted us with his smile, promptly took our luggage and escorted us out of the airport and on the way to a memorable stay in Seminyak.

As soon as we arrived at our Villa we were overwhelmed with how beautiful and serene it was.  The pictures do not do this villa justice, it has an abundance of space, sunshine and is very clean.  The location is unbeatable, only minutes walk to some of the best places around Seminyak.

We were a party of 3 girls and had been upgraded to the 2 bedroom villa. But let me tell you that unlike the previous review, we were not complaining! There is so much space that we didn't know what to do with it!  These villas are huge and worth every penny! I am disapointed that the previous reviewer would give this amazing place such a bad wrap.  The staff are amazing and overly attentive, we never had a problem with the mosquito repellent (if anything it makes the experience even better as our villa was mosquito free all week).  We were more than happy to be upgraded to the 2 bedroom apartment even though they locked one of the bedrooms.  Seriously, you can't expect the Villa to pay for the extra servicing of an additional room if all you have paid for was a one bedroom (don't be so greedy!)

Our stay was made memorable by the beautiful staff at Pradha Villa, nothing was ever too much ( we had requests for i pod cords, international adapters, scissors, extra sunbeds, pillows etc etc and on each occasion our requests were fulfilled within minutes of asking).  We made friends with many of the lovely staff, especially our conceirge Dwa, he was attentive to every need and took care of us.  We already miss the smiles of our beautiful friends at Pradha Villas and we are already booking our next trip there!
title: Truly heaven on earth!

text:
Let me start off by saying that Seminyak was our last stop in Bali so we were really looking forward to this villa that we ended up choosing OVER the W Hotel (terrible idea!). All of our other villa stays in Bali were amazing, so we expected this to at least be the same.

When we arrived, they told us that they were putting us in a 2 BR villa since they were out of 1 BR. Excited for the upgrade, we went to the villa only to find that the second bedroom was locked. We asked if we could take a look at it, and they let us peek in and locked it back up. We decided to go up to the front desk and ask if it was possible to open up the second room for us since 1) there are 3 of us currently crammed into one room (we paid for an extra cot); 2) no one was using the other room and it would cost nothing to them to open the room up for us to make our customer experience better. Their answer? No, unless we pay up. We tried to explain that it wasnt our fault they stuck us in a 2 BR villa b/c they ran out of rooms. We explained that we received great customer service everywhere else and that it would make us a lot happier, but they were just focused on money and mentioned a contract with Agoda that doesn't allow them to upgrade people, which is complete crap since I've used Agoda before and have been upgraded free of charge without me asking. We were all angry by their service, and asked them if they cared about their TripAdvisor reviews and if we gave them a terrible rating, and I kid you not that the front desk lady straight out said, "No."

Aside from the unfriendly front desk people, the rest of the staff needs better training too, but not as much as the front desk lady. They also proceeded to spray mosquito repellant in our bedrooms, which made 2/3 of us sick afterwards. Breakfast, which was served to our villa, was left on our table for hours after eating.

There is a lack of attention to detail in the villa too. If you are looking to pay $250 a night for a mediocre villa and terrible waitstaff, then I would recommend this. Otherwise, I say to stay away. I don't understand how this place got 4.5 stars, but I'm assuming these reviewers must have been blind sighted.

I told the manager on the last day that I would recommend all the other places I stayed at in Bali to my friends, but not Pradha, and she said "Ok" and seemed fine with it.
title: Overpriced for Terrible Service and Mediocre Villa

text:
A return stay with Pradha villa. This time around we came with another couple friend and stayed in their 2 bedroom villa. We've tried out 6 accoms in Bali and feel that Pradha is certainly one of the BEST options in Seminyak in her price category. Here's what we love about Pradha:
1) The design and furnishing of the property. The villa is well designed. Although this is not a new villa, it is well designed with much thought put into quality furnishing/ finishings (proper timber used), care has been put into the upkeep of the place. You feel relaxed and at home here.
2) Location. Great location, near enough to main food/shopping areas, but tucked away enough so you don't hear the sound of traffic.
3) The Bathroom. Again well designed, roomy bathrooms with his/hers sinks, wardrobe, bathrub, and rainshower with open air well aboe. 
4) Pool/Garden. You have a full 275sqm for the two bedroom villa including the grounds, with a large private pool. Again well designed living area. You can slide open your bedroom door and walk straight into the pool! 
5) Service. Reception staff speak good English and are ever ready to help. They were very prompt and attentive. When they were cleaning the room when we were checking out, the staff found my digital camera and came running to the reception with it. Thank you!

The only areas for improvement are: i) Breakfast portions could be more generous, compared to the offerings of other villas, Pradha could certain look into this. ii) free shuttle service stops at 6pm and they only have 1 van. If that is out picking up customers at the airport then you need to get your own taxi. iii) Pillows are kind too 'high' and they only have one type of pillow. These are small suggestions for Pradha to consider :)

All in we truly enjoyed our stay here and will certainly return again. Thank you Pradha villa!

text: We recently stayed at the Pradha Villas in Seminyak.  It well exceeded our expectations.  The rooms where beautiful with your own private pool, lounge and dining area and kitchen. title: Amazing

text:
Upon Arrival at Pradha Villas for our honeymoon my husband and I were greeted with fresh watermelon juice, what a nice touch. Afterall we arrived at 1am in the morning. Upon entrance into our 1 bedroom villas, we were simply amazed. Absoluetly gorgeous. Our own kitchen, living room, generous swimming pool, beautiful decor and complementary wifi. The one bed room was right next to our private pool, just steps away and I literally would roll off my bed right into the pool. The bathroom was also something to brag about. Open air ceiling above the shower and a large beautiful tub. Everything about this property was beyond my wildest dream. We had breakfast, every morning delivered complentary with the package we purchased and to my surprise very good. The fruit was fresh and my poached eggs were perfect, oh might I mention sumantra coffee is to die for. 
Words for the wise... around Seminyak,kuta, and the legion areas the beaches are not really swimable, simply because they are not very clean. I'm born and raised on Kauai my entire life and the beaches were nothing compared to any of the beaches on Kauai, especially the north Shore. Spend as much time in your secluded villa getting massages and drinking arak and bintangs. It will make for a delightfull get away. Traffic in this area is bizzarre. If you are looking for more of a beachy area go to uluwatu, the beaches are better there, but still nothing like Kauai. 

Villa Pradha thank you for a memorable stay.
title: From Kauai To Seminyak

text:
It was my first time to Bali and I chanced upon Pradha Villas on agoda.com. I must however state that the reviews do not do the villa justice because the reviews are not good enough!

Pradha Villas is located in the heart of Seminyak and just 10 mins by foot away from the beach. The villas are just 30 mins drive from the airport and less than an hour and a half from many of the attractions (Ubud, Tabah Lot, etc). 

The hotel staff are extremely friendly and are very willing to help. I emailed them for information about Bali and they promptly replied after doing some research.

Most importantly, the rooms are perfect. The private villa provides the privacy one requires and certainly adds the icing on the already very beautiful cake.

There is no doubt I will go back to Pradha Villas on my next stay and that I will certainly recommend anyone to stay there.
title: The villa made me want to go back to Bali again.

text:
I stayed at the Pradha Villa with my wife and 2-year-old daughter in May 2012.

We were initially nervous about sharing a bedroom with our daughter in the single bedroom villa, however the space was enormous and well exceeded our expectation. The pool was also bigger than we imagined and proved a great way to start, and finish the day.

A few nights we ordered dinner in, and found the food both cheap and of good quality. And, like everywhere in Bali, the service was friendly throughout.

The beach is only 5 minute walk away, however like all of Seminyak, there are very few safe sidewalks, so any venture out (particularly with a toddler) was a little treacherous.

The blue cabs are particularly cheap, and proved a great solution for short or medium length trips. In hindsight I wish we took more advantage of this during our stay.

I'd thoroughly recommend the Pradha Villa.
title: Excellent Villa

text: We recently spent a week at Pradha Villas and thoroughly enjoyed our stay. The two bedroom villa was lovely with a great outdoor area and an open plan living area. The staff were extremely friendly and were willing to help you out in any way. They helped us out by booking restaurants and organising transfers to and from Legian and Kuta (which is for free as it's included with the villa). The breakfast was good, although can get monotonous over the week so we went down to Grocer and Grinder a few times for breakfast. Overall we had a wonderful week at Pradha Villas and have no complaints.
title: Great location and friendly staff

text:
My girlfriend and I stayed here for a week and it was truly a great experience. The staff was completely at our service: Airport to villa transport, day-trip planning, access to their computers and printers, free massages- just to name a few. The villa itself also exceeded our expectations. We stayed in one of the luxury villas, which were brand new, modern, private and about as state-of-the-art as a villa can be.

I looked at about ten other villas and ended up booking with Pradha because it was by far the best value for our money. This will definitely be my go-to villa the next time I visit Bali.
title: Everything we expected and MORE

text:

title: Great location, quiet villas and great staff

text: I booked into this villa for 8 days with my 4 months old baby. Booked 2 bedrooms villa thinking it will be more spacious as i dont intend to go out much. title: WORST VIlla

text:
We stayed here two nights, and found a deal on Agoda for around $220-00 p/n ( USD ) including breakfast.
It was only a one bedroom villa, but to our surprise we got given a two bedroom one, not that we used the second room.
It was beautiful- not brand new, but very well kept indeed.
The staff were very friendly and helpful. The bed was lovely, and the outdoor shower was very clean.
We did have as swim too, in our private pool, and it would be great to stay here for longer and really enjoy it. Sadly the Spa was empty and I think it didn't work.

They are building next door, so there was a little noise during the day, but at night very quiet.
The location is also great, just a short walk to Semiyak Square shops, a Taxi rank and some other shops and restaurants. There is a shortcut you can take near Villa No 6 and 7 ( we were in Villa 7 ) which saves you walking past reception and going down the driveway.
Reception will organise a Taxi if you need one, and we also had free transfer to the airport when we left.
Breakfast was fine, and we had a nice room service once as well. 
Laundry was a little expensive for what we've paid in the past in Bali, but they get it back to you the next day, regardless of when you drop it off, and nicely folded- so no complaints there!
As a lovely gesture, we were chasing a cotton cover for our water cooler at home, and we asked reception if they had one spare they could sell.
Just before we were due to go to the airport, a staff member came to our villa, and said we could have the one in our kitchen. Very nice of them!
Also I must comment the security staff were also excellent. They were polite and friendly, and took note of the Taxi number whenever we were picked up- very professional.

All in all, a wonderful stay- we will definitely come back here again, thank you!
title: Quiet, clean and great service

text:

The staff are willing to help at all costs and made us all feel very comfortable. The rooms were cleaned exceptionally well each day. The breakfast was delivered on time everyday and the food was of decent quality. Especially loved the Nasi Goreng.

Look forward to coming back again soon. Special thanks to Putu and Nia.

text:
During my recent two week stay in Bali I spent the first week in Seminyak and Ubud and then returned to Seminyak for the last 4 days ! Unsure of where to stay i stumbled across Pradha Villas ! title: BRILLIANT STAFF, GREAT VILLAS

text:
During one stay in Bali, we went wandering to find a nice place to stay next time we visited Bali. We come across one little inconspicious sign that pointed its way down a alley towards the Dusun Resort and Villa Aqua. 
When we walked through the main gate of Pradha Villas we were impressed by the staffs hospitality in receiving us, even though it was quite clear that we had only come to enquire about accomodation and pricing. We were offered a cold drink and the sales manager took us through to look at the property. 
The two bedroom units were quite standard villas for the area with one bedroom under the main roof and the second bedroom in a separate pavillion next to the pool. Not really suitable if you have young children who might go wandering to come looking for Mum and Dad in the middle of the night.
What caught our eye was the one bedroom deluxe units that were fabulous. The layout of the unit was great with a small kitchen, flat screen TV and entertainment unit, pool straight of the lounge room and separate bedroom which you able to lock up securely and also step straight into the pool. The bathroom was large and open and very clean with no sign of dampness or mosquitoes that we have encountered at other places.
Loved coming back to the villa just to laze around during the midday heat. An ideal place for a couple getaway. Even had friends who were staying at other locations come back for drinks around the pool one night and all thought it was 'Hollywood'.
Staff were always willing to help with queries and every staff member from security guard through to gardeners always acknowledged you as you passed them
Only one thing I can grumble about is the pool didn't really get to see much sun therefore never really got the chill off the water, which is unusual for Bali climate.
Thanks for the enjoyable stay.

title: You could do better for the money

text:
We booked Pradha due to location and villa layout.
We ended up paying $240p/n for 2 bdr villa
On arrival we were meant to be picked up from airport. They were running 20 mins late so left us sitting around in the heat which wasn't the welcome I wanted for friends traveling with us to Bali for the first time.
We got to villas and proceeded to book in. This took way to long and seemed very confusing and was alot more difficult and slow process than it should have been.
We were shown to our villa and on arrival werent impressed. Had been raing and one of the roofs in one of the 2 bedrooms was mouldy and the the bed was all wet.
After a quick phone call I ws told that they had no other villas available and they would have to call back.
After 10 mins I got a call back saying that another villas will be ready on around 20 mins once its finished been cleaned.
We tried to order some drinks and food communicating that we would like in our new villa once we moved. This proved to cause major confusion the the front desk taking our order and ended up having to call back in the space of 5 mins 3 times to clarify what our order was and when/how we wanted it.
Communication between us and staff for the duration of our stay caused us several problems and frustrations.

The 2nd villa we were showed was much better. Grass on lawn and gardens were heaps better and general design and quality of furniture and decking etc was much better.
Why they were so different I couldnt figure out why they would do up one but not the other.
But most importantly the rooms were dry.
Breakfast from the Pradha villas was a major let down. We only had once then after that just walked out to cafe and restaurants nearby to get a much better breakfast and coffee.
The food from room service too was pretty bad and below bali standards, We ordered some burgers "took 50 mins to arrive" only to get them and they were all raw and not cooked meat paddie. We complained and had them apparently recooked btu they came back 30 mins later exactly the same.
After this we didnt order anything else and chose to eat elsewhere in Seminyak.

One of my and my freidns major gripes was seeing them come in and clean the villas.
They would come in with a cloth and mop only.
How they managed to clean effectively and not spread bacteria with just cloth and mop... I dont know. 
No bucket or chemicals in hand.
Quite a few times we needed to remind them to change the shower gel and shampoo etc beacuse it was empty.
The english of the front desk manager and staff would cause us alot of confusion from asking for things to planning our days.
Alot of things with the room that were missing were ash trays.. on request I was given a old red ashtray that was filthy. I was shocked.
We also needed to request a bottle opener as none was supplied and each bottle of water in villa required one.
In summary the location was good but communication and cleanliness killed it for us.
Would I stay here again.. probably not as b yBali standards this place didnt live up to expectations.
title: Not Bad, But not great- Little things annoyed.

text:
Visited Bali in Oct 2009 and stayed here as I was looking for a different pool villa to stay at ( stayed at the Aston Sun Island Villa, which was also amazing!). The villa is located on a secluded street(cab drivers will surely know where it is so if you arrive via cab, its no prob). Its quiet enough that you dont hear motorcycles on the road and our villa was just beside the road. The walls are high enough that it gives alot of privacy and security not to mention there are guards outside even late at night. 

The living room & kitchen is open air but need not worry about mosquitoes at night as they provide mosquito coils. The bedroom is accesible via sliding door( if you take one step out, the pool is just there) and another main door and it is completely covered up and airconditioned and the toilet is quite amazing:) There's a tub(sea salt provided for scrub), a shower room and a large washing up area. All living and hanging out areas are clean.

The pool is big enough for you to swim and just laze around and no one really complained even when we had the music on from the DVD player while drinking beer next to the pool:) Breakfast is served in your room although the selection is not that great and portion quite small however there are pots,pans, utensils etc readily available for you to cook your own breakfast. 

There's a row of shops + supermarket within 3-5min walk where you can stock up on local/foreign beers and food. There's also a spa(not too expensive but dont expect a 5star spa) within 3-5min walk as well. 

If you're bored with the pool, Seminyak beach is 10 min walk away. There are almost no peddlers trying to sell you stuff and you can just laze around there. Quite a few other hotels/villa nearby although i cant recall what they are called.

Hotel also offers free one way transportation to Kuta or the airport and restaurants like Ku De Ta and Ultimo are around 10-15 walk away. Staff speaks fairly good english.

All in all, its not the most expensive villa, certainly on the lower priced pool villas in Seminyak but it is really quite amazing! If you need more info, feel free to drop a message!
title: Beautiful and perfect!

text:
We made our first trip to Bali in August 2009. After spending ages reading reviews on Trip Advisor, we decided on Pradha villas  and I'm glad we did. They collected us from the airport, received the usual drinks and fresh towel on arrival. Friendly, smiley, relaxed staff. 

Our villa was huge, 2 bedrooms (but as we had booked 1 bed they just kept the other room locked), big open air living area, great bathroom with bath and open air shower, private long pool and a jacuzzi.  Nicely decorated. Staff came every day to clean. 

Breakfast was probably the one thing i would describe as ok rather than excellent, it was a bit on the small side, but you could easily order more and it was cheap. 

The Villa was well located, walking distance from La Lucciola, Living Room, Breeze at the Samaya, etc.

I really loved Bali - perfect weather and the best food i've ever had on a holiday. All of the above had fantastic food (Warisan is another one to visit).
title: Great location, huge rooms, luxury

text:
We stayed in these villas just for one night. Our original accomdation had double booked our first night so they sent us here instead. I'm glad they did! The villas are gated which you can only get into through talking to recpetion - very secure.  I wish we could have stayed the whole week! It was really raining when we arrived and the staff wouldn't let me out of the car until they had an umbrella to stop me getting wet. Very kind of them!
Check in was quick and we were given a lovely chilled juice. We ordered our breakfast for the next morning then shown to our villa. Our bags were carried by the staff and as we entered our villa I just though wow! It was fab! Open plan kitchen/living area out onto the pool area and grass. The bedroom was a separate room with bathroom. There was a second bedroom next to the pool but we didn't have the key as we weren't using it. The staff were all very helpful. We were playin with a blow up ball in the room and we knocked it into the next villa. We phoned recpetion and asked them to get it back. I don't think they understood as they sent someone to talk to us. We evenutally got it back after we spoke to someone who could understand us!
We booked two one hour Balinese massages. The ladies turned up in our villa with all the equipment and we had a lovely massage each while listening to the rain, very relaxing! I wish we had more time to make use of the spa treatments as they were so cheap! Just 150,000 rupees for each massage! (work out at £10 GBP!) At our next villa they were much more expensive! We then ordered room service for dinner, excellent food and again so cheap!
Breakfast was brought to our vill and set up for us. Very good food again. When we checked out someone came and collected our bags for us. 
The staff are all extremely helpful. The food was great, and the spa treaments excellent. Everything was an excellent price and I wish we could have stayed longer!
title: Wonderful villas, should be higher up!

text:
Mein Freund und ich waren für 3 Nächte in einer luxury one bedroom poolvilla. Es war unsere 1. Destination in Bali und wir waren erstaunt, dass wir an dieser perfekten Lage (5min. vom Seminyaksquare), trotzdem unsere Ruhe hatten. 
In verschiedenen Bewertungen konnte man lesen, dass es Probleme mit dem Pickup am Flughafen gegeben hat. Unser Fahrer hat mit einem Schild mit meinem Namen darauf in der Wartehalle gewartet, worüber man mich vorher per E-Mail auch informiert hatte. Es klappte also alles einwandfrei.
Die Villa ist sauber und sehr gemütlich. Da Wohnzimmer/Küche und Bad offen sind, haben wir uns Sorgen gemacht, dass es zu viele Mücken geben könnte. Doch jeden Abend kam das Personal und hat die Zimmer eingesprüht und Insektenspiralen angezündet. Das Schlafzimmer, welches man abschliessen kann, hat AC, ein riesiges, bequemes Bett mit Mückennetz und gute Abdunkelungsvorhänge. Der grosse Pool ist ein Traum, leider waren die Liegestühle nur am Vormittag an der Sonne, aber wahrscheinlich ist es besser so, man sollte ja sowieso nicht an der prallen Sonne liegen.
Wir möchten uns ganz herzlich beim Personal bedanken. Alle waren so herzlich und zuvorkommend, wir haben uns richtig willkommen gefühlt. Uns hat es so toll gefallen, dass wir die letzten 3 Tage von unserer Balireise nochmals zurückkehren wollten, doch leider waren alle Villas ausgebucht. Die Receptionisten haben uns sogar geholfen eine andere Unterkunft zu finden, wir haben uns dann aber spontan für ein Hotel in Amed entschieden. Die letzten Stunden vor unserer Abreise nutzten wir um noch Souvenirs in Seminyak zu kaufen. Obwohl wir zum Schluss nicht in den Pradha Villas übernachtet haben, durften wir unser Gepäck kostenlos dort deponieren und sogar die Dusche benutzen. Vielen herzlichen Dank für alles, wir kommen wieder.
title: Oase im busy Seminyak

text:
La villa è indubbiamente bellissima, grande e spaziosa. Ma :
Abbiamo chiamato la reception perché la porta della camera non si chiudeva( serratura rotta).  
Nessuno è mai venuto a riparla 
Stessa cosa per l’idromassaggio della piscina
Una sera abbiamo prenotato un massaggio in camera . Le massaggiatrice erano in ritardo per colpa del traffico, a detta della reception. Dopo 40 minuti di Attesa, ce ne siamo andate via scocciate. 
È ingiustificabile: se c’ È traffico ( e si sa che a semyniak è sempre pieno!!!) parti prima. 
Ma il peggio deve ancora venire: un giorno ci avevano visti uscire presto per andare in gita con un autista. A sorpresa siamo rientrate abbastanza presto e abbiamo trovato nella nostra villa operai che facevano lavori nell’ altra camera ( noi avendo prenotato la villa con una camera, avevamo l’altra stanza chiusa a chiave). Probabilmente, fiduciosi del fatto che noi fossimo via tutto il giorno, hanno pensato bene di “ portarsi avanti con i lavori per i prossimi clienti . In effetti per noi era il giorno pre partenza.
Siamo dovute rimanere a aspettare i loro comodi nel viale alle 5 di pomeriggio.
Poi: attenzione La strada che porta alla villa di notte è buia e isolata. Fa davvero paura, sopratutto per due ragazze sole.
La colazione in camera non mi è piaciuta, aveva pochissime cosa dolci ma era tutto incentrato sul salato (poco adatto a noi italiani).

text:
2008年4月に宿泊しました。
部屋は非常に広く、ヴィラとしては最高峰なのだと思います。

このヴィラの特徴としては、プールが大きめで、2部屋あるうちの1つのベッドルームからは直接プールに入ることもできること。
そして食事をダイニングまで持ってきてくれるため、部屋内で朝食も食べられること。

また、シャワールーム、バスタブ、トイレについては半屋内、半屋外という配置になっています。
ポイントはこの半屋外というところ。
夜シャワーを浴びたり、お風呂に入っていると夜空が見えます。

一方でヴィラとバリ島の宿命として、どうしても虫という問題があります。
シャワーを浴びていたり、バスタブを使用している際に半屋外となっているため虫が気になってしまいます。

ベッドルームだけはキッチリと仕切れるので蚊取り線香を持っていけば問題はありませんが、その他のスペースを利用する際には虫が気にならなければ素晴らしいと思います。
（そもそも虫が苦手なのであればヴィラを選ばない方が良いと思いますが）

バリでヴィラ宿泊を望むのであればオススメです！
